The quality of what I thought !, I was purchasing and what I was actually getting. To be able to estimate all my daily activities to know what I actually burned. The quality of  food knowledge and updates is invaluable and unlike any other app out there for A healthy lifestyle! The only improvement is to delete doubles n triples of same products.

title: Best health tracking up out there
body: This app really tracks what you eat, and makes it so much easier. You just scan the food you eat and most if not all of them are available, and the choices are growing everyday. It really opened my eyes through a lot of things. The app doesn't leave you alone to figure out how to keep healthy! It has newsletters, community sections, recipe ideas submitted by the app users, etc. It's so involved in what you do, you don't need safari to get through. I highly recommend this app before trying others. So thankful this exists. Other health tracking apps aren't this simple and fun. It's colorful and inviting, this is the only health tracking app I'll ever use. You'll love it

title: Top 10 Best iPhone Apps
body: I just started a vegetarian diet and need to rely on food information much more than I have in the past using the normal criteria for shopping. I was surprised to see that even the products I bought in my local health food store were often not the best choices available. (Ex:  too much sugar; more salt than daily requirements, etc.) Another great feature of this app is that they not only give you info about what you are about to buy as quickly as you can photo the barcode, but with one more click you can see what the better options are- and those products might be right next to the product you were about to purchase!

title: Horrible "upgrade": from awful to worse
body: Just when we thought it was as bad as it could get, they made it worse. First, they removed GMO info and placed it in a separate app that was $4.99! That was short-lived. Now, that same price only gets you a three-month "subscription." Want info on GMOs and gluten? Oh, you get to buy TWO subscriptions! And it's nowhere near April Fool's Day.

title: Great App!
body: I have been using Fooducate for about four months now and it has been instrumental in helping me attain and maintain the goals I have set out for myself. I have not upgraded the app but am considering it to fine tune my intakes. One of the thing that sets this app apart from other calorie counting apps is the letter-grade rating of the foods you are eating. Therefore, while watching the number of calories you are eating, you are also looking at the quality of the calories being eaten.  There are a couple of things that can be improved, such as west coast food and ethnic food selections, but overall the app is fantastic and I have recommended it to many people.

title: Awesome and informative
body: Great product. Many of the foods I eat are already in the database and those that aren't I can put in myself and enter in the nutritional facts. Makes it extremely easy to keep track of carbs, calories, and food points. Definitely would recommend to others (and I have). I have some food allergies so I purchased the pro version, the only thing I would like to see added would be that when grades are shown for a product, it would show me the grade based off of my personal information as well as the grade that would be given to somebody who didn't have any custom preferences.

title: exactly what I wanted
body: I told my boyfriend I wanted an app that calculated my nutrient and caloric intake by using a database that knows what nutrients are in specific brands and other more general things like an apple. I discovered this app shortly after telling him that and this app does exactly that. You can look up your favorite brands and it is so easy to add it in to what you ate today. You don't have to look at the panel and enter in every % this app does it for you. You can even look up menu items from your favorite restaurants and the app will tell you if it fits your diet and fitness goals. This app will really help me transition in to a vegan lifestyle and be healthy about it!

title: Love this app
body: That the database is able to constantly expand due to user support is just amazing. Also having access to so much information, from recipes to individual nutritional values along with explanations and alternatives, allows one to really personalize any dietary goals and habits to their liking. What's more, this app allows for exercise input to calculate calorie burn alongside intake. Meals can be saved, recipes favorited, authors followed, goals changed, calorie quality rated, products scanned, entered, or searched, or submitted, and there is perpetual support from the community. If ever you were wanting to make healthier choices and change your food-centric lifestyle, this is an app you want.

title: Great to use as a way to double-check your eating.
body: I've been using another app (MyFitnessPal) to track my calories for a few months now. Recently, I turned to this app as a way to get more in-depth info about how healthy the food I'm eating really is. Up front, this app provides great information on packaged food products and makes you feel great about making healthy choices. Unfortunately, this app doesn't provide much information on items that don't come with a barcode. Additionally, most of the alternative choices it provides you with are expensive organic editions or just plain difficult to find. For a college student with limited means, this app is not easy to follow.

title: BG MyFitnessPal...My New Fav Food/Nutrition Tracker
body: I really like this app because of the food grades. It shocks me to realize what are Cs and Ds that I thought were better. It's only been a week and I won't say it's changed my bad habits completely, but the detail analysis it provides is very helpful/insightful. I want to subscribe to Pro, but I can't remember my Apple Restrictions password to purchase in App and there's not a Pro option to purchase directly from the App stores, so I can't (Can you fix that?). The only con I have is that the database of food is kind of limited (250k I believe), but you can always add your own recipes and they're quick about adding something that they can verify.

title: Best food app I've seen
body: My nutritionist recommended this app to record food weight activity.

title: Perfect app
body: I needed a way to track the food and calories I eat every day and this goes above and beyond. This is perfect and I have found it to be very well-designed and intuitive. My only qualm is that some product's grade ratings are off (I've only noticed this with two out of probably 40 items I've scanned so far) so just be wary of that and, when in doubt, go by the nutrition facts/ingredients instead.

title: Fooducate has been my bible
body: This app is amazing. Nothing like picking up Jif peanut butter like you always have because "choosey mom's choose Jif" rings in your ears every time you're shopping...only to do a search and alternative find and discover, *GASP* Skippy is way better for your kids...and if you want to go one step further, an all natural alternative is available. Try giving your kids a peanut butter that is made from nothing but peanuts rather than one packing some form of syrup or hydrogenated oil as the key ingredients. Now I do this with nearly everything I buy thanks to fooducate, and have dropped 10 pounds with little awareness I've even made a lifestyle change.

title: Awesome app!
body: I love this app simple because it gives detail on every product you scan! Love the fact that they show you the alternatives and why that certain food product is good for you. It tells you what ingredients are good for you and what to look or in the ingredients. If the food product is rated in the low range, it will explain why and what ingredients you need to watch out for. This is obviously a great app to use when you go grocery shopping because it lets you scan products to see if it is healthy or not before u even buy it and also change your diet and eat healthier. I highly recommend this app!

title: Easier than counting calories
body: I've been using this app for about a week. I'm also a fan of MyFitnessPal because it syncs with my Fitbit. I've taken to tracking my food with Fooducate because I find it easier than counting calories. Although Fooducate also tracks calories,you're always under your goal if you mainly eat foods that are good for you. I'm talking about eating A and B grade foods most of the time. This allows me to eat when I'm hungry without worrying about how many calories I have left because the healthy foods are naturally lower in calories. Fooducate helps me choose healthy alternatives for my favorites without feeling deprived

title: BESTS app out there for eating healthy
body: This app is NOT a meal planning app, it is simply a diet tracker and nutrition app. That being said, it's the best I've found. I use Yummly to find recipes and makes my shopping lists and this app lets me find the healthiest choices to buy when I go shopping! It's simple, scan a barcode or search a product and it gives you a VERY detailed description of what's in the product, why it's good/bad, alternatives, warnings and/or reasons why it's healthy. I love it, this app is everything I was looking for!

title: Best food logging app ever!!!!
body: I love this app for logging food. It has been so easy to use. I love the grading system, the breakdown of how much real food vs processed food. Also the breakdown percentage of carbs, fat and Protein  It's so awesome that it even calculates how much natural sugars and added sugars are consumed. Big bonus that it links my workouts for my other apps and automatically adds them. My only suggestion to improve it for consumers is that calculating fiber not be a upgrade but a standard feature. It is so critical for good health and a big component in the fight against obesity and diabetes to make it a standard feature would be the right thing to do.

title: Warning of a few issues
body: I use this app on my iPhone 4 and since the 2015 update with the new pie chart on the health tracker page, the page now fails to load and gives me a timed out error more times during the day than it loads to allow me to add items. When the phone is trying to load the pie chart it will not allow the phone to do anything else, it does not register a missed call if someone tries to call while it's loading. The new measurements for the recipe or for the health tracker are great additions. I fear I may need to delete the app, since it has gotten difficult to use.

title: Amazing!
body: This app is amazing! Many times we are misled by words in the packaging like "all natural" "low fat" etc. a simple scan of the product quickly details differently. Many apps are complicated with long explanations but once you scan a product it gives you a grade!! Now we all have been in school and know that an A is better than a C! I find myself at whole foods putting back food that I think it's healthy and when I scan it, it gives it a C-!! If you do get a bad grade on a product there is an alternative tab that gives you suggestions on what you should buy instead!! Great app!!!!

title: Fooducate is a life-saver
body: I use Fooducate all day long!

title: Great calorie app!!!
body: I've downloaded several apps and deleted several apps.  This one is by far the best!!  The grading scale helps you make better choices.  I love the pie chart for percentage on carbs, fat and protein.  There are so many interesting things too this app that are not only helpful but it keeps you engaged.  I've recommended this app to others and I am evening thinking of purchasing the premium upgrade.  Take a bit to get use to where thing are but give it time.  It's a great app!!  This is a genuine review!  Try the free download and decide for yourself. All I can say is I really like it and there are NOT loads of ads on the app either.

title: Could be great with a few fixes
body: At first I thought this app was fantastic. A great alternative to weight watchers with an even better explanation of each food's nutrition, and still a points system to count the value of your food instead of just the calories. This was great, EXCEPT it doesn't have food points for every item. In fact because it's based on user input, most unpackaged items that I put on my list didn't have an adequate amount of nutrition facts therefore the app couldn't calculate the point value. It's kind of useless to my diet if I can't count the points of every thing that I eat. I was using fitness pal but I don't want to count calories because it's not as productive as point values. Anyway, I'm deleting the app, but if they update the system and assign point values to everything, then I would totally use it religiously.

title: All You Need
body: After getting sick of the layout of the other diet apps, I decided to download this one just to see the grades of the foods I was eating. I was pleasantly surprised to find that not only can you see the facts and grades of the foods you consume, but also track your weight loss. This app has every thing you need in one place and is laid out in a easy and fluid manner. Unlike the other apps that let you list what you've eaten, this app tells you whether or not the calories were worthwhile. Everything I need in one place. This app was a refreshing replacement to the mundane layout of other nutrition and diet ones.

title: Deal breaker features missing
body: I've been comparing several of these apps and now it's down to this one and Lose It!  If fooducate had the following 3 features my decision would be simple because its food database has more of the foods i scan from costco and recipes and i like being able to take a photo of the food and use that in place of an icon.  what fooducate doesn't have is a way to separate breakfast, lunch, & dinner items that have been logged and it's interface is not nearly as pleasingly designed as Lose It! Hybrid vigor, that's what's needed.  Also I haven't figured out how to get a log of the total vitamins in the foods I've consumed, even though those numbers are in the nutritional information for the foods I ate.

title: Great tool that allows me to make better choices!!
body: I've been using for 2 weeks, I take out my phone to scan food prior to buying. Making what I bring home the first part of my healthy choices. I stayed on the suggested calories but then dropped another 200 (based on my trainers recommendation) eating healthier made it easier. Such a great tool.  Tried to get my husband to install app on his phone but didn't come with same bells. And whistles as the apple products. Easy to add products not available.

title: This app is amazing!
body: I was simply looking for a an app to help me make sure I'm covering all my bases and getting enough nutrition in my diet. This is everything I could've asked for and more, and so easy! You can simply scan the barcode of an item and get so much info on it. My first test was with canned tuna: It showed me the nutrition facts, the A through F grade of how good this is for me, info on other similar products with better grades that I'll likely end up buying, and education on how tuna fish makes it's way from sea to can! How cool! So glad I happened upon this. Fooducate lives up to its name: Very educational. So helpful! Thanks!

title: Awareness
body: Even if you think you know how many sugars, fats, carbs, lack of protein, etc you have a day... You don't until you keep a food log. And this has been the easiest awareness-centric app I've found (coming from someone thats downloaded 10+). It scans labels, let's you pick portions, and almost always has the food I'm searching for. Suggested improvements would be to allow supplement tracking and or adding items when/if they are juiced or blended. I juice green veggies daily and the nutritional value isn't the same as eating them. So I have to compensate. Otherwise A+ app. Also- link with FitBit!

title: I love it!
body: About a year or two ago, my older sister discovered this app. She kept praising it endlessly, and when she showed me how it works, I (being the stubborn younger child) begrudgingly admitted it was cool. Skip to about a month ago: I was in a human nutrition college class, but it was my first class of that nature, and I was very lost with the material. I decided to look up the app my sister was telling me about then. It's not only saved my grades in the class with it's easy-to-understand explanations, but now I'm using it constantly and taking nutrition to heart. Never thought I'd be a health fanatic like my sister, but I'm happy I've become one!

title: Spectacular App
body: This app is pretty spectacular. It provides a high level of detail about all of the ingredients in a product and warnings about items to be concerned about. All of my eating habits are changed for the better because of this app. I would never have thought some of the products I was eating contained some of the bad things they did. Now I look everything up and check ingredients and once you've don't that a couple of times you really just know what is ok to eat and what to avoid in large quantities. I have lost over 80 pounds using the guidance from this app. Highly recommended.

title: System is off a few beats
body: This app is definitely on to something great but the execution needs some work. Categories need their own rating system. You can't rate all sugars a c because they are sugars. I want an f through a rating for sugars where the best sugars in their category are an A and the worst are an F. I don't want all sugars to be a C because they are just sugars. You can't put 100% pure maple syrup at a c and then also put corn syrup at a c. Same goes for baby formula. No formula gets better then a c because "breast milk is the best". That may be true but breast milk is not a formula so the ratings shouldn't be compared to breast milk. They should be compared to the ingredient list vs other ingredients in other formulas. I've only used the app a little bit but I've already found several cases like this. I'm sure there are many more.

title: Love the recommendations!
body: Looking forward to the additions that continue to be updated.  I upgraded to the pro version, like the additional health info provided and the 12 newsletters.

title: Pretty great app!
body: I'm a type 1 diabetic and adamantly trying to keep away from that fructose, dextrose, etc. nonsense... So I'm using it for the sugar intake features, not using the weight loss features.

title: Awesome App!
body: This app is fast and provides excellent perspective.  Aim the scanner at the barcode and it automatically captures it and with a second you have the info.  We're trying to eat healthier and it may take me longer to shop for awhile but if I make better educated choices it's all going to pay off in better health.    It does not analyze supplements and local brands aren't built into the database.  It does ask for help though so if you take the time to provide information it will help everyone else.

title: Unproved Claims about why food is "bad"
body: Good for the obsessive dieter that basically starves themselves and obly thinks about avoiding everything "bad". A bad app for people with common sense that don't subscribe to the latest trends that dictate what is good for you and what is bad.

title: Overall best app in the health category
body: This app absolutely rocks!! The database of food is endless. The food grades and explanations are so helpful. I'm amazed at the difference in food quality even amongst products under the same brand. They make adding new products completely easy and convenient plus you get notified when your new product's grading is added to the database. I can't express how awesome this app is. My appreciation goes out to the creators of this app. They are truly consumer advocates and care about educating us on the food we eat and feed to our families. Get this app today- I promise you won't be sorry.

title: Love love love this app
body: I am on weight watchers so sometimes when I don't have the nutrition label to look at I look up the food in this app and I can see the food points value! And if they don't have the food they make it really easy to take pics and email it to them so they can place it in the database. PLUS when I am shopping and I see something that seems to be a healthy alternative but I want to make sure I can scan the barcode and see if it really is a healthy alternative! I recommend this app to EVERYONE and especially anyone who wants to make healthier decisions!

title: Very nice product.
body: My iPhone 3GS had some trouble scanning before the last software update but now it seems to work fine. Never had any scanning problem when using my iPad. So far this is the best food app that I have used. Because of the scanning feature. What I would like to see improved is the ability to manage my likes and food lists, local products by region, the ability to calculate calories by weight and food type (like wine). I would like freedom from Internet and 4GS service by having the option to store my information on my device and not on some server. What I mean is I cannot use this app unless I'm always connected to wireless service. Which is not always available.

title: An Absolute Favorite!
body: I LOVE this app! I use it every day, multiple times a day for tracking my weight, carbs, etc. but my favorite thing about it is the information you get about food ingredients and suggested alternatives. It has taught me so much and is improving the way my family and I eat. I like that, if the food is not listed in the database, you can take three photos and they are e-mailed to the administrator so it can be added. I also wrote the administrator with a question/ suggestion and received a response (not automatically generated) later that day. Highly recommend!

title: Great App
body: I love this app. I've been using it for about a week, and it's really nice. I like the way the food entry works, and I like the other measurements. I also really enjoy the daily health tip because. My big issue with the app is that it randomly freezes up a lot. It usually happens when I'm entering my exercise. I will have to close out the app and re-open it to finish entering  info. Also, it doesn't always save food I enter myself, which is really annoying. Like today I've entered a recipe three times, and the recipe still hasn't saved. It's very frustrating. If these bugs can be fixed, this will definitely be a 5-star app!

title: It needs one change only
body: I started using this app last night, and I really like it. I wish that Weight Watchers would incorporate notes, hunger levels, and times into its app, because these are the features I like about this app. I would give the app five stars if I could read comments on the same screen where I'm recording my foods, instead of having to go back to the different part. I also like the food grades and the notification which are the top products for nutrition. It makes me feel good to know that I am selecting not only low-calorie foods for weight loss, but also foods that are generally accepted as healthy choices.

title: Good "Weight-Watching" Tool
body: This app is worth every bit of its nominal cost. Maybe you'll lose weight, maybe not, but what it does is make you very aware of what you're putting in your mouth. With this awareness of calories and nutrition, you will most likely eat more healthfully. Having this app on my iPhone is convenient because I add things as I eat them rather than trying to remember it all at the end of the day. The only thing I would add is the ability to enter your own smoothy recipe, for instance, with the total calories you've determined by adding up the calories on the packages. The way it is now, you have to enter all ingredients separately.

title: Excellent way to learn good nutrition
body: This app is the best and easiest I have ever found to help me on a path to better health and weight loss. It is very easy to use, has excellent scanning ability to learn what foods to buy before purchasing and gives suggestions for better alternatives. It gives you a very comprehensive look at everything you consume and links with other exercise apps to incorporate that information onto you calorie count.  I love this app and highly recommend to everyone who wants to improve their health. Support is easily obtained and quick to respond to emails

title: Eye Opening
body: This is by far my favorite app!   I committed myself to eating healthier a couple of years ago.   I've been surprised... and even shocked on one or two occasions... that some of the food I thought was good for me is in fact worse than junk food.  Talk about an eye opening experience.

title: Great Product
body: In the past I've seen products like this, but found that they were missing a lot of products from the database.  This app is great because if it doesn't have information on the food item you're researching the app will have you take 3 photos -- front of box, ingredients, and nutrional info -- and then send the information to them so they can add it.  Also, this product doesn't just grade the item you're researching, but it tells you why it deserves that grade and what healthier alternatives might be.  In my opinion this product covers all the bases.

title: Very Good App
body: I read about this app in a magazine and it was very positive. I downloaded it and have been scanning everything. It's very helpful and detailed and if the product you scan is not in the database, it will allow you to take 3 pictures, 1 of the product itself, 2 the nutrition label and 3, the ingredients.

title: Wonderful app
body: This is a great app that aids you in making healthy food choices for you and your family. It takes the guess work out of translating nutrition labels and it's like having a nutritionist go shopping with you. It's surprising to find out that products you thought were healthy because of labeling actually are not as good for you as they claim to be. I love the "alternatives" feature that allows you to make healthier choices if the product you normally buy doesn't get a good grade. Thank you for this valuable app that allows me to make more nutritional sound food choices!

title: Fooducate
body: This is the best app I've seen on tracking nutrition, and by far the easiest. As soon as you scan something it gives the product a grade (like A- or C), and explains why that prospect has that grade. I was surprised at how many things I thought were healthy actually weren't. Then it gave me some similar recommendations. This was really valuable, since I like to shop at trader joes and like certain products (like hummus or Greek yogurt). The app was able to tell me which yogurts and hummus were the best at trader joes, so I don't need to run all over town looking for a different brand!

title: Actually pretty good app.
body: Like this app since it provides the flexibility to lose weight by using points or calories.  I like the ease of scanning an item that is new and indicate number of servings.  I will guess that their database of items will grow. Only gripe I have is to many user entries for the same item.  There has to be a better way to filter through it. I include all the nutritional info and not just the quantity and calories for an item. Try looking for green pepper and you'll see what I mean. Fruits, vegetables, nuts, etc should  already have a standardized list in place.

title: Awesome
body: I've used many calorie trackers over the years and this one impressed me. u can track ur exercise vs food intake like some of the others but it does something even better. It doesn't track just calories, it can track everything else to customize to ur health needs. So at the end of every day it gives u a very user friendly assessment of the quality of the foods u ate (so not just quantity). It simplifies it and this very much appeals to me since I'm usually more interested in my carb intake than calorie. Anyways... This is great and I say it's worth the subscription.

title: Love this app! A must if you are health conscious!
body: My family and I are making a strong effort to make healthier choices and this Fooducate has been essential. I scan everything! There are many instances in which I have switched to healhtier products based on recommendations from Fooducate. For example, when I first started using it, I was able to find a much healthier granola bar that is less expensive and available in my usual grocery store. It saves me the time I would have spend reading about individual ingredients and comparing labels. Fooducate does the work for me.

title: A bit buggy
body: I really like what the app is promising to do and I have no doubt that it does so but the current version does not allow me to select / input entries including my gender and exercises! I suspect that an update will take care of that, until then I can't justify upgrading to Pro yet. Update: Just updated the app, it works! Thanks. Update: I really love this app's interface, it's the best I've seen so far. However I am using a competitor's app alongside (for now) because it syncs with Fitbit (as does all of my other fitness apps). This setup is eliminating duplication & reducing entry errors and time, with the downside is defiantly the interface and ease of use. Please support Fitbit, I'd want to stick around.

title: Easy to use! Cool features!
body: I love this app. It's intuitive and great features, even for the free version. My favorite is the recipes feature where you can add your own recipe and it calculates the amount of calories per serving. I just wish it had a feature to suggest the amount per serving and how many servings based on the total ingredients. I also like being able to create meals for the most common things I eat. Finally, I would like to suggest an "edit" feature for recipes and such for when we forget to add a photo or find a new thing to do with the recipe.

title: Fives stars on next update if...
body: ...you guys include two things:

title: Wonderful idea
body: This is a very informative product that is well-designed and very user friendly. I do question some of the information provided though. For example, I have yet to find a product that will get higher than a B+. I even tried just scanning frozen broccoli and still got a B+. I'm not sure what can possibly be better than frozen veggies (arguably better even than the fresh form). I also tried scanning peas baby food which is only peas and water and those had a B- grade. I checked the alternatives and it gave me pur√©ed sweet potatoes and corn... Not sure who decided an overused grain (corn) and a starch would be better for my baby than a green veggie... Makes me question the source.

title: Just downloaded
body: I have spent the past hour and a half going through this app and in my opinion it is everything you could possibly need for dieting- whether you are counting calories, carbs, or fat grams. Or if you are just health conscious, this app has info on fast food, grocery food, organic food etc. It also has a place for you to start listing your meals according to the profile you set up to watch your weight. It even has a motivational message you can set to send yourself however many times a week you need it. Amazing!

title: It has everything and more!
body: I've had the free version of this app for 2 days now, and I really like it.  I went through 3 or 4 other nutritional apps before finding this one; none of those come close.  I'm probably going to upgrade to the full version that tracks all major nutrients.

title: Great app for keeping you on track!
body: This is a great app for helping you make healthy decisions about the food you eat.  It has helped me on a 100 pound weight loss journey. The tracking is helpful for keeping you on your path, and the food grades and daily information help you make informed decisions and keep you motivated.  Being able to scan a food's barcode as well as add your own foods/recipes is terrific.  The folks at Fooducate are also always very helpful, prompt and proactive when little glitches come up.  All in all a great app and great support.

title: Best App Ever!
body: A friend told me about this app and I've used it everyday since I put it on my phone. I'm checking labels at the grocery store before I buy a product.  I check the content of the food I eat and have been amazed at the foods that I thought were good but I'm learning now that there are alternatives out there that are better for me.  I have now shared this app with my friends and they are loving it as much as I do.  I even added the profile and pet portions and am equally pleased with those as well.  Thank you "Fooducate" for this app. What a life changer!!!

title: Amazing~
body: This app is great. I find it super intuitive to use and easy to remember, and the way it breaks down and grades the nutritional value of the food is great. It's also really nice that the "pro" features, while they look interesting, aren't invasive and not having them doesn't detract at all from the value and experience of the app. Furthermore, the articles are well sourced and well written, and the recipe section is extremely well organized, and I've found some great stuff there. Overall, no complaints! I would recommend this to others

title: Easier than Weight Watchers
body: I came from Weight Watchers because it was too much to keep up with. This app feels much more motivational, and is also free with the option of a more specialized paid version. I LOVE how foods are give "grades"; I was pretty surprised because some foods WW said were bad are actually good on this app. I like the community interface a bit more than WW, but I think some people may not - its a big list from what I can tell. Also this app appears more gender balanced versus a large number of women on WW. Love this app and I already lost almost 2lbs in a week.

title: Amazing!
body: I absolutely love this app. I've used it for a couple of weeks and love every bit of it. I thought the only downside was some of the foods I eat aren't listed, but they make it ultra easy to get that fixed by an automatic email. All you do is take pictures(with their system)of the label, nutrition label and their ingredients. I love that everything is spelled out right easy for me with grades. The only downside is I've learned the hard truth about American food systems and how corrupt they are with what seems like it'll be healthy and it turns out it's awful for you! ‚òπÔ∏è

title: The best one out there
body: I have been a health nut for years now and this app is hands-down the best one I've ever come across. I've had my plate, and my fitness pal, but this one really goes above and beyond. Very user-friendly, tells you facts about the food you would not be able to find out unless you truly looked into it, and also keeps track of the amount of processed food, and the nutrients break down beyond just macros. It's free to download but if you're willing to invest $30 for the entire year you can unlock so many amazing features.

title: Review
body: Absolutely wonderful app! Always been very health conscious and concerned w nutrition and the breakdown of cho, fat, protein in diet... This app has expanded my knowledge and created the building blocks for newfound product and ingredient knowledge in a simple logical manner. I'm making more educated consumer purchases and loving it thanks to fooducate.  Could NOT imagine going grocery shopping or living without it! I tell everyone about this app because i feel like Everyone should have this app and be more aware of what they are putting into their bodies. Keep updating and adding to this app...I'm forever hooked :)

title: Amazing app
body: This app is so awesome! I am a huge nut about eating healthy and it's not very easy in the world we live in! This app makes choices simple, you just scan, and see the review on the product, and if you don't like it's grade, it will give you better alternatives!!!! To me, diet is the reason so many Americans are in ill health, and for myself and my kids I will be using this app to lea is to better choices for a healthier future!! They grade the product, and in easy terms explain why the product is or isn't the best option! No more reasons to eat unhealthy people!!!!

title: Very easy to use
body: This app is very easy to use. Has a huge food database. Allows for GMO tracking and offers alternatives when you want to make better choices. I like the synapsis it gives you when you read about the foods. I wish it had more detailed food tracking (proteins, sodium, cholesterol etc) and would be nice if you could set your own specific goals to said details. But, over all this app is excellent and like I said, quick and easy food logging (if it takes too much time I usually will not track it all because I need something that can keep up with my lifestyle)

title: Incredible! Outstanding!
body: This app helps me organize what I eat so much better than before! It helps me realize how terribly I was eating before. I love the interface and the ability to comment and like certain foods. My favorite part is the barcode scanner, this is so helpful! I'm sure this app will help me in my trek to weight loss, and an overall more healthy diet! I love being able to find healthy alternatives for potentially dangerous foods. Each food has warnings and background checks to help you know what's healthy and what's not. Outstanding work, this app. I love it!

title: Missing basic food nutritional info
body: Warning - App is only for packaged & processed food shoppers.

title: You can learn more than just how many calories are in a particular food
body: I am not big on the calorie tracker apps and never have been for the simple reason that there is never a push for me to care about what I am putting in my body only how many calories I am consuming. I absolutely love this app because it is a one stop guide for the foods you encounter every day. You learn what to look for and what to avoid so this app is essential for a person who is looking to be healthy and not just lose a bit of weight.

title: Pretty good
body: I like the idea of food grades and alternatives but some of them I don't understand even after reading the explanations. Today I was comparing two different granola bars and couldn't understand why one was better than the other as the explanations seemed to be the same.

title: Love this app!
body: I have lost 10pds already using this app! It makes it so easy to punch in what you eat & then breaks it down into nutrional pie charts for each day and week! It also loads my miband fitness info too. It did that without even setting it up! I would give it 5 stars but there are lots of duplicate entries of foods... That needs to be watched if the list gets out of control. Love the barcode scanner.. Used it to make grocery buying choices in the store. I also make lists from these entries as well. Love looking at the alternative healthier choices too! Sams club sells some really poor food choices üò≥

title: Food "grades" are great concept, but app falls short
body: I like this app only for the insights on food, the grades. I prefer something more interactive where I can put in the exact amount of food I ate, for instance 1.25 because that happens more often than not. I also do not like their stance on supplements. Fooducate will not analyze supplements because it believes you should only get your nutrients from food. Well of course! But Some of us have legitimate reasons for needing vitamins or supplements.

title: Awesome
body: Glad to see that previous issues have been fixed. Another thing I thought could help the app, would be to alert us when a product we've updated has been changed within the app.

title: Watch out
body: Found several products which are rated "A" and "highest quality in class" but received NO red marks for also being highest (or higher) caloric value than the average or next lowest rated product.

title: Love knowing about the GMO
body: We are eating much better due to this app. We are able to see if it could have GMO in it and also track what we are eating.  Trying to keep our food with no GMO and low in sugar when I look in the health tracker. Great to be able to see how many calories  and how healthy I ate for the day.  Love that if you look up something you normally eat and it is not as healthily as you thought, it will give you other similar brands to replace that item with. Would love to see the data base have more generic food store brands.

title: Phenomenal App!!
body: This app is the best app I've ever used! Found out you can program your health goals in there and be warned about GMO's in your food and even get wheat warnings, etc., if you have allergies!  The folks at Fooducate are responsive and kinda crazy smart!  And nice.  And they care about this stuff!!

title: Good weight watching app
body: A good overall app! What I like most about it is that you can add in your exercise and it will calculate it all for you. There are a ton of products to choose from and the ability to scan bar codes makes this app super easy to use. It also helps to keep track of things like sodium, fiber, etc for the day. At the end of the day it breaks down everything you've inputted and give you easy to understand stats. I would recommend this app to anyone who wants to watch what they are eating.

title: One of the best apps on my phone!
body: I typically don't review apps, but I felt compelled to share how awesome this app is. I love how it grades foods, and explains the reasons why. To make things better you can help add to the database if you scan an item that has yet to be graded! I have found the information to be accurate and very informative. My husband and I are very intuitive to food additives and whatnot that are very unhealthy but we still find ourselves scanning items while shopping to double check ourselves. Can't say enough how much we love this app!

title: Useful
body: Note: I downloaded the free version, not the premium.

title: Love it
body: I've had this app for a while now and I absolutely love it. It's definitely helped me to learn what's healthy for me and what's not, and some things I thought were healthy were surprisingly not. With the help of this app in staying on course and I've been able to lose a decent amount of weight. The best part is the support you get from everyone in the community, they are all willing to help and give advice. I would definitely recommend this to people I know who want to lose weight or just be healthier.

title: Pretty good, probably will improve
body: I'm losing weight by exercising and counting calories, and this app is useful for calculating and tracking both. I wouldn't take all the info as gospel, especially when it comes to the calorie credit you get for exercising, as they can only be estimates of what you burn, but still pretty good. Database of foods and products incomplete. If you scan a product not in their database, the app makes you enter the information yourself if you want to add it, which I resent, though it's only 10 minutes. They will then grade the product. I am not a premium member.

title: FOOD IS MY LIFE
body: I live to eat-but I also know that I need to watch out for whatever I put in my body. I have learned so much from fooducate! The new recipe addition is great. I have made five new recipes from this app. I love it, my kids love it and to my surprise my hubby loves it.

title: Awesome App
body: So happy to have tried this this app...to become healthier for life. This app is so easy to use & it has truly been shocking to see how poorly I was eating before. Thank you Fooducate for opening my eyes & also providing the option for a community of like minded people that support each other & are just completely honest & real...I love it! Track your food intake, exercise & sleep to get on track with being a better you! For me...this isn't about losing weight, but getting healthy & exercising. Thanks again Fooducate‚ù§

title: Fantastic App and Great Potential!
body: The food database in this has a real potential to become huge!  I have scanned pretty much everything in my fridge and I have to say I'm shocked and some of the results I have gotten.  But the app does have it's limitations.  There's a lot of foods that I have that really aren't in the database but I LOVE that three quick pictures and they know all about it.  It will take some time to be added to the database of course but they've made it easy to help the database just grow larger and larger!  Awesome app, keep up the good work!

user_name: I care what my family eats
title: So so helpful
body: This app was so helpful the other day while I was shopping for groceries. I'm trying to focus on eating healthier, again... This app did the work for me and saved me from having to burn up so much time comparing labels. It's no secret that eating healthier costs more but with Fooducate I can make choices by quickly comparing the facts and not be misled by advertisements. The top "healthy food" brands don't always have the healthiest content compared to other products I could buy. Now I can save $ without sacrificing the health benefit. Thank you Fooducate ÓÅñ

title: AMAZING
body: Trust me, I only write reviews for apps that really deserve it. I love this app. It really helps you keep track of what you eat. When scanning the barcode, it's great to know what I'm eating, and if it's un healthy, I love having the alternatives with it. Yes, you must set up an account, but it only takes a few minutes. There aren't many ads, they don't spam you with emails or anything, and it's free! Please please please get this app. You won't regret it. It's also good to browse through foods to see what I should eat for snacks and meals. GET THIS APP! I love it! üòÉüòÜüòã

title: Top notch
body: This is a top notch program that in the very near future I will actual pay to use it forever. The only thing so far that the app lacks is a recipe builder. I am sure that will be coming in a upgrade in the future. Otherwise this is a super complete well functioning nutrition and tracking app in just about every respect. If you are a Weight Watcher then this is the app for you that will not cost you a penny unless you choose to spend it and as far as I can tell it would be money very well spent.

title: Raising awareness and counting calories.
body: I like how this app, and those in charge of the articles provide a good summary of the topics.

title: Extremely Trustworthy
body: Scans almost any food product out there, explains in detail what the ingredients mean, how processed the product is, how the products marketing can be so misleading, and what healthy options are really out there. I use this app any time I'm looking at a new food product and actually trust the research they provide. They even look at restaurant foods and snacks from companies like Nature Box! Love this app, highly recommend it if you're interested in what's really healthy and what you're really consuming.

title: I cant live without Fooducate!
body: I have been using Fooducate for some time now, and my life has changed completely!  I have overhauled not only my bad eating habits, but keep junk and decievingly unhealthy products out of my family's meals as well...I never go to the grocery store or buy any item without consulting with Fooducate first :).  I have been tracking my foods and finally have lost my weight and have been able to keep it off (first time in my life)....love the new community and discussion features!!!  Love my fooducate :)

title: Wish it was easier to find carb count
body: Very frustrated to search how many carbs I've eaten based on the food I've actually eaten. When you reduce a portion, it reduces the amount of total carbs consumed in your review. However it doesn't reduce them in the section where you can tap meal ingredients. That means when I'm trying to see where I'm eating most of my carbs- a bell pepper, for example, if I eat a quarter of it, I'm still dividing by four to get the amount I've actually consumed. It would be so much easier for the actual consumed portion to be listed rather than overall good listing.

title: üôåüèº Not just a calorie counter üôåüèº
body: I've tried other apps like MyFitnessPal and Lose it! But I routinely found myself punching in the cals and not not really thinking about the nutrition behind the numbers. Fooducate brought to light all of the health benefits and health defects of everything I eat on a daily basis. It also gave me explanations as to WHY each product was good or bad for me, as well as alternatives for the not-so-great choices with better ratings. Love this app, I feel like the creators actually want you to succeed in reaching your health goals!

title: Extensive info
body: I was at Trader Joe's and a tall gentleman was buying the spinach kale yogurt dip I love placing his phone over the nutritional info.

title: MUST HAVE!!!
body: This app is perfect for anyone who cares about their health at all! Not only is it an amazing app, but it's easy to use too. I let my grandma play with it at the store and after about 30 minutes I started to think I would never get my phone back. This from a woman who says cell phones are 'the devil'. I can't believe this app is free either, I'd be willing to pay a monthly fee for it now that I know how amazing it is! Clear room on your main screen, because you won't be deleting this app anytime soon!

title: Informative & Useful
body: I've been using this app for awhile now, and I'm finding it more helpful than I thought I would. I'm also finding that I'm scanning products I have at home and searching for healthier alternatives when I make my shopping list. That way I can be proactive and buy the better choices on my next trip without so much scanning in the store. It's saving me time!

title: Can't live without it now!
body: This is, by far, the app I use most on my phone . My kids and I love going through all the food in the house to see how they rate.  I can sometimes spend 2 hours in the grocery store now, zapping bar codes to pick the healthiest foods in each category. I am planning to join WW soon and just realized that the app even tells you how many points each product is as well.  It's a real eye-opener- foods that are marketed as being healthy choices often times are not! Its fabulous!!

title: A spoonful of sugar
body: As a general tool to look past my preconceived notions of what is healthy it couldn't have been more useful. I learned: there's sugar in everything, vegetables are always good for you and if it has a barcode there's probably healthier choices. Its surprisingly huge (and incomplete) data base catalogues many of the foods I buy.

title: Education is KEY
body: There's some really scary stuff out there and it's coming in the form of our food! I've been a label reader for years, but this app makes it so easy to identify the really bad stuff. I love that you can personalize it to certain dietary needs. Another feature that's amazing is the fact that you can discover each bad ingredient in depth. It's a bummer that not all foods are listed, but it's AWESOME for what most people buy. I would definitely suggest a comparison feature if the tech guys are reading this :)

title: Fooducate app
body: Pass the word to anyone who'll listen to you on this app. It will warn you on the toxins and GMO's that are in our food supply. It's not survival of the fittest any more but survival of the smartest. You are what you eat and when our food is filled with so much toxins, drugs to make us more hungry to eat more and cancer causing agents (carcinogenic's) then it's no wonder America is filled with fat diabetics who are dying of cancer. This app isn't perfected yet but give them credit for what they've done, and the ARE working on it. Pass the word and use this app.

title: Would be 5 but‚Ä¶
body: I have loved this app for a long time. It seems to be the most comprehensive nutrition tracker. I even bought it after awhile because I wanted full use of all the features. This was soon after iPhone 5 came out, long before I heard talk of any iPhone health tracker much less THE tracker that has come out now with iOS 8. I ask you to please find a way to make this app compatible with the Health tracker. I paid money for an app that has been wonderful. I would like to see it reach its greater potential. Thank you for your time and consideration.

title: Very helpful app!
body: Very happy I downloaded this app. So helpful. I'm glad that I can scan the codes of the products before buying them and see what's really inside and not what it says on the package. It's really helpful for counting calories and watching your carbs proteins and fats ratio.

title: No, "Avoid GMOs" is a PREFERENCE
body: To the reviewer who dinged this app with one star and deleted it, LEARN TO READ.  Avoiding GMOs is clearly a preference setting, along with vegetarian, vegan, eating for healthy breastfeeding, etc.  It is to help users  evaluate and choose items to fit their needs.  Just because the developers accommodate users with a certain dietary preference that you happen not to believe in does not make the app scientifically invalid.  As a diabetic, I have found this app and its extensive nutritional database to be extremely valuable in helping me control my blood glucose, lose weight (75 pounds so far), and eat healthier.

title: Works, but Mediocre
body: For basic food tracking, this app works fine. If you have to go back to a previous day and add a meal, the app gets confused and will save parts of meals to the current date.

title: By far the best App that I own
body: I got this App last night and used it for the first time today. OMG!!! I am so glad they created an App like this. I went through my fridge and pantry out of curiosity and I can honestly tell you I threw over 90% out.. It was interesting to see the small print content of all the so called healthy foods out here. I had what I thought were whole grains and healthy food in my pantry I was surprised to find out the truth. Thank you so much for giving me the tools to uncover what is really going into my body..

title: Excellent info!
body: This app helps you to go the extra mile past the ingredient list and standard nutrition panel.  It warns you about excess sugars and heavily processed foods, etc. The food scanner is excellent- far better than most at catching even a shaky hand picture of the barcode.

title: Valuable Info, Great App!
body: This app is a wonderful source of information.  I use it at home and when I grocery shop.  I have been surprised by some of the poor nutritional "grades" earned by the so-called "healthy foods" I am used to buying.  What an eye-opener!  Be cautious, though.  Some products are not rated accurately and some of the data is wrong.  Some products were listed in the app as having high-fructose corn syrup - but when I read the packaging of the product in the store, it was not an actual ingredient.  This app still makes a fairly reliable guide, and I refer to it often.
for fooducate plus?

title: Wonderful app
body: Love the app. Very useful. My roommate and I are both doing weight watchers and use it all the time as we grocery shop. One thing that I would recommend as an addition to the app is if they would tell HOW MANY servings are in a package. The points are listed for dieters, but it's not very helpful if you don't know the serving size. With that being said, I use this daily and love reading what makes or breaks a product for their food grade. :) I feel much more "fooducated" about what I'm putting in my body and this app definitely helps me make better food choices. Thanks!!

title: Good Little App
body: I'm enjoying this app so far. The only reason it doesn't get a 5 star is because there aren't many restaurant foods available. Also, you have to sift through so many user added foods. It's hard to tell which ones are actually correct. It would be nice if the database of foods was put on by the Fooducate folks only, and users could submit their own foods to see on only their device. I love the fact that foods get a grade (A, B, C, etc.) Clean it up a bit and get rid of so many user added foods, make more restaurant foods available, and it would be 5 stars.

title: LOVE this app
body: I love this app and it's probably in my top three most frequently used. It's become an integral part of my journey to eat healthier as a family. I try not to eat anything rated below a B and usually stay at B+ or above. It's easy to use and I'm always pulling it out during my trips to the grocery store if I'm unsure about an item. My only complaint is that you can't scan a second item after you've already scanned one without going back to the home screen which is a little annoying. Fix that one thing and this is a five star app easy.

title: Best for low-carb!
body: I searched high and low for the best app to track a low-carb diet. This has by far been the easiest and most user friendly! You can switch it to track by carbs instead of calories and it has a status bar at the top so your number of carbs for the day goes up as you add food. You know when you're getting closer to your limit with each item of food you put in. I have had success in weight loss doing a low-carb diet and I owe it all to this app for my success!!

title: Healthy Way to Track Food
body: As a health science student I can back this and it's various rewards to users. Eating healthy is easy when all you have to do is scan and see a break down of food; also helps on my cheat meals cause I can find ways to eat a fun meal like a burger or pizza and balance it with something healthy without going over my calorie limit!

title: Hate the notifications
body: I use Fooducate to educate myself on healthy food choices and it worked great for this purpose. For some reason the app creators have recently decided it would be a good idea to send the notification "Please log your meals. Even a few is fine." incessantly. I am considering deleting the app because of this. Not only is this notification pointless and intrusive, it is passive aggressive and condescending - two things I never thought I would say about a phone notification! As a physician I do not have the time or inclination to log my meals because someone else thinks it is good for me. Please allow me to use the app in the way I feel it is most useful to my lifestyle. And don't treat your customers like children.

title: My most favorite app!!
body: I love this app!!! Its very easy to use.  I have spent hours in my kitchen and the grocery store scanning items and looking for healthier alternatives. It's even helped me save money. I have scanned new more expensive items in the grocery store thinking they are the healthiest choices only to find out there is another option that is just as healthy or healthier that costs less!! I would recommend downloading this app to anyone that is interested in changing the way they eat!

title: Love it! But...
body: First off, I really do like this app. It helps me control my calories without carrying a paper and pencil getting weird looks like I have a weird obsession hah. But, I'm only 16 and have to put my birth year up two years to get an account. So it kinda messes with the BMI I think. The store reminders aren't working on my iPod ( I think it's only an iPhone thing,although I don't see why it would matter, but who knows right?).  So all in all I really like the app, it is going to he'll control my weight ad lose some(: if you get this app you should be satisfied. Thanks.

title: New to Fooducate
body: I've just started using this app and so far am very happy with it. I was driving past my grocery store the other day and heard my phone beep. It was a reminder to use Fooducate while I'm shopping. I love that it does that otherwise I probably would forget to use it when I really am going to the grocery store! Seems very reliable so far. Looking forward to any future updates although I can't think of a way to improve upon it as it is now. üòä

title: Great but could have more features for price
body: I love that this app alerts you to what's in foods based on your own settings and that it will grade foods and give you alternatives. It would be better if you could see nutrient reports and goal reports, and if it was easier to change foods or add them to other days, etc. I love the tips and the information included in the daily tips and newsletters, and I really like that you can be reminded to use the app when you arrive at stores that you choose. For the price though, it should also do all of the reporting that other food tracking apps do.

title: Fooducate is excellent!
body: If you're trying to lose weight, reduce cholesterol, or just track your food intake, get this. I used the free version for a long time, which is quite good, but I upgraded to the premium version. Now I can look up a food by scanning its label, searching for restaurant foods, or entering fresh items. Fooducate has a vast library and will not only track calories, carbs, and nutrients, but it will give you lots of information about the food AND offer alternative foods. Best "diet" app out there!

title: Great Visual
body: I started tracking foods in a diary a few months ago. I knew what I ate, but had no way of seeing the types of nutrients or calories.  I'm currently using this app and one other (still deciding which gives the best view of my progress) to track my daily diet. So far I really enjoy the app and the graphs it provides. The only downside has been when I needed to change previously entered data. For example, I went back for seconds and needed to add another serving. Took a moment to figure that out. Good app, keep adding new foods to keep it simple.

title: Fantastic health app
body: I am someone that has tried numerous food trackers. I have tried this app on the past with so so results. Decided to give it another go as i try to find the perfect food tracker app to go with my new Apple watch. This time around I actually give it a chance and rally dig into all the functions and spend time pitting in my food. After a couple of days I realized the potential of this great app. It's takes some time but give it a chance and you will love it.

title: Excellent and handy food tracking App.
body: I am a long time follower of the Lean for Life program by Cynthia Stamper Graff, president of the Lindora Institute, and this app is a convenient way to keep a daily action plan (DAP), in other words, a record of what I eat and drink, my weight, measurements, etc. I am on the go most of the time, and this app is much easier than writing things down on a DAP worksheet or going online to do it. I really love the nutritional information too. The charts are amazing and a great graphical depiction of my effort and progress.

title: Best Diet Tracker
body: I have tried a decent number of diet trackers and calorie counter type apps. Fooducate is the best I have found. Overall just easy and well thought-out. The database is fairly extensive so the barcode scanning works most of the time. Their water tracking is kind of tacked on so I use a separate app. And the Apple Watch app is pretty basic. I'm hoping they keep improving those aspects since I went ahead and bought the lifetime subscription option. Worth the money in my opinion.

title: Great
body: If I could give 10 stars I would. I don't even care about weight, I just like to be able to quickly get an assesment on a food product before I eat it. This app makes it easy to judge whether I should eat something or not, and the scan option makes it only take a few seconds. Plus its review of the food is very thorough unlike other bad apps that only take into account macros instead of actual ingrediants. I highly reccomend!! Great job with this app.

title: Makes grocery shopping obnoxiously fun!
body: Great app that helps me check on those "healthy" foods that might look awesome for me, but loaded with excess ingredients/heavily processed junk. I forget to look at the serving sizes and actually having the app kinda forces me to not go for the junk food that I try to justify as healthy.... Darn.

title: I'm recommending it everyone.
body: This app was an alternative suggested casually by a friend who counts Weight Watcher points.   Wow--I'm SO glad I followed up and downloaded it.  There is so much information here and it's very easy to use.  I've put a number of items I used to buy regularly back on the shelf.  (I thought I was pretty savvy but one 'healthy' treat I used to pick for my husband was a D- due to additives and stabilizers.). It's a little like having a nutritionist on call.  And I love the "alternatives" feature.  Big 5 stars!

title: Almost...
body: The revised site is far from improved. When I want to read a long form Daily Tip I right into it. When I want to go back to the tips master page I have ti go all the way back to the main menu; ridiculous. When you fix this please make sure I land in the exact same spot on the master page; no annoying scrolling over and over. Also, the new more complex site is not any better really, just more complex and black and white ugly text. Where are the icons.

title: Wonderful unbiased info!
body: I like this app for a bunch of reasons. Briefly, if you contact support, THEY ANSWER! Not always the case with app developers. I especially like the fact that it seems to be an unbiased analysis of both processed and unprocessed foods. With "health" apps, this is not always the case. It doesn't automatically vilify processed foods which is rare these days or so it seems to me. Just the facts as they see them. Good scanning of barcodes and a seemingly broad database of foods. I enjoy the look and feel as well. Good job.

title: Really handy while shopping!
body: I use this at the grocery store almost every time I shop, now. It's so easy to find out about what's in the food I want to buy and get some kind of a rating to compare similar products so I know which one to buy and what to avoid. It helps me find out how healthy stuff really is. Kind of disappointing to learn that stuff I thought was okay is full of crap, but better to know, now, and buy healthier food than have unexpected health issues as I age‚Ä¶

title: Restaurants?
body: This app is fantastic when it comes to watching for harmful ingredients. I also like the alternatives button to help you shop smarter. It's great that it gives you an estimate on how many calories and carbs you should be eating if you want to loose a few pounds. I haven't scanned anything yet that it didn't have in it's database. I do wish there was a good list of restaurant foods though. Fast food, and larger chain restaurants would be very helpful. I'm sure it would be hard to get a true ingredients list but, just a calorie count would be helpful.

title: Changed how I think about what I eat
body: Wow ..finally a way to understand today's food

title: Using it everyday
body: I use this app everyday to look up what I'm eating. It puts food in a different t perspective and helps me avoid things that I tell myself is ok to eat. I love the ability to scan foods and instantly see its health grade to make quick and good decisions. I also love the explanations feature to explain why foods are graded the way they are. I also love that we can contribute to the app by adding foods that haven't been added yet! Can't wait to see this app grow further.

title: Best app ever!
body: I love this app! I first got it to be able to scan bar codes in the grocery store to find out about products before I buy them. It has since evolved and updated. I love the community section where you can connect with other users. There are some downsides, such as if you want anything custom or specific to your needs you have to pay for the pro version, but that's pretty normal in terms of apps. This is great if you're looking to eat healthier, lose weight, or otherwise want to manage your diet and eating habits.

title: Great app for Great appetites
body: Many fitness apps don't live up to the hype or you simply stop using them after a while but I've been using Fooducate for months. One of the most useful features is the food scanner with the grade ratings. I use it constantly whether it be at Costco or Ralph's to evaluate how clean and nutrient dense any packaged food is when decide what to buy. I find that it doesn't encourage calorie counting (although it can accommodate to that) but rather promote clean and healthy eating.

title: Awesome!!
body: Im only 29 years old and I recently found out I have really high blood pressure. This app helps me stay away from potentially harmful products, and has educated me on some of the harmful foods I've been eating/drinking. If the product is not in the data base you can take the pics yourself, and send the info via email very easily! Their research team will apparently do the analysis and then add it to the database. very addicting! You'll want to scan everything! May double your time spent at the grocery store.. Lol.

title: Informative and fun to use!
body: This is one of my favorite utility apps in my phone. Though it may not be practical to scan every item you're shopping for at the grocery store, it IS a very helpful tool is learning about the foods in your home.  If I'm waiting for something to cook or am just curious I definitely scan items I frequently use.

title: NEAR PERFECTION!
body: This is awesome for use with Weight Watchers PointsPlus.  It's very user-friendly and I love the information it gives you.  I scanned EVERYTHING edible in my kitchen and i love that if you scan a product that Fooducate doesn't have, you can send the info in AND receive feedback.  I've already gotten feedback for 6 items.  Great, great, great!  Would be perfect if: 1-you could somehow fix it so that the WW information could be easily linked to my iTrackerBites app, and 2: tell us what constitutes a serving size.

title: Helpful
body: This app offers insights about food and products that otherwise would remain unknown. If Fooducate does not have a product in its database one can email photos of the product, nutritional info and ingredients to be reviewed and added. My complaint is that Fooducate evaluates foods differently, i.e. suggests eating frozen fruits and vegetables because these products are frozen at peak freshness but I'd rather not have frozen preservatives and prefer to stay away from freezer foods. App holds different dietary values but is still very useful.

title: Sugar
body: I just installed this app and the first thing I scanned was Nature's Path Organic Pumpkin Flax Granola. The app gave it a B rating because of sugar however the sugar is evaporated cane juice as opposed to processed refined sugar. Big difference.  Not all sugar is bad and cane juice like coconut sugar and agave are low glycemic index sweeteners and are high in nutrients. The app needs to recognize this and if the concern is the caloric count it needs to look at the product as a whole.  When you click on more info on sugar you'll see that the app lumps all sweeteners together including artificial sweeteners and corn sugars which are genetically modified. This is an apples to oranges comparison and highly misleading.

title: Getting Fit
body: My goal is keeping fit by eating right and exercise regularly or 4 times per week. Since I'm a senior and retired I have the time to prepare the meals and exercise. Fooducate has provided me with valuable information with getting my weight down without depriving my body of valuable nutrition which is critical on any weight loss program where ketone build up can reverse what your trying to accomplish. Many thanks Foodicate. You are very informative and we'll worth the money.

title: Add Recipe Link
body: This is a good educational tool to show what the subject should be eating. However I believe the subject would do much better if recipe suggestions were added. General healthy diets have fruits and vegetables in most diets. One could use good cooking and meal planning web sites to improve nutritional awareness and encourage users to cook at home and attend near by Farmers Markets!

title: Food Finder Fantastic
body: I don't use the app to track my calories and weight, However; this is hands down, the best app to find out if what you're eating is healthy or not, it tells me what's in my food, what possible chemicals or controversial additives are in the food, and it also grades the food from A to D, obviously A being the best. And what's more, when you scan something that's not entirely acceptable to put in your body, it will give you an alternative! It's Fantastic. This app is a keeper.

title: Best food tracker
body: I would surprised to see that this app didn't have straight five stars, so I took the time to look at some of the lesser reviews. One is a review of fish sticks (seriously). Some only praise, but fail to give full stars. One requested the impossible (that the whole food database be off-line). Finally, one complained about the food search, which I think is just great. In conclusion, people can't find anything bad to say about it. Also, it's worth just spending the money on lifetime!

title: Wonderful
body: At first I just used it to make me more aware of what I was eating.  I saw that there were much better choices once I graded the food, and I began looking for alternatives.

title: Hrm
body: Good idea, bad execution. Manual entry for iphone 3G is a joke. Food scanner accurately scans UPCs, so why not fooducate? And since the scanner is obviously disabled on the 3G, as it doesn't even try to capture the UPC, there needs to be an error message or a note visible on the scanner screen, so those of us that forgot the scanner doesn't work on 3G will be reminded. I don't use the app every day and haven't used it for a week. Therefor the likelihood that I'll forget the scanner doesn't work is high.

title: Good, but data collection needs improvement.
body: Very useful when at the store and trying to compare nutritional info on packages based on different serving sizes, etc. Be prepared to spend more time at the store!!! I encountered quite a few times when the app asked me to "help them out" by capturing uncatalogged food item info and sending it in. The "help us out" feature works well enough, but I don't want to use my data plan to send images of items to them. Isn't there a way to que these up then send them when I am on WiFi?

title: Great app, but...
body: This is a very helpful app and is great for people to start paying attention to ingredients. However, the grading on products seems a bit flawed.

title: Love it! Couldn't ask for a better app!
body: I have tried other apps similar to this one, and not many of them compare to what you can do in this one. I love how you can scan your food that you are consuming and it tells you all the nutritional facts about it. I also love that you can input your daily exercise routines and it calculates how many calories you have burned. There's just too much to list about why I love this app, I would recommend this app to everyone!

title: Very Helpful App!!
body: I use this app to scan every food item I purchase and it couldn't be enough help!! I love how it is very accurate down to the T. Just wish they had more food variety. Some of the foods I scan aren't in the system so I have to take pics and send to fooducate......no biggie though. Other than that, I can't get enough of this app. Did I also mention you can track your calories and all the foods you eat in a day?! What are you waiting for?! Purchase this app!! IT'S FREE!!!

title: Needs improvement but I love it
body: I love all of the tracking, options and suggestions. I wish I could search just in my recent foods, and that when searching all foods the results show in order from most popular among users to not. I wish you could edit the entry (like servings you've had or meal you had it for) after it's been entered instead of having to enter another of the same item or remove it and enter again. But the BIGGEST thing is that there needs to be a major camera interface improvement. I can barely ever get it to scan anything!

title: MUST DOWNLOAD!!
body: This app is AMAZING for people who really want to know if you're really eating healthy. Also gives daily news/scoops/tips on health foods. This is just wonderful. I hope I'll be able to update to the premium!

title: Grocery shopping made easier!
body: I love this app! Sometimes I'm in a time crunch (outside of grocery shopping) and can't always cook food. It's nice to know that I can see a letter grade for processed things and determine if they're worth my time. I don't use this as a primary took to determine if I should buy something or not, but it does give me some pause to think about whether I'm making a good choice or if something is worth the low letter grade every once in a while.

title: excellent
body: Revised..  a bit... I really wish the was more food database. Almost everything I scan is not here. :( and it's all good food.. Like shrimp, meat. I am figuring out that you have to add food to favorites to save it.

title: Love This App...hands down the best app!
body: I use this app daily. I have recently lost 11 lbs tracking my diet and exercise (over a month timespan). I use this app while shopping to make decisions based on food selection. I love that you can input recipes and Fooducate gives you the nutritional breakdown. Lastly, the app works seamlessly with my Apple Watch! Thanks Fooducate for your continuous improvement, I have used this app for years and continue to believe this is the best nutrition and exercise app hands down!

title: great for moms maybe? not for me
body: First off, I like that this app points out things that might be of concern like ingredients and additives. The grades given for food, however, have proven to be pretty useless to me. I am an athlete and I was hoping that this app might help me choose better fuel for my runs. Alas, most sports nutrition products end up getting a D+ or C- grade which doesn't really help me compare. This is probably due to the high sugar and calorie contents of these foods, which is actually something I want to fuel a 10 or 15 mile run. Maybe this app might be good for moms looking to buy healthy for their kids, but I'm better off going back to reading the labels myself.

title: Best diet app ever!
body: Love this app,  most comprehensive nutrition guide :D!

title: Very useful and easy to pick up
body: Managed to set up my goals and start scanning all the food in my house in just under 15 minutes! Love this app and hope to use it to put more healthy things into my body...only question seems to be, is there any plan on introducing menus of items prepared at restaurants any time soon?! I frequent a coffee shop and deli quite regularly, and there seems to be no effective way of entering or scanning the items I eat there.

title: A must have app!
body: I got info about this app from a hospital dietician to watch sodium and carb intake. What a great app. It is amazing the crap manufacturers sneak into food. I've been eating vegetarian for a while only to find out many of the meat substitutes aren't vegetarian at all! You need this app if you care at all about eating better.

title: Great App!
