body: Easy to use and I love the grades it gives you on each food item. It sure makes you think before eating or buying something bad that you may have thought was good for you!  I would give this a 5 star, but I have given it a 4 because I would like to have a feature where you can add your own recipes as well as edit the food you logged each day without having to delete and re-add the item. Overall it's been very user friendly and helpful-overall I love the app! Thanks Fooducate!

title: A food app that helps without guilt!
body: I use the scan food rating guide daily and love that it doesn't judge my choices but does help me make better ones. I can consciously know what I eat. Buying a tortilla wrap, here's the best option. And if I must eat a chocolate bar well here's the best of the worst! It was also eye opening what I thought was healthy and most certainly are not! A life saver. I've been telling all my friends and was even prompted to write my first ever app review! Thank you.

title: Probably my favorite app!!
body: I was searching for an app my son could use as  he is legally blind and cannot read ingredient lists and nutritional information on packages. I downloaded the app to test myself and fell in love. What I like most about Fooducate is it takes the guesswork out of buying healthy and nutritional food. With just a scan of the barcode, I can read and understand healthy ingredients and others to avoid. Everyone in my family uses it now!!

title: Love it!!!
body: I've tried calorie count and myfitnesspal but just never really liked either app. I love this app though. It's so much easier to use, and unlike the other two, I actually use it ever day and log in every day. Plus, I've stuck with my allotted calories. What I like most is the search feature. Instead of just a written list of foods you also get pictures so I can scroll through faster and find my food to log in. Love it!!!

title: ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏èüíô
body: I find this app to be better than others I've used mainly My Fitness Pal. Sorry MFP! I do wish it had a multi add feature rather than just a make it a meal option. I don't always eat the same yogurt for breakfast. Being able to select each item I ate and add the items all at once would be much quicker and easier. It does educate and I love the community feature along with being able to read articles if I so choose. It's bright and easy to read, very user friendly. Try it!

title: Great concept but not perfect
body: After hearing from a host in food network channel, I tried this app. Liked it but not that much to buy it. Few months later, purchased the app. I see no difference in the functionality between free and paid. The app is slower than ever and their push notifications won't work, when asked the technical support is not very happy to address the issue. Many food items have no nutritional information. They can't rely on users to update all of these. We send three pics, can't they enter or develop an app to transfer those data. I won't renew it after my first year.

title: Love it!!!
body: I'm surprised by some of the lower ratings... It seems like it is the phone that doesn't work, not the app... I have shaky hands and it scans perfectly and quick!!!  The only thing that would make it better, (and I believe they are working on it) is to be able to search categories instead of just scanning the products that you're already looking at, so you might find something you might not have known about!!!

title: Awesome!
body: I love this app! Really helpful, it provides useful info for users who might be on a diet or simply want to eat better. I always wonder about the nutritional content of my food when grocery shopping (it can be difficult to tell sometimes) and this app helps to break down ambiguous ingredients, list any +'s and -'s etc in an easy to understand format. This is the only app I've ever recommended to multiple ppl! All of whom have loved it! :)

title: Amazing
body: I love this app, I honestly think this app saved my Family's life, I have a son one-year-old, I care about what I give him and the quality of the food that he gets, I didn't know before this app about GMO's genetically modified foods but thanks to this application, Which really educates you about everything in the product that might harm you, You just scan any product and the information comes out so easy to understand simple and amazing.

title: Best App Ever
body: I have been using this for a couple years now and everyone I have had download it loves it!! It probably finds what I scan 99% of the time, it's great while grocery shopping when you need information on a product ASAP... Scanning everything in my pantry I've been able to single out things I do not want in my diet and have been successful in replacing them w/ a healthier solution!! Download it today, you will not be disappointed!!

title: Love the customization level
body: I am a myfitnesspal junky. However I find it limiting on setting my macros to a specific number. So far my favorite feature is I can specify the exact amount of each macro I want for my day. There has already been two foods I was unable to scan and find but I hope in time the database will be as big as myfitnesspal. It was easy enough to submit pictures and nutritional information for too.

title: I love fooducate
body: I use it constantly. Very helpful. The only improvements I would want are it to have more foods, cuz I have searched for something and it is not there. I have given nutrition facts about something and it gave me an email but I could it would not be on there for a while. I want to search for my history a lot so I wish there was an easier way to find a specific thing. The health tracker is helpful. I also like the articles

title: Mind blowing!!
body: Just flabbergasted to see so many food items Gmo labelled. Also I love the fact I can scan all grocery products I buy and see what affect it will have on me and my family. Definitely sticking with this in the new year 2015!  I love it!  If losing weight and changing the way you eat as a new lifestyle is your goal then use this app!  It will save your life and make you more aware of what you are putting in your mouth daily.

title: Life saver
body: I've been feeling rundown and lousy and seriously wondering if I had some major health issues. I decided to start tracking my nutrition. This app has been informative, motivating and health saving. I feel younger and healthier now. I love this app and would recommend it to anyone who wants to be reflective on their decision making around eating.  I tried a few other apps and this one is far superior with nutritional information, ease-of-use, and fun.

title: Great support for eating healthy
body: I love this app and have recommended it many times! It focuses on eating healthy not just consuming fewer calories. I like that it doesn't promote certain product brands, but instead truly educates people on eating foods that are good for your body. It is very easy to scan codes and find out if something is a good choice. It also is a great way to track your food consumption as well as your calories burned through exercise.

title: Great dieting tool
body: This app has really helped me realize how much sugar and salt I was consuming. It's also made me measure my food so that I can keep accurate records which has definitely helped with my over eating and portion control issue. I wish I could figure out how to add foods (it says I need a mail account?) and there are some "premium" features that I think should be free (like the breastfeeding diet!) but all in all I really like this app. It's easier to use than any diet app I've used (and given up on) in the past.

title: It Will Save Your Life
body: If I could vote this app "Most Likely to Save Your Life", I would! Also, I was impressed with its design- one of the best I've ever seen. It does a great job of answering all those little pesky questions such as, "Is high fructose corn syrup really bad for you?" It does so in an honest and unbiased way and supports its info with links to scientific info or supporting documents, where appropriate. It's a must buy! If you're really interested in educating yourself about nutrition, you won't be sorry!

title: Insightful!
body: We are enjoying this app immensely. We've probably scanned 1/3 of the products in the kitchen already. Commentary after food scans provides thought provoking details. It has given us much pause w/r/t "hidden" ingredients. For example, we avoid MSG but we never considered to look for other equivalents! Yikes. At the very least it has given us reason to pause and consider a food choice...so much for mindless binges....gonna have to make them a thing of the past.

title: Great app, it's a must have!!
body: My bf n I LOVE this app! We r both on a path to living a healthier life. We r always making sure that the food we buy at the store is healthy and/or an okay product to consume by looking/reading the nutrition label of the item. However, now with Fooducate we can easily scan n see why the food we pick is either good/bad to eat as well as what alternatives I have if the food item has a bad rating n/or not so healthy to eat! Try it out! ;-)

title: It's as important as my shopping list!
body: It keeps me on track for healthy choices! I really like this app because of it's usefulness when shopping for good food choices outside of fruits and vegetables. Before I was always having to read labels watching for true whole grain, low fat, low sugar etc. This app does that for me. I do wish it included more HEB brands..they really have good products. Maybe they will add more of them as more Texans hear about this great app tool.

title: Excellent for healthy eating
body: Great app if you're starting to diet and are unfamiliar with what to look out for. Reading the nutrition label is like trying to read a chemistry book. And what this app points out are some crucial information that you don't get by reading the side of a box. Since I've gotten this app I've used it every time I shop and it's been extremely helpful. Truly recommend it!! Only con: need to expand healthy alternatives; list is very limited.

title: Unbelievably Great!!!
body: I am not only a food junkie, but a diet/healthy lifestyle app junkie as well.  Since purchasing this app, I have deleted all of my other diet/healthy eating apps.  This app has it all - scanner, food choice grading with better selection alternatives,  calorie counter with exercise inclusion, water counter, and much, much more bundled in one user-friendly app.  The only downside I can think of in reviewing this app is that I cannot give it more than five stars.

title: Fantastic!
body: Just what I've been looking for. I use this app all the time at the store. It's not hard to use, I just open the app scan the barcode and it gives me all the information I need, from highly processed foods, to high sodium, to sugar content, this app is great if you're trying to have a healthy lifestyle. If the information you want is not in the app scan it and send them the information and they will update it!

title: love it, BUT
body: we're all fighting for gmo-labeling on our foods, right? and if it isn't fair that organic farmers have to pay big bucks to get the 'certified' label on their foods, then how is it fair that fooducate is withholding their gmo knowledge from those of us without premium accounts? i think we all agree that we shouldn't have to pay to know what is in our food and how it was grown; so why don't you lead by example, fooducate?

title: Good But.....
body: I like that it has pictures of the food and that it gives you food grades(A.B,C,D).  It also gives you daily point and daily calories allowed which is good if you like the points program; however, the food database is small especially for restaurant items. The My Fitness Pal has everything, I've never had to add an item on that app while I have had to put in a lot of effort to add foods on this app.  One final note, servings are only available in .5 increments which is not always accurate, sometimes I'd like to put in 3/4 or 1/8 of a serving.

title: Read this if you're wise
body: It's not specific in some effects of the foods. For example, with the research I done on artificial colors, they state that high doses of "Red dye..."to rats cause cancer, which they say they banned. That doesn't mean we can get get cancer if we eat that specific item we scanned. Also they say others things but I'm lazy to say, just do research. My suggestion is to scan and do research on what shows red in writing, you may change your mind. Don't always trust what people say, be wise and stay happy.

title: My favorite app
body: This app is my most used app by far. I'm not into calorie counting and but do like to try and put healthy food in my body but sometimes it's not clear in the grocery store what's actually healthy and whats not. I love how easy it is to use and if a food doesnt have the healthy rating that you thought it would, fooducate has suggestions for you to eat instead and tells you why it's not that healthy. And scanning the food is really fun :)

title: Happy Appy
body: This has been well worth the cost (a tiny bit of space on my phone)--it's free! True, some of the foods you'll scan will be missing, but you can be part of the solution and easily submit them to Fooducate. The product info is very helpful when shopping and helps you look past product marketing (which runs close to fiction) and get to the real food values. Quit wasting your time reading this and try it...!

title: Pretty good
body: I think out of all the possible nutrition apps, this is one of the better ones. It definitely helps you realize what exactly is in your food and why its there (emulsifier, preservative, etc.), and its range of producs it has grades for and gives reviews on is impressive. The one drawback of this app is that the information it gives on products will start getting repeptitive and some products will have a "bad grade" without an explanation as to why other than "they're a chip/snack product".

title: Very Useful
body: I do not use shopping apps, but I have found Fooducate to be very useful in the supermarket for several reasons. 1. I can instantly check on the nutritional quality when trying to compare similar products with different brand names. 2.  The shopping list is useful and right on my phone, so there is no paper list. 3. The A, B, C, D . . . grading feature is an immediate indicator to rejecting or further considering a food item (e.g., a D gets little consideration).

title: Great Resource for Healthy Food
body: It is so simple to use and really helps you stay on track! I use it to track my calories, fat, cholesterol, sodium, workouts, etc.

title: FOODUCATE
body: This is a great App! I like being able to make healthy food choices and keep track of my eating (good) habits. Thus I always have my own grocery list right on my iPhone! There are times that I don't make the right choice. Love the alternative option of finding a healthier choice! The food scanner is my favorite!  I can take my iPhone to the grocery store & scan my food choices with my Fooducate App. This comes in really handy!

title: Food Education! Fooducate!
body: Think you know a lot about the food you eat and how it works in your body? Think again and get Fooducate! This APP has already helped my family stay healthy! We thought we knew it all about food and the food industry and nutrition but Fooducate teaches us very vital information that we need to stay healthy. You won't believe the amount of information you can learn through this valuable tool!

title: In LOVE!!
body: I absolutely love this app!!! It allows you to track EVERY calorie that you put in your body and even allows you to track calories burned! When you first set it up it'll ask you your weight, intentions (to gain/loose), and it'll tell you how many calories a day you need to consume! If you work out you can input it and it'll track it! This app is an amazing tool to weight loss success! I'm down 6lbs in 8 days (and I'm NOT starving myself!)!!!

title: Best one I tried
body: I went on line, compared, and tried Atkins, "Carb Diet" and this. By far this is the best. Carbs and calories, fairly easy to use, decent database...helps me look at whole picture whereas before I was only focusing on net carbs. Adding calories made a difference!!! I think their estimates of calories burned during exercise is high. And occasionally just shuts down out of the blue during entries. But again, best I've tried so went with the 5 star

title: App #5 is the keeper
body: News from docs the other day has me needing to cut out carbs and cholesterol. Searched online for best apps. Tried several before finding this one. Very easy, clean, intuitive interface. Love the tracking device and how it can be personalized. I'm trying the free version for now but will likely pay for the year subscription soon. Thanks for a great app. Probably one of the most important ones I'll ever own.

title: Great app! Easy to use!
body: This is a great app! Super easy to use! Love, love that it gives you lots of great info. in addition to calories, saturated fats et... It educates you on things like TBHQ, other types of preservatives, gives you healthy recipes and alternatives for store bought box products!!! It's for everyone! My 12 yr old has been using it, checking out various products when we hit the store. I've recommended it to my fitness studio clients.... they love it too!!! Love it!

title: Absolutely love this app
body: Easy to use interface, at-a-glance food rating, and it actually made shopping with my 14-year-old son fun.  He enjoyed scanning the items and seeing their rating, and he made smart choices. I learned that some of the choices I was making when buying groceries such as cereals and "healthy" sandwich meats were not so smart.  I have recommended this app to many friends, and they are also happy with it.

title: Best App Ever!!
body: I LOVE THIS APP!! As others have said, I thought I was fairly knowledgable about the foods that I eat, I was dead wrong! I love the fact that you can not only scan the barcode, but also look up specific items by name. Other awesome features include: alternatives to the food you scanned, comparison of two different foods, GMO info, and weekly contests that cost nothing! they also have web support and a fb page.

title: Very helpful.
body: I liked this app a lot because it helps you track not only the calories you take but it breaks down the nutrient part too. It made me aware of the amount of carbs, protein, and fat I take in every meal. It also had a bonus of tracking the kind of food I consume (i.e., gmo or ngmo). The thing that I wished they improve is the availability of product information. Some of the products are not yet in the system. But other than that I highly recommend this app to anyone.

title: Tons of missing food & inaccuracies
body: I bought the premium version of this app ($40) to replace myfitnesspal and have something that gives better information about each food. It's such a great concept except a lot of the foods I scan are not in their system so I'm then prompted to add it for them. Then when foods are in the system they are very often wrong nutrition info including stating they are non vegetarian when they really are or saying their are GMOs when there are not. On top of that my scanner only works about half the time. So I paid $40 to use an app that barely works and I am spending time adding foods for them. I'm so disappointed.

title: 3 Stars
body: Fooducate is better used as a reference than as a food logger. MyFitnessPal does a much better job in regards to having many foods available to log so you don't have to manually type in every ingredient. This app does show more information about the actual content of the food (not just the calories). 3 stars. I prefer MyFitnessPal, purely because it is more user-friendly and you are able to easily connect with friends, as opposed to Fooducate. This app is best for someone who eats mainly natural/non-processed foods. MyFitnessPal is better for the average person.

title: Amazing App - Must have if you are trying to eat healthy
body: This app is wonderful and extremely helpful.

title: Amazing app!!
body: This app is so helpful in so many ways for me. I've been using it for 2 weeks and have lost 10 pounds so far. It's great because it makes it so easy to see what you're putting in your body. It rates your food and actually tells you why it was rated that way and alternative choices if you need it. I recommended it to several people and they love it too. This app is literally changing my life. I love it.

title: Educational and useful
body: Fooducate is by far the best fopd tracking app out there. Not only can you track calories and nutrition, as well as look up specific products, but the app will actually tell you which foods to avoid and which to buy based on a health scale. It will tell you what grade each food item you eat is and why, as well as offer helpful tips and educational explanations. It is well worth the trouble of inputting your foods!

title: Not quite 5 stars yet
body: I would rate 5 stars, but I have only been using it for a few days now. The app is better than I thought it would be. I absolutely love the rating system that it has for food products. It also explains why it has the rating. Also, if a nutrition label is off, wrong or missing, you can send in pictures of it.

title: Amazing App for Smart Food Choices
body: I recently downloaded this app based on a clients testimonial she recommended using this FREE app after she started the 24 Day Challenge and needed to make some smarter food decisions, and hates reading LABELS!!! I'm recommending it to all of my clients, who have iPhones, to use this when they decide its time to make better choices in their grocery shopping and food preparation, especially when they re on the 24 Day Challanges and thereafter for the BEST results.

title: Free app with excellent customer service!?
body: I was scanning everything within reach after downloading this app. I scanned a bag of tortilla chips that wasn't in the database. I did not take the pics to send to the Fooducate team, but a few days later someone else did. Fooducate sent me a message informing me that the info has been added to the database. The info this app provides is great and the follow up and customer service make it amazing! Download now!

title: This is amazing!
body: I love this app, it has helped open my eyes to undercover unhealthy foods. I also use it every day at work (teaching) to check allergens in the kids foods, frankly I was surprised to find how much crud/fillers are in food. The diary for tracking food is so easy to use and I love the newsletter full of healthy tips. Thank you so much for this wonderful app! This makes my healthy lifestyle choice easier to reach and fun. I recommend this app to any one.

title: Lovin' It
body: I've only recently found this app but must say that I'm loving it so far regarding the grading system used to help me sort through all the food products that are available out there.  I want to be educated and make sure I made good, healthy and conscious food decisions because it definitely plays an integral part of your life!

title: Don't like the update
body: I can't stand the update. Tracking gmo's and sugar content use to be free. Along with eating heart healthy and now since doing the update, I have to pay for them!!? This irks me so bad considering I've had this app since it came out.

title: 41 yr old Wife and Mom
body: Got the free version of the app after my baby was born in July, but really didn't do anything with it. Purchased the 1 yr plan and have been using it religiously since 1/5/15 and, as of this morning, I've lost 9lbs!!! (Due to a recent shoulder injury, the weight lose is based strictly on dietary changes; NO exercise.  And I allow myself a cheat day once per week where anything goes!).  It really helps me hold myself accountable for what and how I'm eating. I recommended it to all my Facebook friends!

title: A fantastic app
body: I recommend this app for everyone who is concerned about their diet and health. I use it s lot at the store while shopping. I've pulled products from the shelf, scanned them with the app, and then put them back after reading the results. But when I find a food with a good result it often will become one of my regular foods. I love specially like the emails I get with nutritional advice. You can't go wrong with this app.

title: Easiest diet tracker app I've used to date
body: Fooducate provides a variety of food choices from  commercial to homegrown to track with a detailed list of notional in for each item. Interaction with other users for support and feedback. But my favorite part that makes it stand out from ALL the other apps is that it interfaces with the iPhone/iPad Health Kit; logging all your information on you device for you.

title: Simply Excellent!
body: This, hands down, is the best food nutrition app I have come across. It not only shows me the nutrition metrics but it also provides explanations for why a food item is good or bad. Not only that, it provides a list of better alternatives for you to try on your next meal. It truly does a fantastic job of educating users about nutrition. I will certainly be purchasing lifetime subscriptions to their products! Thank you awesome app peeps :)

title: Great App!
body: This is a terrific app for weight loss and nutrition! I've been using it for about 2 months and have lost 7 pounds (13 more to my goal!) It not only counts calories, but also gives food ratings. Trying to eat only A's and B's has really helped me change my habits. I have the full version and it keeps track of added sugar. That's been a key for me as well. The community chat is great and the app itself is easy to use.

title: Rethinking my pantry now!
body: Just got this app on a whim because I saw the icon in an ad. Went to my pantry and randomly scanned some food items. Amazing discoveries!! I thought I was a careful shopper but this app uncovers many dirty little food secrets. Its not all negative and scary: in fact my pantry gets plenty of good grades too. Mostly though, I love the quick and easy info I get when I scan. This app is going to be one I use every day.  Thank you Fooducate makers!

title: Most loved and used app I haveüç¥üçâ
body: This app has so many useful features that I don't know where to start!

title: Great app!
body: As a physician, I think this app is really nice in terms of simplifying what are good food choices for my patients.  I understand fooducate is trying to roll out versions or updates that include special diets.  I think it would be really helpful to be able to specify all the dietary needs of an individual. For example, low sodium and carb control. But all that said I think this app is wonderful... If only more of my patients were tech savvy!

title: Great app for someone interested in losing weight
body: Love the scan option, also love that if an item isn't in the database you can send its info in and they will eventually add it for you. However, I'd really like to have it track my other nutrients other than just calories. Love that it reminds you to add your meals and love that it warns against GMOs and other health risks. Exercises are kind of lacking. Most of the time is have to use another app to track that and then manually add it to this one.

title: Inconsistent
body: I like this app in theory.  I have seen several circumstances of products whose nutritional facts and ingredient list do not match what it says on Fooducate. Within the app I have tried to select 'contact support' to report issues I have found and it just takes me back to the home screen.  Functionality for that needs to be improved.  Also I have seen items that have gotten very poor ratings and their alternatives that they suggest are exactly the same but get a better rating.  Doesn't make much sense to me.

title: Very impressed
body: This is hands down the best diet/nutrition app I've ever used. Lots of apps track calories and basic nutrients, but I've never found another that tracks as efficiently for me as this one. I can finally use an app to keep with my goal of cutting carbs and upping protein! Plus, having a feature that suggests healthier alternatives to the food you already have is an absolute life saver. Would definitely recommend.

title: Use responsibly
body: This app has a tracking option which is amazing and it grades food items to give tHe consumer an idea of what the food means. Aside from this it offers a community board where anyone using the app can make comments, ask questions, and support one another. This is wonderful, unfortunately the makers of the app do not regulate what is out on the board and I see a lot of wrong information being shared, just recently someone was advertising herbalife as the solution to everything. Wonderful app just needs monitoring.

title: Great Nutritional Information!
body: Comparing Fooducate to My Fitness Pal, I much prefer Fooducate because of the nutritional information and grading of foods in its database, as well as the user's ability to add foods to the database. I used MFP several years ago and don't recall this feature. Fooducate is easy to use, helps you track your caloric intake and physical activity, and also posts articles on health and nutrition. I'm thrilled that all of these features are in one app!

title: New Year's Resolution..ers!!!
body: If you're looking for an App to help you learn how to take control of your appetite, this is IT!!  Not only does it help you learn about which foods are better for you..and gives you alternative suggestions, the member community is GREAT!  Lots of people with lots of experiences and knowledge willing to support you every step of the way!  No judgements, no 'attacking!' ...just helpful motivation!!  Remember:  the change you want to make can't be immediate to be long-lasting. This is a LIFESTYLE change!  Come join us!  You'll be glad you did!!!

title: Must-Have App for a Healthy Lifestyle
body: Very thankful for such a beneficial app to track weight loss progress, view healthy meal ideas, and search for almost every food item currently available on the market today. The Fooducate team performs all necessary research (with citations!) to effectively inform users about what they are consuming. With this app, there is virtually no reason to be uneducated about what you are consuming each day. Thank you!

title: Almost Perfect
body: This is a well-designed app that is both easy to use and useful. The adds in the free version are not intrusive and do not interfere with using the app. My only criticism is the lack of detailed information on nutritional values. Fooducate gives a "grade" and the total calories. It does not tell you how many calories come from carbohydrates or unsaturated fat, for example. Does not provide specific ingredients. Fooducate did tell me that they are going to provide this info in future version.

title: Great app!
body: I love this app! No problems thus far. My only negative is that when your shopping it doesn't always have the information for "house brands" like those specific to a store such as aldi or trader joes, or off-brands like those carried at Costco and such. The app gives u ability to scan and file information yourself, but I find difficult to get whole label scanned for nutrition info. Other than that five stars!ÓåµÓåµÓåµÓåµÓåµ

title: Love, love this App!
body: No matter what type of diet you are using, Weight Watchers, Low Carb, Low Calorie or some other type this is a great tool. Not only do you get your calorie or point value, you also get complete nutritional value, this app let's you know if there is gluten or salt and how much. It also tells you if it's overly processed. All this information is based on serving size and allows for an informed decision before you take that first bite.

title: Great for tracking brand-name foods.
body: This app delivers most of what I was looking for, but it's a little weak on generic food items. Produce items are well covered, but try searching milk, eggs, meat, grains, pulses, cheese, and you are presented with lists of brand-name products, with no easy way to select just generic 2 eggs, chicken breast, 4 oz ground beef, 1/2 cup brown rice,etc. You can enter these items, but you have to do the nutrition info and food grading yourself. A better database of generic food items would make this a 5-star app.

title: Best app for a healthy life
body: Leading a healthy lifestyle sounds easy enough, right? Could be, but there are a lot of obstacles trying to divert our attention from eating healthy, making healthy choices, and exercising. Fortunately, FOODUCATE

title: Good App for Basic Recordkeeping
body: I've used this app for a while with great results. BUT I have noticed that the database of entered food that comes with the app has redundancies and errors; there are some foods that are exactly the same with different calorie amount (for example). If you use this program, you cannot -- and should not -- rely solely on the database, but you should double check the labels and, if unsure, check other sources.

title: Best app out there but still could improve
body: It's by far the easiest app to use. However, there are a few things that bother me. First, they don't track sugar, which is one of the major belly fat causes. Seems odd bc we are trying to lose weight!  Second, they don't let you add an item from yesterday to today. That's annoying. Yes, they keep a list of recent items, but usually it's just faster to rescan than deal with that all over again.

title: Great App
body: I'll keep this short because I don't usually do this but this app is great. I found it today by accident and am amazed by the wealth of information it provides. I went grocery shopping today and spent most of the time scanning everything I picked up and seeing how fooducate rated it and its recommendation for an alternative.

title: OK, but beware of premium
body: Overall this ap is good for tracking calories and a lot of nutritional info. I upgraded to premium to track how much cholesterol I was eating. But when they say you can "track cholesterol" with the premium, they mean enter in your score results from the doctor's office--not track your daily intake of it. Not worth it to upgrade to the premium versions. Also, I'm not sure how to manage the Fooducate points. Today, I am 200 calories under my goal, my calorie quality grade is A- so why am I over on my Fooducate allotment?

title: Bare Basic Minimum
body: Unless you want to pay one of their monthly fees and I don't, this app is pretty useless. Everything that would make this a useful app, requires the "pro" (fee) version. For example, I can't update my weight, BMI, add exercise activities (outside of the app (Nike+) and other features that would help me to achieve my goals.

title: Couldn't get much better!
body: I've been with fooducate since almost the beginning. It was a great app and an awesome concept with so much potential- and boy, after such a short amount of time, they've already made it practically perfect! Let me tell you what, this app changed my life. I started eating only foods with a and b grades and I never could have imagined that I would ever have this much energy! I love everything now!

title: Great app overall
body: This app has surprised me. I eat pretty healthy but found that some of the stuff I have been eating has not been as nutritional as I think. This is awesome for helping to sort out the massive amount of information out there about what foods are good for you! My only complaint is that sometimes things are not listed or registered, so the more people who use it and add to it, the better it will get.

title: Obsessed!
body: Seriously a life saver! I used to spend double the time grocery shopping reading all of the ingredients! Now I scan and done! Most times I find something better. The only thing is that the better option usually isn't available at main grocery stores so I now shop at sprouts and trader joes.

title: Great app, sometimes misleading
body: Great idea and format.  Unfortunately, some information is based on old rebutted research, or just straight hippie paranoia or misinformation from "research" that isn't credible.  For example, MSG sensitivity is a myth, as you would be allergic to a naturally occurring compound in your body if this was the case (and there has never been a confirmed case of such a disorder).  If you have special dietary needs or need to watch your food intake. make sure to educate yourself on the facts and maybe even consult with a good nutritionist or doctor in conjunction with using this app.

title: Best ever!
body: I love this app! It's so user friendly and has many features that are incredibly useful without upgrading to a pro version. It's really easy to look up foods and even add them to the database if they're not listed. This app is a great reference beyond just calorie count--there is a ton of information about food additives, sugar sources, other chemicals, etcetera. It's super handy to add foods to a food tracker and exercise too. Wonderful!

title: You don't deserve a ban
body: I speak the truth and mostly the truth. Well this app doesn't like honest opinions so it banned me for saying what I thought was true. The whole point of the app is to learn, but clearly they'll ban you if you say something "incorrectly". I didn't offend the person, curse at the person, I just gave my honest opinion about the food they ate. If they don't like my honesty, instead of a fake statement such as "wow how healthy, looks delicious" then they can go and do business with themselves. If you like to be fake and give fake opinions, then download it, otherwise stay very, very far away from it. This app deserves every 1 star rating it can get.

title: Easy to use and informative
body: The UI changes pretty often and sometimes not for the better. Any change should make the most frequently accessed items easier to find but they seem to add an extra tap every now and the. That cost them one star. The information is really helpful in leading a healthy life and the data integrates with Apple Health well. I am starting to use it daily and on shopping trips to avoid GMOs and track my diet.

title: Excellent App
body: It is very useful application, you have all the information and easily you can pursue your your diet goals.

title: Awesome!
body: This app has clearly identified and open eyes to look for my favorite foods that should be an A or B safe to eat products. And better answers to understand what those ingredients are in the Nutrition list too. Not everything in the market is safe for us to keep a healthy diet balance. Download and see for your self. Check out Fed Up Movie too. It's sad we are being sold this items in the market.

title: Excellent
body: This app confirms the old adage that knowledge is power. It allows you to have a much better sense of what you‚Äôre eating, how much of it you‚Äôre eating - and if you should be eating it at all. And it makes it kind of fun too. The Pro features are definitely worth it, as it allows you to track protein, fat, sodium, etc, as well as weight and other medical info. Support person was helpful and super nice too

title: Fooducate
body: What an incredible app!!! When your @ the store and about to make a food choice...you have a super easy, really fast way to assess your choice to see if it's all it can be for you.  Quick & easy way to offer alternative & healthier choices.  It's points out products that have controversial additives that could be carcinogenic!  It's a really fun way to help you quickly make better food choices...and it's free!  Love it!!!

title: Eating healthy (finally)
body: I just found out that I have some health concerns that require me to watch what I eat. It seems overwhelming at times but Fooducate is really helping me realize I can do this. I can make the right decisions in what to eat. I know my family is eating healthier too. My doctor is impressed with the way the program is assisting me making appropriate food choices. Great program and easy to use. Thank you.

title: For Health And Knowledge
body: As an entertainer I love to push myself to limits I couldn't see the day before. Therefore if I want the results, I need to eat satisfyingly to my mental goals. This app is everything and then some! It breaks down all key ingredients and what could hurt or help me. They rate all foods in their category from an A to F scale (They're honestly rated; I haven't seen an A+ yet). I recommend this to anyone wanting to take their knowledge to the next level.

title: Fooducate Review
body: LOOOOOVE this app! It makes it so easy to not only stick to a healthy eating plan, but to also know which foods are the most healthy for your plan. Once your eyes are opened as to what is really in some of the food we all eat, it's blatantly obvious how harmful it is to our bodies. Fooducate helps you find the healthy/organic foods that will help you not only lose weight, but detoxify your body from the toxins that are in GMO foods. Highly recommend!

title: Awesome
body: I love this app. I take it out each time we go grocery shopping. It helps me decide and find the healthier product, tells me why a product was given its rating and why certain ingredients should be avoided. I've also learned a few things that got me to switch from a product that I thought was good to something better...and this is just the basic use of it. I just learned there's a whole lot more to this app that I have yet to utilize.

title: Relieved
body: I have been looking for a calorie/serving diary app alllll day! I am so relieved to find it...I was about to develop one for myself. The barcode scan works great and the database is up-to-date. It also included BMI calculation and info. That's great! The suggested calories for height, age and goal weight is correct. It also has FoodPoints (food grades) and alternative recommendations. I love that! I recommend this app for anyone looking for a genuinely helpful calorie counter.

title: Brenda
body: This app has been very helpful in the grocery store. It assists in making healthier choices.  I am being held accountable for each food item I take in.  Although some items are not readily available by scanning, I'm sure to find something comparable to enter.  You always have the choice in helping the app by providing pictures and nutrition information so it can be added.

title: Love this app!
body: This app is great! I follow weight watchers and am able to use this one without paying the additional for theirs! I am amazed at all of the items I scan that are in the Fooducate data base. I also like that I am able to add an item if it's not available to my foods. Fooducate adds it to their database quickly too! This app makes keeping a food diary fun and easy! I'm well on my way to swimsuit season!

title: Loooooove this app!! Best one for weight loss!!
body: I love everything about this app!!! I downloaded it after seeing it in a magazine & have found it my duty to tell ALL of my friends & coworkers about it. Easiest & most helpful tool to help aid weightloss. We all know we have to count calories but searching or inputting it yourself is a drain & you get bored/over it after a day. Fooducate makes everything easy with its scanner!! Love love love!!

title: Best All Around Nutrition App
body: This app is great whether you are dieting or eating for health.  I refer to the site every day and have learned so much about the nutritional value of a variety of foods.  It's easy to scan a product at the grocery using this app to determine if it's healthy or simply advertised as healthy.  Often I find that foods promoted as healthy or junk food disguised as healthy.  It also gives healthier choices.

title: A Winner ... With potential to be even netter
body: I just got this app but I'm impressed. SO easy to scan a barcode and get a rating. I'm hoping they'll give more reasons for their ratings in the future. Also, can't personalize ratings now, but they say that's coming. I hope this will mean we can add filters like "gluten free." They also make it very easy to use iPhone to send them new products to add to their database. Way to go, developers!

title: I'm a teen, and I find this fun! d;  b
body: I took a day and scanned almost everything in my kitchen, and was shocked at how much I didn't know about what I was putting into my body! My parents recently lost weight, so they usually payed attention to mostly just calories, so I was always interesting in that too. Bu with this app, I now know there's more to being healthy than just calorie count! I'm looking forward to eating healthful foods. Thanks Fooducate!

title: Love it!
body: This is easy to use and fun to see what you thought was healthy really isn't!  Just scan and wait for the results!  It even gives you healthier alternatives. However, I didn't give it 5 stars because I would like to know where I can find these healthier options. It shows and tells you about these products but some are not easy to find at regular grocery stores. maybe on the next update we'll see this!  Other than th

title: Nice app
body: This app is easy to use and provides great info on why a food is not good for you and suggestions for food that is. If they do not have info on a food, they have you photograph and send the label to them by email. It is great to know that they are trying to improve. My only quibble is that there could be better options offered for healthy alternatives to junk food like chocolate. The app suggested that instead of a Hershey bar that I have a banana. What PMSing girl wants that?

title: Makes food shopping more fun!
body: Definitely a fun little trick to have in your back pocket while shopping. Really eye opening to see what you actually buy. Love the alternate suggestions given for each product and the ability to compare two products instantly. Lots of products already in there so you'll have a blast at your next trip to the grocery store!

title: Awesome App!
body: If you're trying to eat healthier, this app us a must have. It helps explain many of those hard to pronounce ingredients and gives better alternatives when applicable.

title: Amazing Resource!
body: Love lots of features from the grading of foods (A-F), ability to scan barcode of food eaten, details for grading of food, percentage of minimally processed, daily tips, and links to learn more bout food nutrition or harmful additives.  I use this app everyday!

title: Never, ever loads....so frustrating!!
body: When I first got this app, I was very happy. It's got great info and was exactly what I was looking for to help get my family's eating more on track. However, in the last two months I have been unsuccessful in getting the database to load so, I can actually use the app. I always want to blame my connection but when I'm using my own wifi and I'm not having issues with anything else, I have to wonder about the app.

title: I love this app so much
body: Im not a dieter or fitness freak but I do try as hard as I can to eat non-GMO, non dyed, non processed, etc types of foods and this app helps SO much! A quick 2 second barcode scan and you know just about everything you need to and it's usually very accurate. Only thing I noticed was it said tap water is perfectly safe and I have to disagree with that, other than that amazing app

title: Very helpful information
body: Knowing what's actually in the food and drinks we consume is a nightmare... unless of course you go to the market and buy fresh actual food and prepare it yourself.  Or, unless you scan it into  Fooducate's data base and let them tell you. It's great to know what they think of a product. The facts are right in front of you.  They also have great recipes and a lot of other goodies.

title: Great app- in so many ways
body: This app is not only helpful but very educational.. It doesn't just explain WHAT is bad for you/good for you, but also WHY. I love this app and use it all the time- my favorite part about introducing this app to friends is watching their response after they use it... It is important to understand why foods are good and bad for you and what alternatives there are out there. Thanks so much for making this app.

title: My favorite app yet!
body: This is the very best app! If you're trying to stay on track with Weight Watchers, and you want to feed your family healthier, and you want your whole family to have fun while trying to navigate food shelves then this app is for you. Super fast scanning of even obscure products. I kept trying to trick it and I couldn't get over it's accuracy. My whole family loves it.

title: One of the most useful apps out there
body: I have bought apps in the past that look good then never use them because they are not very useful.  Not this app!  It shows me everything I need to know before buying!  The best part is that if they don't have what you scanned in their database, you can take pictures of it to have it added.  Super easy, the app just walks you through it!  Genious app!!!ÓÄ¢ÓÄ¢ÓÄ¢ÓÄ¢ÓÄ¢

title: Love it!
body: This is by far my new favorite app! It's so easy to use and convenient and has so many different products in the database.  If you are looking to maintain a healthy diet then this app is your new best friend. Not only does it give each product a grade rating, but it also breaks down the important things you need to know like controversial ingredients and the existence of trace amounts of trans fat. Absolutely recommend this app!

title: Great Nutritional Tool
body: Fooducate is amazing, easy and fast at providing nutritional information on everyday items we hardly think of. I have been using it when I go grocery shopping and have been scanning food already in my refrigerator. Thanks to the  letter grading system, I have been apple to choose healthier food alternatives. Everyone should use this it really does help eat healthier and live healthier. : ]

title: I love it!
body: I have now started trying to maintain healthy eating habits... I came to know about this app through my friend and I immediately downloaded it...

title: Best app ever!!
body: I never write reviews, but I had to let everyone know how good this app is. It alerts you when you are close to a supermarket so that you buy healthy stuff, but the thing I like the most from it is that not only do you get ratings and advise from the fooducate professional team, you can also see what users think about the product which is very helpful.

title: Awesome!
body: It's really neat to be able to visualize what I'm putting into my body. I assumed I was eating fairly healthy, but it turns out I have some opportunity for improvement. The scanner is convenient although it would be nice to have some quick fresh meal options already stenciled out so you don't have to add each component of a fresh dish individually. Overall I think this app is a must have.

title: Wonderful app
body: I have been using my Fitness Pal for years. I liked the app for tracking food intake and exercise but it doesn't educate you like this app. I prefer the letter grade for each item I eat and the reasoning behind the grade. It also provides alternative choices as well.

title: Even better than my fitness pal
body: I have used my fitness pal for years. I have always loved it, but needed a change to jump start my fitness goals. I tried several different apps but none compared to MFP. That is until now. I love this one even more. It's not just a tracker, but it really is an educator. It provides useful and thought provoking insight to really teach you how to live healthier. 5 stars!!

title: Amazing!!
body: I'm currently working on getting my Ph.D. In Nutrition and I use this everyday due it it's amazing and CORRECT information. I use this everyday, not because I'm a shopping mom who wants to buy better for her family, but because I am a college guy that is staying away from any kind of weight gain and also want to stay healthy. It's fun to use on stuff that you're curious is actually as healthy as the box says it is. GREAT APP!!! Get it!!!!!

title: Invaluable tool! Get this one.
body: If you are interested in what you put into your body! This app is an invaluable tool!  I appreciate the instant letter grades given to rate an item- especially when I'm shopping.  I like the in-depth details on content- and the ability to compare similar products.

title: My favorite app!
body: I love this app. Fast and reliable, it helps me choose the best possible foods for my family - older parents as well as kids. I love the comparison and alternative options features, especially when it shows the best alternative option for a sweetened drink is really just a glass of water!  Yes, this changed my daughter's decision about what to get!  Highly recommend this app to all my friends.

title: Fooducate rocks!!
body: When you're stumbling through the grocery store aisle looking at 8 different brands of a product all claiming to be the greatest (and some with some unknown ingredients) it can be extremely frustrating. The sense of empowerment with the touch-of-a-finger advice that fooducate provides cannot be put in words. It's easy to use and informative and best of all...it provides you with better alternatives! Love it! Love it! Love it!

title: Best app ever!
body: I just started the Whole healthy thing two days ago and this app has been very helpful. I'm skinny but I LOVE to eat which can be a problem in my family. This app has helped me realize that I can't just eat everything and then some. What I like about this app is even though I'm not trying to lose weight, it recommends me healthier alternatives. My ONLY PROBLEM: it freezes up sometimes which can be REALLY annoying but overall it's a great app. üòäüòÄ

title: What an eye opener!
body: I have been learning over the last few years about the harmful additives in our currant mainstream diet. However it has been hard to remember all the information necessary to help make heathy choices. Fooducate dies a great job off helping me keep my eye on what is good and bad choices and keeping well informed on how to choose a heathy alternatives. I have even learned about some heathy foods I never heard of before. I buy nothing new without checking with Fooducate.

title: Really good App!! BUT......
body: I really love everything about this app... The layout , the features, everything!

title: Best of its kind
body: I LOVE this app.  It gives you realistic alternatives to the foods that you like to eat but aren't good for you.  If you want a burger it doesn't say eat a carrot instead.  I use this app everyday and it really helps me make better choices about my food.  I wish they had more fast-food info on here as I travel a lot and sometimes have no choice but to eat airport food for days.

title: Learning so much!
body: Downloaded this app 3 days ago, and it's already my favorite. The scanning feature is the absolute best. Just when you think about cheating on your clean eating/real food lifestyle, you scan something that is graded as a D+. If reading about additives and chemicals doesn't motivate you to choose a healthier choice, not sure anything will. Such a great tool for guiding a healthy & smart lifestyle.

title: Very well done
body: I have been using this app for about a week now, and I appreciate how clean and simple the user interface is, while maintaining its utility. I appreciate being able to track the overall nutrition and health of my food choices, to attempt to live a more healthy lifestyle, rather than just counting calories.

title: Great app
body: And the other reviewers have valid points about the database, but the only way to make this better is to send them updates. It's extremely easy and thus far I've had no problems. You might get an email saying they're swamped but at least they respond, which is more than I can say for other apps. I am absolutely loving this app and I think you will too.

title: Excellent app.
body: I have to say that Fooducate is very beneficial for whoever wants to eat healthier of for whoever is simply curious about what they're putting in their body. I rate the whole concept and options five stars. As for the phone application's scanner...  when I'm in a store, it may not recognize products well until I restart the app or wait for some time. All in all though, it makes a real impact and I recommend Fooducate to any customer shopping in a supermarket.

title: Holy Grail
body: I loved this app before the update. Since then it had become my fave! Not only can I see what is healthy, it tells my if the food might have GMOs, tells my how many calories, carbs or whatever I'm getting and tracks it for me! This app really couldn't be any better. My only minor suggestion for improvement is to actuate the flash in low light for scanning. Other than that, nice work!

title: Amazing
body: I thought I ate healthy before, I always check labels, but with all the Gmo in foods it's very hard to know what's in a product. The fact that I can simply scan a barcode and get told of any harmful ingredients, is life changing. I had no idea how horribly wide spread Gmo was, and the fact that any convince/fast food restaurant (like subway and panera) all use Gmo. I use this App everyday, and I'm very happy that I stumbled upon it.

title: Great App!!!
body: I love this app so far.  It makes tracking your dietary choices and goals so easy.

title: Wonderful
body: Finally a tool that I can use to track the ingredients of the food that I am eating.  Before I buy I could scan and review the product before committing to the product and then regretting what I bought.  I can create a grocery list That I can share with others.

title: Great info, could use some more
body: If you want to know the skinny on any pre-packaged food, Fooducate is the app for that. TONS of info; you might even learn a thing or two. But here's where I have a problem: if your goal is healthier eating, and you want to keep track of that, it's dang near impossible to use the tracking feature with fresh, unprocessed foods (which, again, fits into that whole "healthier eating" thing). I wish I could meld this with another app, My Fitness Pal, to get the complete picture of what I eat.

title: Pretty good app
body: Overall, this app works really well. Sometimes the calorie and nutritional info in the app doesn't match that of the product, but it's not off by too much. I'd like to see the exercises explained as I'm not always sure what to choose, i.e. What's the  difference between "biking to work" and "cycling"? How vigorous is "vigorous walking" compared to "moderate walking"?

title: Good app, needs more info
body: This is a great app for calorie counting, but could be improved for nutrition tracking. Much of the info is "user added" & is therefore missing a lot of information. I've also been prompted numerous times to add my own info.

title: Easy, accurate, gives alternatives
body: I've used several apps over my 2yr loss of 80lbs and this is my favorite.  I like that it gives options / alternatives and that I can bundle items to make a 'meal' and then re-use that meal and/or edit it.  Only using missing from perfect is having a Glance on my watch showing my daily total and from where I could add those standard meals or my food items.  That'd make it 5star perfect.

title: I love this app
body: I have not stopped scanning items in my house. I scanned an item not in their database and it asked me to help by taking photos and sending them along to them. I am on WW and it also gives you the point values. The only thing this app doesn't do is cook for me! I have an IPod touch so I cannot scan in the store but I know what I am buying so I search by item name before I go shopping. Live it!!

title: Fooducate
body: This is one of my favorite apps! I love using it while grocery shopping- it is very helpful when comparing products. The only negative is there seem to be duplicate entries with slightly different information and/or grades, and some entries only come up when searched by keyword instead of scanned barcode. Cleaning up the database would probably take care of that, though. The product alternatives list could use a little work as well.

title: Great tool, but imperfect
body: I like using this app when I'm trying to specifically decide between two similar products--in that capacity, it's helpful. However, the database is somewhat limited and the grading system is at times unnecessarily harsh (and unhelpfully so--it can make it seem like NO food is a healthy option, when all I want to know is THE healthiest option). Still, I turn to this app on a daily basis, and I find it to be overall worth the money.

title: Incredible!
body: Love this app!!!  Amazed at the things I think are healthy and find out they are not!  Especially kids snacks, I was convinced that goldfish cracker would be bad, when in fact they are better then the Annie's organic version I have been buying!  My quick grocery store runs have now taken twice as long because I'm so curious what the "best" brand is for everything I buy!

title: Fantastic awesome app
body: My sister in law told me about this app & I love it!  I've told so many people about it!  We have been more careful about the food we buy & been shocked at how things we thought were healthy but really weren't. Needless to say, my teenage son doesn't like this app b/c his favorite snacks are rated C or D!  Thank you.  Please expand your data base to include ethnic foods as well such as items found in Indian or Middle Eastern stores.

title: Freezing ?
body: I love this app, it is fantastic!  So the app is probably a 5 star.  But recently it has been freezing on me.  Some times it freezes when I want to scan something, then if I wait long enough it will eventually unfreeze on it's own.  But now it is frozen on a food result.  I scan scroll up and down on the food description, so the app itself is not frozen, However I can't use the controls on the top. So I am stuck inside this food, i can't get back to the home screen.

title: Frustrating
body: App food list is not geared for the Northeast.  Lots of trouble finding local foods in grocery stores and restaurants, even tho they are major chains.  Did a search for filet mignon- which I enjoyed over two days- and search came up with DOG food!  What that has to do with a human dietary plan escapes me!  Support is VERY slow in making effective changes.  Do like the tip explanations they give, however.  Sorry I spent the money for the Pro package.  Still hoping, however, that things will get better.

title: Awesome I love it! Very helpful!
body: I love this app. It helped me out a lot and gave me closure about a lot of the foods I've been eating what really shocked me was whole-grain bread. A lot of the stuff that you would think it's healthy but is most definitely not healthy for you. This app will stay with me! I recommend it to anybody that's trying to keep track and want to know the truth about what they're eating.

title: Takes a lot of effort out of healthy eating
body: With all the info out there about what is and isn't healthy it's easy to be inundated how many different things there are to remember: types of carbs, types of fats, processed, organic, hormone-free, sodium, nitrates, GMOs, vitamins, the list goes on. This app makes it so easy, just scan a food and see what's wrong with it! Saves me time at the store researching everything I buy.

title: LOVE
body: This is such a great app. We use it when we go grocery shopping and it's really easy to stay in the A/B range when all you have to do is scan the barcode real quick.

title: I am a dietitian
body: This app is great to get people to start eating better. Yes foods with additives aren't on my top ten favorites but in reality as long as you're getting ample vitamins, minerals, low fat, low calorie, whole grains, etc. That's what should be top priority and this app does it. Plus for ppl wanting to know about GMO I have news for you non GMO is not guaranteed in anything in america anymore at all since insects go from crop farm with GMO crops and pollinate non GMO crops.

title: Fooducate ME!!
body: and they did! I love this App.  2012 has really been our year to get healthy, and the one thing that has help us the most is realizing we need educated on the food we eat.  Fooducate has help so much. I enjoy interacting in their contest too, it's fun, you should try it.  How are we doing with our New Years Education on Food??,  my husband has lost 27 lbs and I have lost 14 lbs.  Good luck everyone, and thank you, Fooducate.

title: Fooducte review
body: Simply said, I love this app!!! I live how thorough it is with every item. I like that this app educates you on the ingredients in certain things and why to be concerned, even offers extra links if you want to learn more and some awesome alternatives. I could spend hours on this app especially because I know it is an investment in my health! A BIG thank you to the people who creates this wonderful app!!

title: Pretty good!
body: Solid App! I feel much more energetic than usual because of my diet choices. It is an excellent way to track what junk you are possibly putting into your mouth and to change your eating habits.

title: Good, not great
body: Nice app for the feedback of nutritional values, and better options tab.

title: 1st Tracker I've stuck with!!
body: This ap has kept me using it because of its multiple easy to use features! All food  nutrition values, exercise tracker with many choices (by the minute),   and added random nutrition related articles/ videos added daily, and goal setting/tracking keep me coming back daily!   I love the end of day summary! Keep adding the foods I send in! I üíú this ap!

title: Amazing!
body: This app has everything you could ever want in dieting or learning to eat healthier...calories, nutrients, macros, points, scanning, vast list of products, exercise tracking, community support. And you can't beat the price!! Best diet app I've ever seen...even better than weight watchers, which I lost 30 lbs on. Fooducate takes it to the next level...excited to see the results!

title: App used with Apple Health Tracker
body: I started out using the app in connection with the Heath app on my iPhone. I am doing my best to live healthier. I love that I can personalize my choices. I have always been frustrated by the ratios that diet plans give for carbs, protein etc. How to figure percentages were too complicated to track. But now with the pro version I see exactly what is going into my body through my choices. I love seeing the big picture of my health.

title: Best Health App Out There!
body: I don't usually write reviews but I had to for this app. It's so refreshing to see an app that keeps track of not only your calories but the QUALITY of the food you're eating. The fact that it gives you alternative, healthier options to any food is a great feature. I absolutely love this app, much more beneficial than other health apps out there.

title: This is way better than myfitnesspal
body: I appreciate this app way more because of the fact that it isn't bombarded with ads while you are tracking everything. It even provides you with healthier alternatives which is definitely amazing! The grade helps to show you where your food item ranges, more helpful than nutrition facts ever could.

title: Worth every second
body: While it may require two more seconds at each food item - your time is well spent! I don't read food labels but I love the compare option. Soup v soup- cereal v cereal. And I disagree with the rating that says "helping" the app is worthless. They don't have a lot at food lion - but I took a picture of each item they didn't have yet and I was immediately emailed with an update. Great app!

title: Hall of Fame Worthy Nutrition App!
body: This is one of the most useful apps that I've ever used.  The barcode scan feature is practical and convenient--I literally use it every day!  And the informational basis for the grading system has the unique attributes of being both thorough yet concise.  I hope this app continues to be maintained and updated, because I don't know how I can go back to living without it!

title: I LOVE IT !!
body: This is an EXCELLENT APP !!  I love the special features this has.. I love the fact that you can scan your product and if it gives it a low rating it will let you know of a more healthier product.. I also like how I don't feel like I need to join WeightWatchers to just find out my point value.. It's all right here in this APP.. I would HIGHLY recommend this APP to my family and friends..

title: Awesome!
body: Constantly use this app to track my calories, carbs, servings, exercise, weight, water intake.. Literally everything! I also use it to scan everything at the grocery store before I buy it, in order to make sure that everything is GMO free, and to see any pros/cons about the food. Love this app! You can personalize it for your own food needs too! Legit, this thing is so awesome!

title: Love Love Love It!!!!!
body: By far the best weight management app I have ever come across.  It's so simple and the health tracker is absolutely amazing!!!  The grading scale they have developed for this program makes shopping easy and fun and it also takes the guess work out of what to eat.  It's not a chore to chart your meals or anything else....I actually look forward to charting meals.  I just wish I had this app a long time ago!!!!

title: Not good for tracking what you eat...
body: Not good enough to track what you eat if you're on a weight loss journey BUT I do use it when I'm questioning quality of the processed food I'm buying. I like that I scan a product & then get suggestions of a better product. That's what I use this app for. I don't use it often but it is helpful when I do need it. I'd give this app 5 stars if the food consumption tracker was better & easier to use.

title: Great concept
body: I really like the concept of this app. The idea of giving foods a grade letter based on their nutritional value is awesome. And I love how alternative food choices are given. However, I'm really disappointed with the inconsistency of the grades. Foods will have different grades depending on whether I'm using my phone or my computer. A lot of times the current grade will differ from what reviewers have previously noted. I would love to use this as a resource but I'm just concerned that I'm not getting the correct information.

title: Extremely useful
body: I'm a college student trying to avoid her "freshman 15" and this app is perfect. I love the scanner which helps me to quickly log foods. I also love how easy it to adjust the servings and find foods. My one complaint would be into hard to find restaurant foods, but you can look up the nutritional information and find something close to it to log.

title: Great Tool!!
body: At first, I kept getting frustrated with learning that my favorite snacks and condiments were grade C or lower, but then I adjusted a few things, based off of their alternative suggestions. My body feels much healthier and happier as a result!

title: My Grocery Store Companion
body: This app helps me easily sift through lists of ingredients to ensure I'm making healthy choices at the grocery store. I'm always surprised when food that would seem healthy ends up with a "D" rating. With clever marketing schemes and loose standards on terms like "natural" or "low fat", Fooducate helps me to figure to decipher which foods are best for me. I recommend this app to all of my friends who are trying to make good decisions about their food choices.

title: Awesomeness!!!
body: This rocks! I love how I can find healthier food choices when I buy processed foods. I just wish the developers could keep up with the plethora of food items people are sending, it seems to take a bit for your food item to show up if it wasn't in the database already. But I love the message center when it tells you your food has been added and the games!

title: Best App!
body: I absolutely love this app!! It's amazing and tells you so much information on the food you scan! I scan everything I eat that has a barcode on it now! It's also super great at the grocery store when I'm deciding what to get and I could just scan to see if it's healthy. I also love I could keep track of my food in the health tracker. Really great app, highly recommend!

title: Why do I need an account now?
body: I loved this app and recommended it to a lot of people but in the recent upgrade, I have to create an account. I used to be able to save lists to my phone but I no longer have that option. I do not like creating an account for every app I download...it's just one more password to remember or get stolen. Facebook is an option, but I prefer not to use that either. It worked just fine storing the data locally, please give us that option back. In the mean time, if you don't want to create an account to just use an app, I suggest finding other app as I will be doing.

title: Food-u-catersssssss Mount Up
body: I love this app. I never knew that there could be such a big discrepancy in virtually the same products. One oatmeal might get an A vs another that might get a C. Many factors determine a grade such as sugar, processing amount, controversial ingredients etc. I carry the fooducate app in the supermarket with me and I scan everything. My only concern is that not every item comes up. Other than that, this app ROCKS.

title: Eye opening what's in food // grades!!
body: So surprised our sour cream was not so healthy. Most of our foods were but a few weren't! So impressed with alternative choices that were graded already!! So helpful in making decisions.!!! Very impressed that we can help update new products not already in memory base. Also the information details on ingredients ( mini nutrition class) is AWESOME. Well done bravo!!

title: The Best app in your smart Phone
body: Yes you may have many apps in your smart phone but this app only and the only one will help you to take care your health ...whenever I go shopping I use this app and I make sure others also use it remember you are what you eat ...

title: Love this thing!!
body: It even offers alternatives to foods you're sketchy on. Very helpful while shopping as well to steer you away from guilt. It works quickly so you're not spending any more time than what it would take to check the ingredients. I use it not so much for weight loss but as a way to judge what kind of foods I'm bringing in to my household for my kids and I to consume.

title: Use this everyday!
body: It started as a kind of homework assignment I had given myself, now I look forward to seeing what the grades will be and the quality of food I'm putting in my body. I'm down 41 lbs due tomorrow to being more aware of what is going into my body. If you're someone who wants to lose weight or just curious what you're eating....This is the app for you!

title: Full featured and user friendly
body: This app delivers on what most other nutrition apps promise but fall short of: it is an intuitive way to build a healthy lifestyle when it comes to diet.  The barcode scanning works like a dream and the additional information that the app gives on different foods helps build greater awareness of what one is really putting into one's body.

title: Great program
body: I was encouraged to start this by a trainer. It tracks your food like weight watchers. And adds the burn from exercise! I think it needs a little instruction button to help people find their way. I had a hard time figuring out how to do updates on my weight( the only way I found was changing it on my profile). And how to add exercise ( not on the daily tracker)

title: Love love love fooducate
body: This is one of the best apps!! I use it all the time now when I go shopping and it helps me to learn about a product so easily it's a no brainer!!! I have made so many healthier choices because of this app. I used to think I was making good choices for my kids only to find out what really was behind clever food marketing!!! Everyone should get this app- and it's free!!!

title: Helpful but have trouble taking pictures
body: I really like this app, enough that I've submitted several items.  Or at least I've tried to but the pictures taken look nothing like the images I see when trying to take the picture. One of the problems have been been the image will rotate and enlarge so the label  expands beyond the edges of the picture.  Otherwise, I've found most foods in the db and it's been useful.

title: Fooducate
body: This app is awesome, especially since  it is free.  So easy to use, just scan the barcode from any package. It gives you the food point value, similar to weight watchers. It also gives you a grade of the product along with a better alternative.  If they don't recognize the item simply take some pictures and they will figure it for you.

title: Valuable app
body: As a new Vegan, this has become a vital app to see how we are doing with the products we stocked in the pantry.  The first time I opened it, I scanned everything in the fridge and cupboards.  Some successes some errors.  I am so focused on buying things without animal products, that in reading labels I am missing other unhealthy additions.  I like that I can easily add items they have missed.

title: Great App
body: This app is awesome! So often, I think I'm making a healthy food decision and it really isn't. This app REALLY helps with that. I love that it gives alternatives and explanations.

title: A life-saver!!
body: This app is amazing!! I'm in awe at all the random, dangerous additives in food now-a-days! I'm a college student trying to avoid all highly processed foods - a seemingly impossible task with a small budget.. But Foodeducate has become my BEST FRIEND! I scan everything before I buy it! I've even recommended it to my family, and it has become a must-have shopping companion for them too! :D

title: Keeps shops honest!
body: I absolutely love this app! Having this had given me opportunities ta talk with store managers because they always want to know what i am doing scanning their food. This has opened up many doors of dialogue about the food they provide for me andy family!! Interesting how they are not quick to tell me how good a brand is anymore! Thank you so much for this tool!! Keep up the good work!!

title: I love this app but....
body: I really like this app for the simple fact that it shows you alternatives for the food that's not good for you and it's also shows you what the food is rated on a scale from A to D. Okay now the ONLY down fall is that it's doesn't have all the products on here that you'll looking for and very few of the information is incorrect if they make improvements it would make the app much better.

title: Amazing App
body: This app is incredible. I would highly recommend it to people who suffer from allergies. I have peanut and tree nut allergies. This is the first weight loss/diet app that keeps me aware and up to date on these allergies.  Yes I had to pay for the added allergy feature but it's already worth every penny. It will seriously decrease the amount of time I'm spending at the grocery store reading labels.

title: Please fix the crashing on notifications...also we need an iPad version of the app üôÑ
