body: I mean seriously people it's the digital age üòÇ when I'm not on my iPhone, I'm on my iPad. The stretching of the iPhone app just isn't working for me üòÇ please developers, develop an iPad version üò≠. Also a major problem with the current version of the app is it keeps crashing while trying to access notifications üò≠üò≠üò≠ please fix these things and this app would be a definite 5 star rating üëç

title: Very Nice!
body: My wife and I have been trying to eat better and this app is the ticket for finding alternative food items that are a healthier choice. The Fooducate team is very helpful if you need to ask a question. They will get right back to you promptly with an answer and an explanation. I will be looking forward to seeing the database grow to include more food items.

title: Very Useful and User Friendly App!
body: I've been using this app occasionally from time to time.      It gives a real good invaluable and impartial dietary review of packaged products.  It even provides alternatives to a product that you've scanned (competitors).

title: Very helpful !
body: This is a very  useful tool.  Our family has several people with allergies and health problems, this app. has helped me be aware of some of the hidden dangers that are in foods. I would like to see it expand, or have sister apps, that would help with ingredients that are found in cosmetics and hygiene products or have a app. that would help with the food in restaurants.  Great app. !

title: Review of Fooducate
body: I downloaded the app to see what it was all about. I was pleasantly surprised. It really helps you become more aware and conscious of the food you eat and the choices you make concerning nutrition. I installed it on two other phones and my friends are impressed. They use it almost everyday. Looking forward to database updates as more products are included.

title: Doesn't organize well
body: This app is great to really see if what you're ratings good for you or not but it fails to organize what you eat well. Normally breakfast lunch dinner snacks etc are separated but I find this to just have a long long list of what I ate. If I drank 8 cups of water it lists it individually created a king and unnecessary list.

title: Favorite App
body: I use this app every time I go grocery shopping! It's amazing the amount of food  I thought was healthy was in fact not. It gives you alternative healthier options to buy. Also, if you buy the premium version it will identify if an item is vegetarian or vegan! I highly recommend this app for anyone who is trying to live a healthier life style!

title: Love this app!
body: I use the app every single day and love it!  I like the flexibility of tracking calories, points, or carbs, getting a nutritional breakdown at the end of the day, and a graph of your progress on key metrics.  My only suggestions for improvement would be standardized calories and nutrition for whole foods. I'd also like some additional metrics or space to add my own, like body fat percentage.

title: Need major improvements
body: In the beginning I really liked this app, but over time I've found not to trust it as much. Just a couple of things I find VERY annoying are when inside any supper market I'm lucky if I can get to scan one item after that I always get the same Time Out error message ( which I have sent in but have not received any feedback on)

title: Busy working mother of 3, fitness enthusiast
body: This app does have its flaws but all in all I use it everyday for the great community of people with all one goal in mind. To be healthy. It's fun to talk to others and have health and fitness related discussions as well as discover new ideas of healthy meals from others. It's also has a great food scanning devise that tells you all about the food your putting in your body. Why it's good or bad.

title: Great way to live a healthy life!
body: I like to live my life not counting calories, but adding up all the fiber/protein/nutrients that I need to the day. I don't particularly need to lose weight, so I use this app as a way to choose healthy food options and keep record of the amount of natural nutrients/vitamins that are in the food I eat. I love that I can keep track of iron and calcium - the two that I am deficient in.

title: Love it!
body: This is an app that I have used every single time I have gone to the grocery store!!!! It has been a real eye opener for many foods that I thought were ok. I also love that it has "point values"! That has been extremely helpful! I have submitted a couple items that were not listed. I am very interested to see if these items will be listed at some point.

title: A great App
body: This app is awesome for all of its intuitive information, easy to use menu system and it's updatable library of info. Sync it to Facebook and teach your friends about what they eat and buy for their loves ones or kids. A must have app for any parent who has the time and money to really choose what's right for their kids. I'm even teaching my parents a couple things and getting them to buy better groceries.

title: Love this app!
body: I'm not very savvy on food ingredients, and this app really helps me discern between the good ingredients and the not-so-good ingredients. I love all the definitions of what the chemicals are and what they do in the food. It's starting to get a lot of users, so there's a wide variety of foods to get information on. The alternatives tab for finding better food options is great too! This is one of my fave apps.

title: I can't believe it doesn't cost more
body: I am considering upgrading to premium. The scanner is fast and addicting and I use. If your like me, you still buy some packaged foods and can't stand around in the grocery store reading every label and looking up every ingredient. This does the work for you and let's you learn later if you choose to do so.

title: Perfect For Anybody
body: I recommend the app to every one, it's Really nice and The Community on the App is surprisingly Active! You can track the food you eat and See how you have been doing with eating. It has a Fee for wanting to check other stuff like vitamins and other stuff but it's worth it! I don't have it because my Apple Account Pay doesn't work but if it did I would 100% Buy the monthly Prescription!

title: Learn your Body
body: Nutrition technology is rapidly developing, allowing us to learn more about what's happening inside our bodies than ever before.

title: One of the few apps I can't go without
body: I think most apps are generally unnecessary, but this is one I use almost  daily. Getting real facts about the food we eat is invaluable. We regularly use this app to explain basic healthy eating habits to our kids, and it adds a level of validity to our advice. I definitely recommend it.

title: Just what I needed
body: This is a wonderful app. It has all the elements I need to take control of my eating and my weight. Not only does it count calories and exercise throughout the day, It rates food from A to D so that I can tell if the food is a good choice. It also explains the rating and offers better choices. It has a robust community and many other features.

title: Healthy Decision Making
body: This app is not only good for losing weight. It also is great for taking to the store and helping you grocery shop. You'd be amazed the things that are marketed as healthy actually don't have a great grade. I love that I can let it calculate points or it can count my calories for me. Everyday they seem to be adding more and more to their database. This app will not disappoint.

title: Enlightening
body: This app has really educated me and opened my eyes to see what I am eating and feeding my family. I love the explanations of the grade. Very helpful in understanding the ingredients that are bad for you so you can look out for them in other places. One suggestion I would make is a "where to buy" feature for the top graded products or alternative products listed.

title: This app is awesome!
body: Wow! It's super easy to use, and it gives you such great info! I try to read the ingredient lists, but it gets very confusing and frustrating at times. This app makes it so simple to stay on top of what's really in the foods that we buy. This is a great tool especially since I have kids and I want to know what I am giving them!! Thank you for this free app!

title: Informative, a bit scary
body: A friend recommended this app but never really used it.  We went through her pantry scanning items and were surprised by the information provided.  I had no idea how much sugar and preservatives were in foods.  I continue to use it to help me make better decisions.  My most surprising scan: frozen fruit bars, even the 'good' ones have +5 teaspoons of sugar!

title: Educational, fun, and about food!
body: What could be better?! Kidding aside, I think this I a great app. I wish the information supplied by this app was more sought after by our nutritionally imbalanced population. The app contains lots of nutrition info, articles, and suggestions for more nutritional options.  Super easy to photo and submit, if the product you scanned isn't their database. Thanks for a useful app.

title: Amazing
body: We love this app because it makes it so much easier to make informed choices even while you shop. And it helps sift through all the marketing that promises a great product and helps you find the one that truly delivers. Great way to put the power back into the hands of the consumer. Thank you for making this app available for all people!

title: Good info but not well integrated
body: I like this app. It helps to quickly scan for numbers (sodium content) and ingredients I might miss.  However it feels like there are two sets of info by different authors. I've found multiple products with grades of A- or B -- pretty good of any scale -- but that when you read the description of the ingredients a clear recommendation is made to 'put it back'. If that rec is there, shouldn't the grade be lower?

title: Almost amazing...
body: I heard about this app from The Splendid Table and downloaded it. When I explored it at home, I was so excited to try it out in the real world. Unfortunately for my sad iPod touch, this app 1. Makes those without fancy phones manually add the barcode and 2. Requires the 15 of us who don't use their non-apple phone for Internet to have Internet to use fully while at the store. I'm disappointed I can only use this app at wifi equipped stores or at home (which defeats the purpose...).

title: A must have app
body: Weather you're a health nut or not this app is a must. I was never a food advocate and just ate whatever my taste buds craved. With this app, fooducate defined ingredients and word it in a way where I can understand what I was really consuming. This made me rethink the things I eat for the better not only for myself but also for my family. Easy to use app as well!! Thank you fooducate!!

title: Clear, quick food evaluator
body: I know the details are important, but the quick grading this app provides really helps speed up shopping when you must navigate a supermarket because the local co-op is closed.  It even helped reduce snack arguments with my son. Scanned some puffs, shows a D-. Pretty clear to everyone. I didn't say a word, he put it back on the shelf.

title: Wow! What an amazing app! They have everything!
body: I am in awe of the people who developed this app. Amazing! You found every food item and analyzed it. I think I'm pretty savvy when it comes to suspicious ingredients but food companies have gotten so sneaky that anyone can be fooled. And who can everyday people rely on to tell them what's good and what's not? This app is it! Thank you thank you thank you!!

title: Very limited database of foods
body: While the app has the capability to provide a lot of information, it falls short due to the very limited and frequently inaccurate database.  For example, a boiled egg has anywhere from 0-160 calories. The location feature is great. But the grading system is far more subjective than objective. The articles are simply a facade for advertising which I thought my $9.99 got rid of. The biggest real pet peeve I have is that the predictive spelling is disabled. If the developers can get the database up to par with my fitness pal and get rid of all advertising, I'll gladly give them more stars.

title: Totally user friendly
body: Fooducate is an extraordinary app that not only allows you to make educated decisions on food choices, but offers alternatives to your favorites. The interactivity is one of my favorite features. Compare your food favs to other products, help the app grow by simply sending in a photo by email, and even enter to win prizes while doing so. Definitely 5 stars.

Love this app. Was looking for a food tracker, I like the scanning capabilities and that they provide healthier alternatives. Also TONS of information about your foods if you want to dig in and read about ingredients, preservatives, Gmo etc. I'm a big fan. Hard to use when going out for a meal because it pretty much only works if you itemize the ingredients. But the educational material is really great!

title: A must have app!!!
body: using this app, I have learned so much about what I am eating.  The information is so easy to understand and the way the app is built u get basic information instantly upon scanning a product and then u can dive down more layers to get as much info as you want.  If I could only have 5 apps on my phone this would be one of them!

title: Pretty good
body: What I like about this app is that it gives you alternative foods to eat instead of the usual junk. It keep tracks of calories, "food points", and all foods are graded. I would give it 5 stars if it had accurate information. Some of the foods that I've tracked are off by 30-40 calories, and for those of us that are trying to lose weight every calorie counts. But overall it's a decent app.

title: Best food app!
body: This is the best app I have ever had. I have not dropped a penny on any in app purchases but I paid $10 for this one back in January, best $10 I've ever spent! Everyone that knows me knows fooducate. It's really a great wholesome app that is all about your nutrition rather than your dollar. I would probably cry if they got rid of it. I'm a little too dependent. And I'm okay with that.

title: Useful app
body: I've used this app from the beginning when it was just a free app. When the premium became available I got that right away. Currently I'm tracking my food intake for cholesterol purposes. My health coach wants numbers that I can easily give her. üòä all I have to do is enter what I consume. Thanks so much for such a great app!

title: For the most part super accurate
body: I was going to give it a 4 but I decided to give it a 5 because it really does educate. For someone who really needs to lose weight, it shows you cannot touch anything that's processed which is the goal! There have been slight errors but always corrected when I look back.

title: Amazing app
body: I absolutely love this app. I love that I can compare products in the store by scanning their barcodes to see their health grade. I also love that it gives me alternative products that may be healthier for me. It explains why the product is graded as it is and it also gives me the diet points for each serving which is truly helpful for those of us counting them.

title: Awesome and easy to use!
body: I love this app! Whether you're trying to lose weight or just eat healthier, you'll find a TON of helpful info in here. The tracking is super fast and easy to use as well. There have been products I've had to add (mostly local food store's items), and the support team is lightning fast at adding them in for me! Love this app!!

title: Very Helpful
body: I have been trying to loose some weight for the summer and this is the perfect app to track it. Unlike some people, I really like to track my calories; this app makes that really easy. Its interface is easy to use also! I would highly suggest this to anyone who either wants to lose weight or just eat healthier!

title: Good if you have an iPhone
body: I have an iPod touch 4g and the scan functionality just does not work. No matter how steady or how much light or how close/far away I am, it won't read the barcode. Thus I have to manually put in the numbers. This is because the iPod camera isn't auto focus capable. Still, the information given is great and recommend the app

title: Great
body: I just purchased my iPhone and just got this app but for now not looking what else is out there I do love this App I think it is a must for u who want to eat good . I usually always read labels but using this app speeds that process up a lot. Plus the comparing items feature is great. I would recommend this app for everyone... Thank I will add more after I use this more !!! An A+++

title: Fooducate
body: Love this app! It's fast, easy and direct. And if it doesn't recognize a product, it gives you the option of adding it which took less than 1 minute. Once i submitted the pictures, based on the picture I took of the ingredients, it gave me a rating even though the product wasn't in the system yet. Awesome for health conscious people.

title: Interesting!
body: I enjoy using this app. It has helped me make a few positive diet choices. I really appreciate that it not only scores food but gives reasons. I have also been impressed with the extensive database for products, it is rare that I find something not scored.  Only down-side is the fact that so many products are just not very good for us.

title: Great App Overall
body: This is a great app to help you make better eating choices. Easy to use too I like it and so far, this is the only diet/exercise app I use daily. I just wish the activity section had more depth to it exercise-wise ( i train martial arts and there is no choice to put that in)but for this app being free, that's a minor complaint. Everything else is spot on.  Great app!

title: The most important app if you care about what you put inside
body: I know it sounds cliche, but this app could change what you eat and therefore your life. It makes you aware what are you putting inside you and gives you better alternatives. It motivates me to eat right. There are so much more to this app .... I use it many times throughout a day. Get it!

title: Wonderful App
body: I love this app. I tend to have a narrow shopping list so many items are repeats that I have scanned and decided upon based on Fooducate's input. Whenever I am looking for something different or a special is offered , out comes the app to check it out. Also at home I sometimes scan items as we unpack the groceries if I was not the shopper.

title: Fooducate
body: I really like this app!! The app lets you program your food in and lets you pick the serving size, unlike other apps were it does it for you incorrectly. There is a wide selection of exersices that you can choose!

title: Awesome
body: This app is great! When you have something that is not in the system you can take pictures and write to the company and they get it on there for you. This has really helped me keep track and be responsible for what I eat. Way cheaper then other programs with monthly fee's. the best part it remind you to track. I love love love that part!

title: Amazing!!!
body: I am so thankful for this app. It is the greatest. It makes my life easier when trying to shop for healthy food. It is easy to use and I like how it gives you alternative choices to not so healthy products. This has literally been what I been looking for in an app. My son actually introduced me to it. I am hooked on it. I can't be without it!!!

title: Very helpful and awesome
body: Wow! This app is amazing. I couldn't wait to start scanning items in my pantry. Very detailed.  The great thing is that if you have an item that they don't have on the database all you have to to is take the pictures and email it straight from the app. You get a reply quickly about the item. I'm telling all my friends about it. Awesome that it's free too!!!!! Love it.

title: Changed the way we eat!
body: Awesome! This made going to the grocery store with my 9 yr old a blast. He scans everything he likes and tries to avoid foods with a grade lower than a "C", by his own choice! It's makes eating healthy fun, educational, and easier. This app has had a healthier benefit to my family than any other app we've downloaded (out of over 200 apps we use!)

title: Cool
body: It is a cool app that does what it says it does. It is fun scanning things in the store. I've even been surprised at the fact the it had some more obscure items documented. This is especially good for someone just starting out trying to eat healthy because in most cases it identifies "fake" healthy food- which may be alluring to people starting to pick healthier options.

title: Good an useful app.
body: I like this app, but when I'm standing in the grocery store trying to use it I sometimes feel a little overwhelmed. I try to make healthy choices but it's a bit time consuming to scan items before you buy them and even at home it makes me a little crazy because I never seem to pick the most healthy option. It's good but it takes a long time to use.

title: I love this app!
body: I give it a 4 & 1/2 stars but I'll label this 5 stars simply because its a leader! Its designed in informing the consumer. Sign in and approve the option to inform you of Genetically Modified Products and your on your way to informative decisions. It's unbiased in its strict detail on products giving you the power live a more productive lifestyle. It's keeps a history of your scans too! Awesome app!

title: Very helpful!
body: This app is very helpful in making the right food choices. It tells you all the nutrition facts, as well as the positive and negative ingredients in each product. The only thing I didn't like about this app is that it did not have a few products I scanned. But for the most part, they have a majority of all the food listed.

title: Good nutritional info
body: The scan aspect of the app is really effective and helpful for grading the healthiness of a particular food or drink. However, there are limited options when typing in an item to log and it doesn't allow you to customize your portion very well so it ends up being under or over what you actually consumed. Hopefully they'll work out those kinks with an updated version. Definitely great to use at the grocery store though!

title: I want to love this app again...
body: It worked great when it first came out but after an update the scanner would freeze my phone---in the middle of the grocery store so I couldn't use other apps for my grocery list and coupons! Frustrating! I don't even know what features are new, now only available if you upgrade or whatever, because I never use it...I'm afraid to! I still like to read fooducate articles on Facebook though.

title: Just try it!
body: If you want to eat healthier or at least find out what you are eating try this app.

title: Much better than my fitness pal!
body: I love that you can just scan the actual product you are eating and don't have to worry about searching for it! I pay for the extras and I love it! It helps to know exactly how much of everything I'm eating and I've lost 19 pounds in 2 months! Yay! Although I do wish there was a burn activity for core workouts or crunches.

title: Love this!
body: While shopping, labels can get confusing, reading 3 different brands, comparing each to find out which really has the lowest fat, salt and carb count. (as they all claim) With this app, I either scan quickly for the rating or choose the best one under the "popular" tab, then move on. It's made my trips so much quicker and less frustrating!

title: Great app
body: I just started using it.  I like that it educates users about harmful additives in processed foods.  I also like that it suggests alternatives, so people can contemplate making healthy changes or look for those food in their supermarket.  I don't agree with some of the ratings for the fresh produce.  They rate organic produce higher, but it comes wrapped in plastic.  I always try to buy fresh and local and often go to farmers markets for the freshest produce.

title: Love it !!.
body: Love this app, very helpful in my diet. I'm kind of a data junky and the amount of data that this app provides and tracks is just the thing to keep me on track.  I've lost 5lbs already just by having the ability to make better choices. All it takes is a quick consult of the app and I'm on my way to better health. Love this thing !!!!.

title: Excellent app!
body: I really like this application. I was looking for something to help me make healthier diet choices versus just a calorie counter. I have learned so much from this app. I now consume many more tomatoes and tuna, I stay away from processes sandwich meat and certain breads. I always thought that I was eating healthy! Little did I know... This app has made a world of difference for me.

title: Great app- with a few flaws
body: The app overall is extremely useful, but I sometimes find it hard to figure out why some foods are rated the way they are. The milk I drink is rated C+, although it is organic and lowfat. I'd like to be provided with more insight into the food grading process. Also, the place to enter your age has major flaws. Many months are gray and unable to be selected, as well as any year before 1995. Please fix.

title: Food Search -You'll be there all day!
body: THIS APP IS A WASTE OF MONEY AND TIME!!! SAVE YOUR MONEY!! USE MY FITNESS PRO!!! While the graphics are pretty and it might be a tad more user friendly with the interface. This horrible app has a horrible search feature. Type in "steak" and every processed food shows up. I emailed with Lisa at Contact Us but she could not answer the simple question...Is the search feature going to be up graded..instead she gave me a list of commands to follow to get to STEAK. No I don't want steakums and every other processed food with the word steak. Save your money and use My Fitness Pro. I am going back there.

title: Excellent
body: I love this app. Easy to use, accurate, recognizes 85% of the foods I scan. The information is well presented, consistent and accurate. It supplies Weight Watcher points which really helps to stay on track and even tells you why the product earned it's rating, offers alternatives and other nutritional information. Try it. You'll love it

title: Fantastic app
body: I was looking for an app that would help me eat healthy and pick the right foods and I came across this one. I love being able to scan an item and get the nutritional info right away and keep on track with the food grading and carb, fat, and protein counts. I'm losing weight the right way with healthy eating and exercise. Just love, love, love it

title: Food grades are a nice feature.
body: I've only been using it for a week, but I'd recommend it over my fitness pal. On the basis that it gives you advice on your food options and it lets you know if there are better options when you add foods to your health tracker. I use the food grading feature multiple times a day.

title: Couldn't shop without it.
body: I know it sounds crazy but I spent 30 minutes in the grocery store one time comparing different peanut butters. Had I known about this app it would've taken about 30 seconds. I wouldn't and couldn't grocery shop without it now. I and my girl friend use it every time we grocery shop!

title: You better watch what you're eating Fooducate is in town
body: I am so in love with this app, they have changed the way  I eat and buy food. They are honest and get straight to the point. I tend to watch what I eat if thier is an expert out there telling me the good and the bad. Last but not least their customer service is the best, the reply to your emails and your requests. Thanks Fooducate.

title: The BEST!
body: This is one of favorite apps for nutrition information EVER! It's so much fun to scan when shopping - it really helps you make better decisions. (found out one of my favorites is rated a "C" - NOT good!) I scanned one item & it wasn't in their data base so the app asked me to scan the front of package, nutrition label, & ingredients. Then they sent me an email telling me they would add it asap. How cool is that?? LOVE it!!

title: Great app. Needed app!!
body: I have been using this app also to search products,  but a few Pictues show different products than what was searched for. For example,  Blue Bunny orangecicle bars show a big screen tv!!  And another blue bunny product shows Kirby product. Not foods,  looks like someone got some lines crossed!  Otherwise it is  perfect app for me. Love knowing what Not and what To eat. I

title: Awesome and so useful
body: I actually have pulled this app up while in the grocery store to check the healthiness of certain foods. It's really useful and provides nicely presented and nicely organized info. which isn't a bore to read. Even though some products aren't listed, a VERY good amount is. Plus I love that healthier suggestions are often listed! :) very handy.

title: Love this app
body: This is an unbelievable healthy & helpful app. I've only begun to use it, but I've already changed the tea I drink to one healthier for me. I also learned some very useful information about other foods like honey. Get this one and use it, you won't regret it, in fact this is one you'll want to share with family and friends so you can be their hero.

title: A must have to anyone wking out or whom has a family!
body: This app is simply amazing.

title: So helpful! I love it!
body: This app is so cool!

title: Amazing for the health conscious!
body: I have always read food labels and paid attention to ingredients and now fooducate has an extensive database that does that for me! Also since I started using it less than 2 weeks ago, they had added 3 foods that weren't in their database and analyzed them for me in a matters of 48 hours. Talk about an amazing idea and amazing execution. Bravo!!!!!!

title: Amazing!
body: Love this app!  Never realized how bad for you some things are that are labeled "low fat" or healthy.  One feature I really find helpful is how I can input my goals and when I scan a product it will tell me if the product falls in line with that goal. U also like the reminder it sends my phone using GPS when I am at the grocery!

title: Use it almost everyday!
body: I love this app and can't feel complete going to the grocery store without it! I love that it tracks GMO's now, although having to pay for it's a bummer. It's just missing one star because it'll rate things lower for having a higher food points value even when it's because of "good fats". It would be helpful if it pointed out and taught about the differences in the fats

title: Great for everyone
body: Everyone should have this app. I have a very extensive library of food knowledge, and yet this program is always teaching me lots of small things that overall help me make better decisions. Instant product contrast has never been available like this without years of tried experience. Who needs a mentor now?

title: Great app!
body: So far this app appears to be everything I had hoped it would be, which is something I can rarely say about apps. I'm a lifelong health nut and reliable information is very hard to find, especially when you're at the grocery store. Fooducate is well-designed, well-implemented, easy to use, and appears to be well-documented. Here's to your health!

title: Should be a Top 5 App!!
body: This app is amazing. Not only is it easy to use but it's educational! I'm trying to be more healthy so when I'm in the store and want to buy something, I use this app to see how it rates. If I don't like the rating, it also gives me healthier alternatives to the food I'm choosing. Everyone should download this app. One of the best Free Apps I've downloaded.

title: A great app for vegans
body: I'm rating it a 4 because it doesn't ALWAYS have the food that you scan into it, but its getting more and more everyday from people that input the product. It's a great app for long time vegans and new ones because it will tell you clearly if the product is vegan, not vegan or seems to be vegan from looking at the ingredients. Also great for allergies and watching one's weight. A great app for a great price!

title: So great!
body: This app is awesome, the scanning feature is a great way to quickly add the food you ate instead of scrolling through all the similar products to find your exact brand. It is also so easy to add a product if they don't have it in the system yet and they are quick about putting it in! My new favorite app!

title: The best!
body: This is definitely the best calorie tracker I have ever used. Not only does this app count your calories and give you your recommended intake for your goals, but it also rates your food and provides better choices. Amazing! I've used this for about 4 months and it has helped me lose 20 lbs! The healthy way I might add!!

title: Weight Watchers Clean Eatinf
body: I wanted to do weight watchers with a focus on clean eating. Although Fooducate doesn't have a connection with weight watchers, they use "food points" which happen to correspond with weight watchers points. This app makes it very easy to see how processed foods are and gives alternatives. It is easy to use and the displays are attractive.  Love this app!!!

title: Best App Ever!!
body: I use this App several times daily.  I am very Gluten intolerant & it has been so useful to help me avoid Gluten in any foods I eat. I love using at the Grocery when shopping to shop wisely to avoid certain foods.

title: Awesome app
body: Great for beginners, intermediate, and advanced people in the nutrition field. Though there may be some if's, I always get asked at the super market what I am doing by other shoppers, then explain to them how amazing this app is, and they go to download it. In short, if this app was $4.99 I would buy it. Only comment would be make a cleaner, simpler user interface.

title: Amazing
body: It's a great app dedicated to people usually you find apps mainly looking for money and not caring much about the users. This app isn't that way. They do have a premium but it's nothing that you have to or would feel obligated to buy. Only if your all that more into dieting then it'll be something you actually want to buy.

title: What a fantastic little app!
body: This app is tops when it comes to determining the healthiness of a food product! I love being able to see 'alternatives' to what I scanned, and see the grade range on the type of product, so I know whether it is healthy overall or just within it's class. This can help keep you on track to a healthier lifestyle!

title: Good Stuff!
body: This is a great app! If u want to know more about what your eating and what's really inside your food, then this app's for you! Ex. Tells u if what your eating is truly "whole wheat" you'll be surprised to know that a lot of products that claim to be 100% whole wheat are not! What's even better is that u get alternatives to that food that are what they say they are! ;)

title: It's very useful!!
body: I find fuducate to be in line with everything I've studied and learned. I have also picked up a few things from it and it's very convenient to use. I use it everywhere I go. I'm also very active in sending them new information and additional information in updating their data base. Keep up the great work Fooducate!

title: A real eye opener
body: Excellent app that helps you find information on food quickly! The letter grading system and useful information make it easy to see the truth about products that claim to be healthy! My kitchen may have less food now because of this app but it will be replenished with food that is better for my family.

title: Helped me!!!
body: I have been battling my weight and no matter how many books I read my biggest challenge was what to buy and prepare for food. This app has allowed me to easily evaluate and compare the foods in the grocery store. I actually have hope that I can change my lifestyle and eat healthier. I can never thank you enough.

title: Lifesaver for people with Allergies or Intolerances!!!!
body: Everyone should know what they are eating and feeding they're family! This app is a lifesaver for me! It's spot on with glutamate free/MSG info which is why they won't rate anything an A+. Unless you grow it yourself... You truly can't be sure what's in your food or how your body will react to it. At least that's how it is for me with Ulcerative Colitis. Love this app and the blogs!!!

title: Great app missing just a few things
body: Awesome app , I love it and use it daly to check out the foods I consume and how healthy they really are . Only 1 downfall and me being picky is that on the self health tracker I would recommend adding the amount of fats and sodium and such you consume rather than overall calories and carbs ! But would recommend this to anyone starting or even expert people in fitness to check out !

title: Fabulous!
body: I really love this app because it not only tells you a letter grade for your food, it gives you alternatives as well. It's super easy to scan bar codes in!

title: Easy to use! Quick response by Development Team
body: I have never been one to keep track of calories, but after my Beachbody coach challenged me I new that I needed an app that would be very easy to use. Well, I found it with this! This will be a 5 star app after some tweaks and adjustments for sure. The devo team here has been quick to respond on several occasions I sent info in to them. Thanks!

title: Healthy Motivator at your fingertips
body: I love this app... The best part is that it counts your calories for you when you scan the barcodes of the foods you eat:)

title: Very Cool
body: This would be a five star review if foods had a glycemic index. I have used this many times at the market since I downloaded...people give me a pleasant, curious look when I'm scanning away. Knowledge is power with food! I've learned that "healthy" looking packaging may be deceiving. Definitely eating more whole foods as a result of this App. Let's face it, good health is priceless & proper nutrition is essential...step away from the junk food people !!ÓÅñ

title: Just a guy making changes to get healthy
body: Great tool, but to really utilize it for the great tool it is, you really have to use it regularly. I don't agree with some of the grades, but they are close enough that I consider it more of a help than a hindrance. I highly recommend it for those that are serious about making a lifestyle change.

title: I never shop without it!
body: This app is absolutely fantastic! I lead a very healthy lifestyle with lots of exercise and healthy eating but still I was eating things that I didn't know were bad or even illegal in other countries. Thanks to this app now I know! Even my husband got it on his phone and he usually isn't into scanning and measuring food.

title: Amazing app!
body: I installed this app over a week ago because I decided to live a healthier lifestyle. I scanned nearly everything in my kitchen & found some disappointing foods that I thought were quite healthy. Overall, very informative & extremely useful for those of us who care what we put in our body.

title: A+ app
body: My kids love using this app to grade their food! It helps them to know better what foods are good for them! We had a great time grading all the food in our house! We had mostly B- some C foods so now they are on a mission to chose only A's and B's!! What a fun and fantastic way to teach kids how to eat better!! Thank u for creating such an easy and wonderful tool!

title: Fooducate
body: I didn't know about this app until I saw my daughter playing around with almost all my pantry's products and she started to explain and now I got extremely worried about food containing GMOs, trans fat, too much sodium and too much sugar and food dyes. Now I don't buy a single product without using this app. It truly is amazing. I do recommend this!

title: Fantastic, but....
body: This would be beyond fantastic IF the site was up all the time. While frustrating to try and enter a food not yet in the data base , that is to be expected. What is frustrating and NOT expected is finding the site "busy" most of the time and thus finding it hard to enter foods and exercise. Bigger server please...

title: Love!!!
body: I love this app! I depend on this app while grocery shopping and it has allowed me to make better food choices. The only complain is, sometimes they don't have products listed.. Like when I'm

title: Using the scanner to make choices at the grocery store is my favorite feature.
body: This app has exceeded our expectations. I downloaded it so that I could find out the level of added sugar in processed and other foods. It's done that in spades. I'm now recommending this app to most of my patients and have also to many of my friends.

title: Amazing app, everyone should use it!
body: I've used the website forever; the app is super helpful since you can scan the products' barcodes and get all the info you need.

title: Fun and Enlightening
body: This is such a nifty little app! It is very entertaining and informative. Foods I thought were good have too many additives and I am pleasantly surprised how nutritious other foods are that I used to not consider. It is helping my family make wiser choices at the grocery store. My wife and I scanned almost our entire pantry. I highly recommend this. Darn, my Cheezits ranked a C, but Cashews got a B+

title: New favorite app
body: I've had an iPhone since they came our and this is the first review I've written. Great app and definitely something I will use (instead of download and forget like many other apps). Gave 4 instead of 5 stars because sometimes the comparisons see a little inconsistent on which product is "better". If you read food labels (or want to start), download this app now.

title: No Freshman 15 for Me!
body: Fooducate is a great app to help you make better food choices in a split second. Being able to simply scan a barcode and immediately viewing the pros and cons of the food is both educational and helpful for everyday use and for future reference. This app is helping me to stay healthy while in college!

title: Could be just a little better‚Ä¶
body: The app is quick, provides great info, and I like the fact that I can see my list of favorites.  It would be even better if there was a shopping list integrated, or better still, a way to view things / export on a website.  I'd be willing to pay for those extra features.

title: Awesome!
body: I <3 Fooducate!  However I wonder about their ratings. A regular Coke rates a D or D-, when I'd give it a F. I'd also like to see it offer a recommended replacement product (I use it in the grocery store and have to scan multiple products to find the best product). Overall a great resource and I look forward to the coming upgrades and improvements.

title: Too good to be true
body: This is an app I always wish existed but never thought it would be possible to build. It recognizes every single food I scan, tells me everything about it, gives it a grade and tells me why it got the grade. I don't know how in the world it they did it, but I'm really glad someone did! I don't eat without it.

title: It's amazing...
body: ...how many controversial additives are in our food. Packaging is just another form of marketing and doesn't give you an accurate description of what you're eating. Fooducate details the positives and negatives along with suggestions for better alternatives. This app changed the wag I eat and look at food. Paired with my fitness pal it's a great weight loss tool.

title: No option for weight gain
body: I need to gain weight. I have a hard time rendering to eat and an even harder time making sure I eat enough. I travel a lot and my schedule is intensely hectic so I need to eat whatever is available. I really wanted to use this app because it seems like it would provide great information for my lifestyle, but there was, sadly, no option for setting a goal weight higher than my current weight. Hopefully they can add that option so everyone can use it!

title: Best health app I've used!
body: This app is better than any other health app I've used. It is thorough, accurate and very helpful. I've yet to have any issues and love all of the features you can choose from. If you are looking to really focus on your health, for whatever reason is unique to you, then I'd suggest this app over the others!

title: Great App, would like to see some changes
body: I really like this app, nothing negative to say about it.  What i would like is a different dashboard where I can update my weight and other metrics just as easily as entering food/daily diet instead of having to go through the side bar options. Outside of that, great app again!

title: Could revolutionize your shopping trips for groceries
body: I find myself comparing EVERYTHING now with this simple, easy-to-scan tool in my hand. Sure, you can compare items by putting them side by side and reading the labels back and forth. . .but this tool makes it much faster and easier. And the price is perfect!

title: Nutritional info, additives, etc
body: I love the information added-- although most parts are generalized (if it has a specific artificial sweetener then the info given will be about artificial sweeteners in general). I love the alternatives, I like how i learned that food I once thought was junk food turned out to be healthy (popcorn) and drinks I thought was healthy was not (chocolate soy).

title: Fasted & Best App for Food Ratings
body: This app is great.  I have taken it to Costco on several occasions and it identifies all scanned items.   My favorite part is the grading system it sets for the particular food you just scanned.   Of course, there is more information in the app about the food you just scanned.

title: Male 55 yrs.
body: This App is Great!

title: Read this review & install this app :-)
body: Fooducate is everything I need to make better food buying decisions for myself and my family. I prefer to eat natural/organic proteins and whole organic fruit and veggies, but when making choices between processed food options - the fooducate app is a great tool to help select the lesser of the evils among processed foods. Enjoy!

title: Helps control my carb intake!!
body: This is a great app that's really easy to use.  I like how you can monitor your calories or food points and also check your carb intake for the day. You don't have to worry about segregating breakfast, lunch or dinner which was always kind of a nuisance for me.  Also the options of better selections is great!!! I've had this app for almost a week and have gone down almost a belt loop!  Yay!!!!

title: Bad since update :(
body: I used to live this app but it does not work since I upgraded. For example, it constantly errors out due to no network/cellular connection but BOTH are available and I confirmed my settings are correct (not having problem with any other app). This alone makes it virtually unusable. Further the scanner doesn't work properly since I downloaded the newest version . Sooo disappointing esp because I wanted to get a premium account... Now I'm afraid to pay of the app is NOT GOING TO WORK.

title: I can do it! With help from Fooducate.
body: Great app! It's an easy way to do something I never wanted to do before...track calories. I like having the 12 month premium version because I can track so many other things like fiber and protein intake. Love that I can input my energy expenditures too, be it exercise in a gym or cleaning house. Thanks, Fooducate! I'm excited to see my progress a month from now.

title: Very good but.....
body: As others have said, it needs a larger database, it often doesn't recognize food she's scan. My other problem with this app is that it is not at all intuitive, you can use it for weeks and still have difficulty finding your way around and all the various features. That said, it has a lot of pluses, hence the four star rating.

title: AMAZING
body: Love love love this app. I take this to the store and scan things as I go. I really feel like I  learning something new about how to eat healthier all the time. Enjoy the emails they send as well. I plan to upgrade but there is so much even if you don't upgrade. Certainly worth downloading this app.  To whomever made this app. Thank you so much!!!

title: AMAZING !! HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT !!
body: I just installed this today and made use of it at two different stores. It was INCREDIBLY fast to scan on my iPhone 4 and 100% accurate on everything I tried it on. Even STORE brands were INSTANTLY recognized and graded.  This type of APP makes owning a SMART phone worthwhile,  It now lives on my home screen and I plan to use it whenever I shop. AND IT'S FREE !!!!

title: Top Notch even if it was a paid app
body: I'm actually surprised this app is free (at least currently). It works nearly flawlessly (have had minor issues scanning in low light) and i'm impressed with the depth of the database. Keep up the great work and I will definitely spread the word on this one, it's important enough to move to page 1 of my apps.

title: Awesome
body: My favorite app yet!  I have made much wiser food choices using this, especially for my kids.  Amazing how many chemicals and how much trans fat is in our food.  I have people ask me what I am scanning at the store and once I show them, they immediately want this app too!  They have a huge list of products and the scanner works perfectly!

title: Keeps getting better
body: A good app overall. I wish that it would factor in if something is organic as part of the rating. Also wish there was faster turn around about products whose information you send in to find out about. But it's excellent and I use it every time I hit up the grocery store.

title: 100% necessary at the store!
body: I never shop without this. The ingredients lists these days read like science experiments! This app helps to understand the basics of nutrition and untangles the advertising mumbo jumbo so that consumers can make healthy decisions. Sometimes it's horrifying to see what is really in a product but I'd always rather know if I'm buying a chemical nightmare. Thanks Fooducate!!

title: Time saver
body: This makes life so much easier. In this journey to becoming healthy counting and keeping track of calories isn't easy. If I had to use pen and paper I dont think I would; I actually think I would give up. This is the best tool for keeping track. I know there are others like this but I'm stuck on this one!!!!

title: Love this app.
body: Especially while shopping, because it gives you better alternatives when scanning an item...thank you for this...

title: Great little app!
body: I really like this app! I've been using it for a couple weeks and have already lost a few pounds! I wish more restaurant foods and foods in general were added in; some days 60% of my intake is unknown. But overall it's a great app to use if you're trying to lose weight or just eat healthier. I recommend it!

title: Nathalie
body: This is a great app for counting your calories and keep a food log and knowing exactly what your eating. It even allows you to scan the barcodes on food packaging and tells you everything you need to know about that product. It even gives you info on fast food and restaurants. It's great!

title: Very good
body: Easy to use and a lot of fun features. Only thing that I would improve would be having the daily tracker be the home screen when you log in instead of going to the menu every time as clearly it is the most often used of the choices.

title: Best App Ever!!!
body: I absolutely love this app! Especially because it explains the way different ingredients affect your body, healthwise. This, then, enables you to see why you should make healthier choices of food. And, it puts healthier choices right there for you. So excited about this & I hope many people will start using Fooducate & get healthier. I definitely rate it A+ or 5 Stars.

title: Why does the app say compatible when it's not?
body: After reading the description I finally found out why it wasn't working for my phone. The app itself does state that it works with IPhone 3G, but the app store states it does NOT. Kind of a bummer considering I don't want to manually input a 16 digit long number for info... This should be something that they make a littttttttle clearer. Good info overall just a major inconvenience for those of us who can't upgrade to the iPhone 8G or whatever it's at now. Maybe next year people will start dating them too.

title: Awesome... When it's working which is usually
body: This app is fantastic. You go shopping. You scan the lunchables. You realize it's full of stuff you'd never feed your kids. You put it back and fix the real deal. My only gripe is that occasionally it says it's not connected to Internet which is impossible because I have wifi and a data plan. But it usually works anyways.

title: Informative but slightly disappointing...
body: My aunt got this on her Droid and found it interesting, I downloaded it on my 3rd gen iPod Touch and started playing with it, but soon found that the "random" feature does not work on an iPod without a camera.  Which I don't really understand.  It's a great app if you have something specific in mind that you want to research, but if you are looking for aimless education, then this app is less than desirable.

title: Love it!
body: So happy you fixed the error message so fast! It's super fun to scan all of my household items. Its super simple to use too!  I love the daily tips section, it has some really interesting articles. I also like how it saves your past scans. Looks like I need to start eating wayyyy healthier but I'm glad this app will help me with that. Thanks for the great app!

title: Love this app
body: This app is an eye opener for me. I am learning that some of my favorite foods are not as healthy as I thought and by making simple changes I could live a healthier life. To those that say the app doesn't work- I rarely get that message and when I do it asks me to take a pic of the food do it can be added to the database. I love it. Cheers to eating better.

title: Impressive
body: This is exactly what I was always looking for. And since that whole "right to know" prop in California failed, this is exactly the perfect app to find out if products contain GMO's.

title: Fantastic app.
body: I love this app! It gives great information on what you're eating, alternatives, and the addition of the tracker is great!

title: Informative & eye opening app
body: It is amazing how much I purchase food based on food packaging & I will also look at the nutritional facts. Many items I thought were healthy are not or the amount of crap that is added to our food is crazy. Very informative app & it will help our family make wiser food choices.

title: Excellent, thorough, and helpful
body: This app has helped me keep track and summarize my daily caloric intake; additionally, and most importantly, it is constructive in its standard for quality food and has directed me away from food's I wouldn't have known were poor for my health. AND it's free. What. Thank you to those who put the time and effort behind this app.

title: Great App
body: Make educated choices about the foods that you eat... Surprising how many product labels

title: I Love it
body: I find this app so helpful.  It does make my trips to grocery store longer, but it is so cool to compare products side by side right there before buying. I love how it will give you a "better" choice for a product. Also it tells you why it gets the grade it gets like "processed" or" not whole grain".  I give the app A+

title: Great ap
body: I love many things about this ap,it tracks my daily calories, helps me set goals, and keeps track of food points so I can monitor what I take in.   I also like that it always burn counts and allows for exercise.   My only request would be that I would like a tally of my protein count as well.  Being a vegetarian I need a reminder of where I stand and would like a running tally.

title: Pretty good app
body: I really like the scan option on this app. It would be nice if you could view your nutrient chart any time instead of just at the end of the day. It would also be nice if the nutrient chart showed more of your nutritional intake...such as iron and all minerals, vitamins, calcium, fiber etc... The ability to add a product that the app doesn't have would also be a plus. Its the best one i have found although I haven't done much looking.

title: So helpful!
body: I love this app! After I set up my goals and preferences I had fun scanning everything in my house to see how items measured up. There were a few surprises and helpful explanations along the way to assist me in making healthier choices next time. I had my boyfriend get it, so he feels more confident picking up items at the store. Love it!

title: Ultimate Health App
body: Fooducate is the ULTIMATE health app. You don't need to follow any particular diet. Simply scan EVERYTHING edible in your house. Anything that scores less than a C/C+, THROW IT OUT! All the nutritional value is listed there for you and it even suggests better alternatives for those low scoring foods you like to eat. Plus, they post daily articles that are good reads for health and nutrition. AWESOME APP!!! DOWNLOAD!!!

title: I'm liking it so far!
body: After I broke my back, I had put on a good chunk of weight from not being as active as I was before. I wanted to see what all I was eating and this really puts it in front of you. I'm amazed how looks can be deceiving on portion size. It's nice to scan or write the ingredients in and it keeps a record of everything.

title: Free version good
body: Like it & using it for over a year. Scan bar codes, find popular restaurants and grocers from thousands of foods and meals. Or photograph and submit your own recipes to keep track of daily calories. Then see them melt when you include exercise or physical activity of any kind. Get health tips in daily newsletter. Paid version includes much more specific to individual.

title: Best food app ever!
body: Fooducate is simple and easy to use. The barcode scanner works and the database of foods is very large. Also if you need help in your dieting process and need some idea of foods to eat, you can look at the recipe section to get some ideas. Overall I love this app I already have began a healthy life style with my eating.

title: Educational and Useful
body: This is my second day using the app. So far I love it. It has handed me some surprises - and affected my snack and meal choices for the better. Sometimes I don't want to know everything about the ingredients in my snacks - or do I?  Now I am very interested. Love it - thank you to the creators. The barcode scanner works exceptionally well.

title: Great App! Very useful
body: This app gives our family a good idea on what is good, bad or better for us when it comes to eating. My 12 yr old daughter has fun using it while we're grocery shopping & I feel like its also teaching her about good food habits in general. I love the alternatives it gives you as well. One of my favorite apps!

title: No more guessing
body: It's so nice to no longer have to stand in the grocery store isle and try to figure out what is healthy. This app not only helps with that but also tells you if the foods marked "healthy" actually are. It also explains why or why not. I've been using it frequently since I downloaded it and really like it.

title: Very informative
body: I love to use this app when grocery shopping to get the better options even if I can't afford the majority of the  "A" graded products...so my only complaint is the grading system because I don't quite understand it. Other than that it's a great way to stay informed on what's in your favorite foods, why it's good or bad for you, and how to swap them out for healthier alternatives.

title: Needs a little help
body: I love this App, I try to use it consistently to track how/what I'm putting into my body. Suggestion when you go to scan an item (say cranberry juice) and it gets a low rating (c-d) maybe suggest other types of cranberry  juices with a higher rating (A-B). Also your food library needs work, all fast food restaurant items should be on there already?...this will be huge if you take the guess work out of it.

title: Great for Weight loss & maintaining
body: The points information that I get from this website is excellent. I can find things that r not on the Weight Watchers website. It is really well rounded with all foods good and bad. U need to know the good and the bad when u r trying to lose and maintain your weight. The only negative is it is sometimes hard to get the WW Points cause we do not count calories. Thank u Fooducate.

title: Me
body: I love this app! It's easy, hold me accountable and teaches me how to make healthier choices. BUT, best if all, it teaches my 11 year old son how to make healthier choices. Being graded every day is great for us. Who doesn't want to get an A. I've told all my closest family and friends about it, because we are what we eat, and I want them to be healthy!!

title: Awesomeness!!
body: I love this thing!  It was a real eye opener for me. Never realized how many calories I was actually consuming during the day. The feature I really like is what I call the calorie count down. Entering my food and seeing how many more calories I could still consume before hitting my daily goal, helped me lose 10 pounds in one minth.

title: Extremely Helpful
body: I don't typically rate apps but this one has worked better than all the other similar ones I've tried. Not only is it simple and easy to use, but also gives helpful information on why they give the rating for the food!

title: So helpful, I love it!
body: I never usually rate apps but I had to rate this one! It's so helpful. I love it. You can look up foods, or scan them. & you can also add your "quick calories" this has helped me a lot to figure out what's actually healthy and what's not. I go through the store and scan it before I buy it! Awesome !!!

title: Great app
body: I love to food grade and the healthier suggestions. It makes you look at what you can do better. Then you can track your exercise and they have so many options to choose from. If you want a high tech food journal this is perfect for you. I love it and have recommended it to many people.

title: Love it!
body: Does everything it promises!  It is so easy to find healthier alternatives to the food you normally eat.  I have already made a quick rule for my kids.  I told them we can't buy anything below a C, now there are no arguments when they don't get the junk food they want. We just scan it and they see the grade!

title: Great App!! Please fix camera for 5 stars
body: This app is very easy to use, informative, and addicting. Great job!

title: Most used
body: This is one of the most used apps on my phone.  East to use & a must have for anyone concerned about the health aspect of the food they eat. The added bonus is for anyone tracking point system diets the info for this is on here too without the extra cost for that feature.

title: Didn't know all the junk I was eating!!
body: The app is very eye opening! I considered a lot of the foods I ate to be healthy but found out I should really look past the "healthy for you labels" and see what is really in some stuff. I also like the healthier alternatives section! I just wish they listed where you could find them.

title: Facebook connection
body: I like the product, but I have one complaint. I signed in with my Facebook account and this app posted my scan of soup on my page. I checked,  And I had turned off the posting without my permission. It's not a big deal, but I don't necessarily want my friends to see my processed food choice. Now I can't get it off my page. Just a little annoyed.

title: Excellent, eye opening app!
body: I absolutely LOVE this app. It's unbelievably eye opening. My husband and I are generally fit and strictly eat home made, healthy meals M-F. That being said, I used this app the last time we went food shopping and could not get over how much crap was in items I usually keep stocked! Packaging can be so misleading! Highly recommend.

title: Fooducate Challenge
body: I'll be using this app for an entire month and sharing my experiences with others. So far I absolutely love it! It's so convenient and informative and some of the things I'm learning, although they may make my stomach turn, are going to leave a lasting impression on my diet! Amazing application! Definitely worth a download!

title: Awesome!!!
body: This app is very easy to use and so much better than keeping a food and exercise journal! I love that its customized to the specific user and tracks progress. I also received a VERY prompt response when contacting them with a question...I HIGHLY recommend this app! Really helps keep you on track for a healthy lifestyle!

title: Exceptional!
body: I love this app so much! I never write reviews, but this app is so great that I am writing one for it! It's perfect for anyone who wants to maintain a healthy lifestyle. Or lose a little weight like me! :) The scanning feature makes it so much easier to count calories and look at nutritional values! I recommend this app to anyone who wants to easily stay in shape! :D <3

title: Awesome app!
body: Only have been using it for a week and I have already lost two pounds. It takes the guesswork out of my food choices. I was surprised to learn some items I thought were healthy were actually bad.  I looooovvvvveeee the scan feature and the notification feature.

title: Healthy Food App
body: This is a great tool for finding out the skinny about the foods you are thinking of putting into your body. It offers "healthier" alternatives, some better than others. The grading system sometimes seems a bit arbitrary and the comparisons occasionally don't offer an equivalent alternative, but overall, it is a handy app to have in the grocery store aisles.

title: Amazing App
body: This is an amazing App.  I would love to see it progress as more and more foods & drinks are produced worldwide.  Very informative and educating.  I learn lot thru this app.  Keep up the great work & continue to grow.  And thanks to all individual contributors.  Though many international barcodes do not work / scan properly, what is available are very enlightening!  Thank you!

title: Fun & Easy to Use
body: I love this app! It's super easy to use and actually pretty fun to find healthier alternatives to the food you usually eat.

title: Great App
body: I find this easy to use and I am able to track my eating and exercise. As more foods are added this will be an even better healthy eating app. Also extremely helpful while shopping. Easy to scan products for nutrition value. I love this app and use it every day.

title: Great app to lose weight!
body: This app is inspirational, offers tips, community, informative, great food tracker w pics, track weight loss, provides break down of carbs, fat, protein, sugar...I've used the lose it app and my fitness pal and this one is fantastic, right up there w those or even better in my book!  Very impressed.

title: Amazing app, but would like offline mode
body: This app is perfect for calorie tracking to meet target goals, for the first time I'm actually able to keep count of what I'm eating every day. That being said, I'd really love to be able to add food from my recently added or user created folders when I'm offline

title: Really great app
body: I really like this app because it makes me so much more aware of what I eat. It allows me to track what I'm eating and learn how healthy it is and why. It's better than apps that just let you keep a diary because it tells you what's healthy and what's not based off way more things than just calories.

title: Truly impressive app
body: I have tried many food tracking apps and this one is by far the best.  I consider myself pretty knowledgeable about healthy eating, but the apps food rating system has led to make a few different choices.    The suggestions for alternatives to poorly rated foods is especially helpful.

title: Helpful and intuitive
body: I've used nearly every iteration of healthy eating app available and appreciate the depth of information I can get quickly and easily on this one. It's easy for me to track how I'm doing- get great ideas and recipes from the community and add recipes that I make on my own (including raw vegan). My only wish would be for suggested meal plans - yes, I can be that lazy.

title: Excellent!
body: While I dont use the app to track daily calories (choosing instead to focus on micro-rich nutrients) I regularly rely upon the Food Finder which, with few exceptions, accurately grades food products. I have also joined the Fooducate Community, which I absolutely love! Having tried other similar apps, I consider "Fooducate" to be best in class.

title: Fooducate- great application
body: Now you can know better what you are eating, and you will get surprised! You can find most of the products at the grocery store and get the nutrition score. For those who really care of what they are eating, it gives you healthier alternatives. There some products missing though, but you can help out by taking pics of the package and nutrional info.

title: Awesome app!
body: This is a very useful app.  I am seriously impressed with their current database of items and look forward to more being added! I also love the fact that new items can be sent through the app to be rated in the near future, quickly and easily with pics.

title: Really fun and informative
body: This app is super fun to use at the grocery store. I consider myself knowledgeable about healthy eating but I'm surprised at the grades sometimes, so I'm learning a lot. I wish there was a way for it to use your location to determine which stores are available to you so the suggested alternatives were more appropriate.

title: Great app with limitations
body: I do like this application, I have learned a lot about the food I like to eat and what I should be buying.. However, my town does not carry all of the "A-B" products and it's hard to buy the "better" food item you need. I wish there was a grocery store you could choose from so the app would know what products your store should only have.

title: Like it but needs usability improvements
body: I really like this app but it gets annoying when adding things to a list causes a prompt every time.

title: Transformative App!
body: This application has changed how I grocery shop. This is the first truly impressive app I have ever downloaded. I highly recommend it because it brings ingredients and nutritional content to your attention in a different way and helps you sift through all the mixed messages in current food packaging.

title: Pretty nice app
body: This app has a pretty complete list of reviewed products. I've been able to find a few things that aren't listed but I'm seeing that less now then when I originally downloaded this app a few weeks ago. It's a lot of fun to see what grade different products will get

title: Awesome!
body: Best app for nutrition and food education. Makes it so much easier to shop healthy and smart when there is a nutritional grade attached to your purchase. Amazed to have learned how many products that are advertised as nutritious and healthy, but were filled unhealthy ingredients and hidden sugar and sodium. This app will always be a staple in all my smartphones.

title: New user
body: Just getting started, but after spending about thirty minutes checking out this APP I think I'm going to get a lot of use out of it.

title: Best app to stay and eat healthy!
body: Everything you need to know about what you eat in one app!! So much information but all is easy and quick to use to eat and cook as healthy as you can. Love the 'alternative options' it shows so you don't have to seek out and find the best alternatives to what you already get.

title: Great idea
body: I love this app, it's very informative, I learned a lot in 1 week about the foods I thought were "better" than others. Only thing I would like to see is when I share on FaceBook, others would be able to see the information about the products! This is an app I use everyday!

title: Absolutely Terrific ÓÄéÓÄéÓÄéÓÄéÓÄé
body: Eat better using advice from dietitians. Food products have confusing ingredient lists and hyped health claims. This app demystifies all of that by using simple English, giving good & bad product highlights, and providing recommended alternatives. I didn't know the real truth about the food I was eating until I used this app.

title: Very Informative!!!!
body: I absolutely love this app, it's informative and makes making better and healthier food choices MUCH easier, especially while grocery shopping. I like that it offers alternatives to foods as well, and that it explains why a food is graded the way it is, may it be a bad grade or good grade. I can't believe it's free, highly recommend.

title: If you care about what you eat....
body: Then you definitely need this app!  I have learned so much about food, and especially I learn things I need to know BEFORE I buy it.  They have detailed information on most foods, and offer a way to submit information on foods when they don't yet have a listing. This one is indispensable!

title: Love this app!!!
body: This app, with its scanner, ingredient info, and ease of use, has helped me to see exactly what I eat, what's in it, and what to stay away from, with its GMO alert. It is helping me to be a better food consumer, and eat more healthy. It's got everything a person who wants to be healthy, could possibly want, to reach their goals. Love it!!

title: Pretty good
body: Sometimes it seems the app has its own agenda and rates foods very low for prejudice against a certain ingredient. It also is incorrect as to some caloric and ingredient info, would be nice to update or be able to flag it. But overall it's a great app that calls attention to things people may not see or notice, like possible GMO ingredients or inulin or colorings. I like the alternative food suggestor.

title: Fun with family
body: Love this app. It's nice to know good from the bad and my 8 year old loves it too. She even had me scan candy to see what grade was given....she didn't ask me for any type of junk food and also told her dad certain foods weren't good for him. I also love the reminder to use it when I pull up to the store

title: Alice W. Yarnell
body: I think that Fooducate is a very good website. One problem I found in the variance of calories for the same item by different users. It would be good if everyone could report the same number of calories for the same product. They are also showing different grades. Is there anything that can be done about these problems?

title: Works for me :)
body: I've only been using this app for a little over a week and it seems to be a great alternative to do a "self started" weight watchers type of diet. So far any foods I've needed have been in the system already and I like that you can change from calories to food points or however you are wanting to manage your diet. So far so good!

title: Very useful
body: Often times I find myself at the grocery store faced with too many options for the same thing...I'm able to quickly and easily pick the healthiest option using this app. Barcode scanner makes this all the easier to use.

title: Love it!
body: I can't believe this app is free! I would pay for it, it's awesome. I'm starting a health diet, this helps so much! I scanned a few items I already had in my cupboard and felt guilty! I need to stop taking everything written on the front of the package for face value! This app will definitely be with me during my next shopping trip!

title: Awesome app! I use this daily!
body: If you're trying to lose weight or just be more conscious of what you're eating this is a great app! Constantly updating database, love the option to take pics and upload so they can add products to their database. My only suggestion (minor) is to add the ability to group delete messages.

title: Great App
body: I love this app.   I use it all the time in the grocery store.   I scan the barcode and it tells me all about the nutritional value without having to decipher the nutrition label.   Also, it calculates dieter's points the same as the weight watchers points plus system so I can tell if it is also worth the points plus value.

title: Might be the best app in the app store!
body: I LOVE this app!!! The first day I got it I was so obsessed I ran around scanning all the food in my house lol! I would have paid $5 for this app honestly. I love that it gives you such an in depth review of the foods AND gives you alternatives! I just hope the makers of this app keep up with it and continue to add food! :)

title: Very useful app! Love it - u need no other!!
body: This is the perfect app - the scanner picks up easily & lists all kinds of items - even helps me to add items that are not listed! I feel better prepared in making healthier selections for my family. I'm so glad (& thankful) for this app! I'm totally satisfied and would highly recommend it!

title: This ap is my grocery shopping companion!
body: We may have lost on 37 last night but that won't stop us from moving onward and upward. Fooducate is an amazing way to stay on top on your non gmo diet plus they ad new products every time I check in. We deserve to know we are eating quality and natural foods..Love this ap!

title: So convenient
body: If not completely sure about a food product while I am shopping, all I have to do is whip my phone out and scan. This has helped so much with making cleaner food choices. I try not to purchase anything graded below a B-. Makes me feel more confident, and is very educational!

title: Fantastic app
body: I'm not one who writes apps reviews, this one was worth it.

title: Fooducate
body: This app is awesome! I have lost almost 16 pounds since July using this app and weighing and measuring my food. I even told my granddaughter about it and she is now using it to lose weight for her upcoming wedding! I highly recommend this app. Even when I get off track and gain a few pounds, it gets me right back on track.

title: Love it!
body: My favorite part is that it gives me healthier alternatives and explanations for why some things are rated lower so for example, if it is high in sodium and that isn't a concern for me at least I'm educated on my choices. I also like seeing my progress on weight loss even if it is up and down sometimes.

title: Thank you!
body: This App is exactly what I was looking for - incredibly easy to use and extremely informative about what we are putting into our bodies. There are so many calorie count and exercise tracking apps out there but this goes beyond that and offers alternatives and health risks for each item. LOVE

title: Love this app!
