body: I am so glad someone told me about this app I had it for a while before I started using it but once I created an account and put my weight, goals, what I was eating my workouts, etc i have come to depend on this app for tracking my burned calories and what I can eat based on my workouts etc! I love it!

title: Best food & exercise tracking app for me
body: this app stacks up against the other apps out there. The design is attractive as well as ability to scan foods and adjust servings. It does a decent job at guessing how many calories you've burned but even when you've tracked a different amt, you can change it. I tried MyNetDiary and MyFitnessPal which are both good but I like Fooducate best.

title: Great but could use a few more tweaks
body: I've had this app for a while and it's been very useful. However, the latest update required a whole new app and now a subscription is required. Not sure I'm too happy with that now. I'm not really interested in all the extra features. I just want to use it to scan stuff at the store and that's it.

title: Awesome!
body: I love this app! It tells me Everything I need to know about what I'm about to eat. And with this App's help, I've already lost 5 pounds. Not changing much, but watching what I'm eating! If your looking for something that gives you all of your info on a food, this Apps for you!! Thank you for making Fooducate!!

title: Unable to customize
body: Overall I like the app. It's set up well.

title: Buggy Update
body: Edited 10/1: Latest update fixed some of the previous bugs and I like the features, but now I'm unable to enter any new food. It's practically useless for me at this point since I can only quick add calories right now.

title: Great app!
body: This is a great app! Every time we shop, we use the Food Finder to switch out at least one item for a better alternative. With Congress so enamored with big food companies and CAFO's, we can't rely on proper, honest labeling. With this app I can take the power back and put food (rather than chemicals) in my family's mouth.

title: I use this app EVERYDAY, love it!!!
body: I don't go to the grocery store without it. It takes the guess work out of label reading and gives me a detailed assessment of the health value, as well as the low down on on the additives (which I can barely pronounce) I can make truly healthy choices for myself and my family.

title: Just great
body: So easy to use, intuitive - for anyone trying to track their daily intake of everything! Would be super if once you chose a fraction of portion size the nutrition information - specifically sugars - for those who need to monitor that value - would adjust automatically as well :)

title: I love it!
body: Not only is it awesome , they have contests that you can win stuff. You don't have to sign up, you just scan! I love all the info that the program offers when you scan a product. And it gives you alternative foods to eat that's healthier for you. I love this program. Highly recommended.

title: Love this App
body: This app is AWESOME & its FREE!!! Spent 3 hrs in the store & I scanned almost 150 items--at least now there is not 1 single item in my kitchen below a B-  It also help me choose healthier choices! Some things Ive been eating that are thought were healthy didnt score so well so that means I will never buy them again! Thanks Fooducate for helping me be a healthier person!!!

title: VERY GOOD
body: This app (Fooducate) is a very useful app. When I first got it I used it each time I went to the supermarket. A lot of the products I scanned were rated a C, which was very disappointing, but I learned about the unhealthy ingredients of food such as preservatives and other things I wasn't even aware of. All in all I recommend this app. It is convenient, easy to use and understand and best of all, it is free.

title: Great for decision making
body: I love this app because it gives you the information you need quickly. It tells you the ingredients that you should be aware of and helps to steer you in the right direction. The app also gives better alternatives so you can use it while shopping.

title: Great way to start being healthy
body: If you're ever confused or concerned about whether or not your food choices are healthy this is the app for you. The best part is that they give you healthier alternatives to any product you look up! Plus you get detailed descriptions on why each item is healthy or unhealthy. Great app.

title: Great app. Seriously use it every time when grocery shopping.
body: Great app. Seriously use it every time when grocery shopping. Has quick an easy ratings to go off of as well for the things you scan. It is able to pull up everything I have scanned so far.

title: Wellness
body: I have recently become familiar with fooducate and find it very beneficial in learning about  various foods and their nutritional value. For this reason it really does help to contribute to over all Heath and wellness. It is very simple to use and people friendly. Just point and click. I am greatful that this app is available for my iPhone.

title: Very informative
body: This app gives you real insight on food and what it's really made of! I was so surprised to see that some of the foods I thought were considered "healthy" actually had GMO's and other scary things in them. It really makes you aware of what you're eating and think before eating something. Wonderful app!!

title: In love
body: My fitnesspal app keeps messing up n today I downloaded this again. I love how it gives you information about the food you post ABC -+ etc, so you can know to take that food out of your house. So far I am loving it I am sure it will help me to stay on track plus lose weight. Thx

title: Only one suggestion....
body: This app is amazing but I have one suggestion. It would be amazing if you guys could let us know if the item is vegan. I always have to read all the ingredients, even when I'm in a bit of a hurry. Needing to just scan something and know if it's vegan or not would be a game changer

title: Excellent
body: Well-researched, organized, and informative without being preachy, condescending or dumbed-down.  Great for the more experienced food-label reader, yet friendly for those who are learning about food additives and making smarter food choices.  Easy-to-use interface with clean, bright graphics and uncluttered layout.  :)

title: Very informative app!
body: I teach nutrition and I recommend this app to all of my students. It really helps them make healthy choices when shopping. Marketing can be misleading and sometimes reading the labels can be confusing. This makes it simple to know what to eat and what to stay away from.

title: Great app!
body: Making sure you really know what is going in to your body is incredibly important and this app makes it to simple. Just scan the barcode, tell it how much you ate and you're done!

title: Great app
body: I go armed with my iPhone to the market. I scans every box I buy. If it scans A or B I buy it. B- maybe, C the product go back on the shelf for someone else to buy. I am trying to but as many A products as possible.  This app makes you aware of how much trash food is out there. This app should come on every smart phone.

title: Very good
body: I find it easy to use and has lots of food information. I wish there was a way to create your own food with your own info for things you make yourself. Or maybe some stock info for things like cuts of meat. I'd also like to have an easy to access list of favorite foods.

title: Awesome
body: This app is perfect, I wanted to easily look up the nutritional info of foods but not track everything I eat. This app lets you set goals that are health related not weight related. You can use it to track your calories and weight but it does so much more! I tried lots of similar apps and this one is the best.

title: Love it except
body: I love this app except some products I've scanned the calorie count is different on the item and in the app. But over all great app, comes in handy when grocery shopping and making a grocery list! Love reading the comments on different foods that people put their own recipe or twist on how they cook theirs!

title: Great enabler
body: The scan function is very useful, but the tracking that comes with the upgrade is superior.  I can track my intake for all nutrients and make adjustments through the day to arrive at my targeted goals.  I also enjoy the daily articles that are educational.  The frequency reinforces healthy eating habits.

title: I love this app!
body: I tell everyone about this app because it is fun and educational.  The articles and tips are great. Love that it gives alternatives- though some are kind of hard to find. Still striving for an "A" day but the process makes me more conscious about what I am eating than any other app or diet ever has.

title: Good
body: This is a wonderful app. It makes it easy to see the nutritional content of the foods you eat daily. My only complaint is that I don't like seeing the comments left by people on the different foods. I don't care that someone loves or hates a certain food. It's aggravating that you can't hide the comments.

title: Never shop with out it
body: This is hands down the best app I've gotten to help make better food choices. I love everything about it.

title: Great to have in the grocery store!
body: I started using this app right away to help my kids make healthy choices in the grocery store. My son is now keenly interested in picking foods that he likes with good nutritional scores.

title: Love this
body: I have told so many people about this app and they have downloaded it and loved it as well. It gives so much relevant and helpful info about each product. The reason I didn't give it five stars, which it deserves, is because I bought an ipad2 and couldn't wait to use this app, but it won't read the barcodes. I was so disappointed. Otherwise FANTASTIC app!

title: Best nutritional education app ever
body: I thought I was eating healthy until I started using this app and discovered all the hidden health risks in my food choices.  I love all the information provided, the ratings and especially the five alternative foods which offer better options.  Everyone should have this app.

title: Great!
body: Love this app.  It's been great for making decisions in the store and for educating us on how unhealthy are some of the regular brand items we were eating. My only criticism would be that oftentimes the alternatives offered seem to be obscure brands that I don't have at my grocery.  We have a great grocery, extensive grocer, but no trader joes or whole foods near us and many times I cannot find the alternatives.

title: Changed the way I eat!
body: Super easy to use and I've learned so much!  It's helping me make better decisions about what I eat while teaching me to recognize what makes good things good.  It also teaches about common marketing tricks that food manufacturers will use to mislead consumers about the quality or creation o a product.

title: Excellent app but many products not found
body: When I break out the iPhone to shop with fooducate, I take so much longer because I spend a lot of time sending photos back for missing products. I know it only works if we contribute, however it does seem a good percentage of things in my stores are not found.  Overall it is a neat app.

title: A positive motivator
body: I heard about this tool during a continuing education course for dentistry. The excessive amount of sugar being added to everything has become alarming. This app is a fantastic aid to help rate your food items without getting bombarded by the numerous choices and lengthy labels. Very helpful tool for a busy working mom.

title: Best Nutrition/Health App
body: I have been looking for something that could educate me on what I was eating and what was good or bad about it. I feel like I just don't understand all the calorie/carb/fat counting. This was perfect. Great articles, add your meals/recipes, scan your groceries... I felt like I understand for once what I'm actually eating. Great app! I use it daily!

title: Super easy app!
body: This app is so simple to use for keeping track of your calories, carbohydrates and sugars! Just scan a barcode on your product or scroll through all of the menu items on many many restaurant listings. I've been using this app for a several years and love love love it!

title: Love it
body: Loving this app. Scanner works well. Lots of products in the database. Had a new food added within a couple days of my request. Detailed nutrition info and good tips about what makes a food healthy. Clean UI. Thanks to the developers and please keep this one going. I would be highly upset to see it die.

title: Great app
body: This app is amazing! I scan everything I buy and if it's lower then a B I won't buy it. It's very helpful for people who live a healthy lifestyle and tells me everything I need to know about what I'm buying. I'm also vegan so it will tell me whether a product is vegan or not and the alternatives I can buy. Def the best app I ever used!

title: Annoyed
body: This app was awesome but for some reason with a recent update the scanner doesn't work anymore. I figured they would notice the bug and fix it but that was several months ago and still nothing. Instead of posting a negative comment I wanted to report the bug but when I clicked on the button it lead me to their homepage and I said you know what this is just too much effort for a stupid app. You had a good thing going, bummed you changed it.

title: Not what it use to be
body: I use to use this app a while ago. I just downloaded it again because I really like the ability to see what food is really processed and what's not. It's absolutely great for that.

title: New user
body: Thoroughly impressed with how quick items not in data base get added. It's so neat to be able to contribute to the available selections. Having the option to scan your foods in the tracker instead of always typing them in is awesome. Time saver for sure. Love the app!

title: Fantabulous App
body: The best App ever if you are a health conscious individual or wanting to make better food choices. Has helped me select better brands with better and healthier ingredients. The rating system is great. I recommend this App to everyone. If you are on Weight Watchers, it gives you the point values per serving.

title: So grateful for this app!!!!
body: This is hands down, the best app on my phone. I can't live without it!! I would recommend it to anyone who is conscious about what they are putting in their body.  This app has convinced me that cancer is running rampant in our country bc of the food source. Thank you for helping me protect my family!!!

title: Great info
body: Love using this app while grocery shopping to scan bar codes. The app grades the nutrition value of the food and provides better alternatives. Also enjoy reading the articles.  I have recommended this app to those who take interest in the good they put on their bodies.

title: new update...
body: I really don't like the new update...it shows too many products added by users and not the actual product I'm looking for. I don't always have the time to scan each individual box and sometimes searching it is easier but now that there are so so many user added products it takes double the time to come across the one I'm looking for.

title: Great resource to learn what's in your food
body: Fooducate is amazing. If you want to know what you're really eating (and you should) just scan the barcode or enter in the item and the app tells you a grade, the ingredients and explanation of how healthy it is. Great for reducing amount of processed food in your diet. Highly recommend.

title: Don't understand
body: I have scanned a few items and it always just goes back to the scanning screen after a search. So I guess that means it didn't find the product. Also I have had 3 unread messages for weeks now and when I go to read them it says no unread messages right below where it says 3 unread messages. Huh?  I have reinstalled and still the same thing. Don't know what I am doing wrong.  1 star until I can figure this out. 1 star for me if it is operator error but I don't know what I could possibly be doing.

title: Not bad
body: Turns out what I eat is mostly C's.. Ah well. Win some, lose some. Anyways, the app itself is pretty good. Has everything I can think of except a few local-only store brands such as Market Basket and H-E-B.

title: Dare to Relearn What to Eat
body: Quite an eye opener to what we choose to consume! Many people may not care what they eat until they get a heart attack or worse. We all can live full lives if we educate ourselves and this app does just that. Thank you to all the researchers that provide accurate assessments to foods that are healthy and wholesome.

title: Great App AND Customer Service!
body: Great app. Offers so much information! Very compatible with the Weight Watchers points plus program. I found a point discrepancy with one product and wrote to them. They immediately wrote back, asked for more info, fixed the problem and followed up with me!!

title: Phenomenal App. So easy and informative!
body: This app is awesome. The best free app I've had in a looooong time. So much great information. Especially about things I had no idea were not so good. Im on WW too and this is PERFECT. why does WW not have this scanning ability?? Crazy. Makes tracking so easy! This app in incredible. Thanks for this gift! So much crap in our food!

title: Easy to use, informative
body: App makes it easy to get information about stuff. Some of the ratings seem a little preachy and arbitrary (e.g. rating a frozen low-calorie meal a D because there are healthier alternatives, while giving diet soda, which has no health value whatsoever, a C- ) but once you figure out the biases it's useful and makes you feel better about what you're choosing.

title: Works well
body: Moving around this app is very seamless. I cannot rave about the design and user experience enough. It is filled with great facts that are useful when shopping and also has a great feature to help with losing weight by eating a healthy diet specific to your caloric needs that adjust with every few pounds you lose. Worth a try!

title: Great resource for anyone eating healthier
body: I love this app! It's easy to use since you scan your foods to find out the pros and cons of what you're eating.  It's also easy to add new foods to the list and check the score if it's not already in the data base.  Great for parents who want their kids to be eating nutrient rich foods.

title: Rate, explain, offer an alternative
body: This app really lives up to its name. It does all the things that other health apps like Lose It do, but it's additional features of rating food, providing detailed and well-sourced explanations for these ratings, and offering alternatives to help improve your nutritional life.

title: Enlightening
body: Being a ballet dancer who has a rigorous schedule six days a week, I always assumed I would burn off everything and I didn't have to be AS cautious of what I was putting in my body. This app really helped me see that I was wrong. I really believe it will aid me beneficially in my journey to weight loss and a healthy lifestyle.

title: Amazing!
body: I usually shop very healthy anyway but now with this app, grocery shopping takes a lot longer. The food I thought was extremely healthy isn't. Other than a slight headache when I leave the store from concentrating so hard, I will still rate this app excellent.

title: Only problem ....
body: This app is great! My only complaint is that it doesn't let you choose the amount of carbohydrates or calories that you want to consume,  some diets have much less-  like the Atkins diet just has allowed for the induction phase of 20 carbohydrates. And to lose weight I want much less than 1000 something that it requested to eat on a daily basis.

title: Love this app
body: I use this app all the time.  It's amazing how many food items I thought were healthy alternatives to other items - only to find I was way off base! I use the GMO function too. Use it at home and the grocery store.  I am a weight watcher member and love that it also gives food point values!

title: Lost a pound a day so far
body: Well. Okay. So it's easy for me to go on a diet but this app made it easy to show my husband I could not eat whatever he was shoving at me. Also the scanner made a great calorie counter, however I think it could be improved with suggesting what I should eat next such as suggesting a protein or starch.

title: Done and cancel buttons are backwards
body: This is a really awesome app! It has calorie information like MyFitnessPal and points systems for dieters akin to Weight Watchers, and the barcode reader isn't too finicky, but the cancel and submit buttons are reverse than their position in every other app. I suppose you get used to it, but I've accidentally deleted almost every submission.

title: Not bad!
body: I would give it 5 stars but more often then not when I go to scan an item, it more than likely not in their data base and I'm having to submit everything to them....at this point I feel like they should be paying me for doing their job....that's why I have it 4 stars...overall great concept and good app!

title: Great App but lot of ads if not Premium
body: It has been useful to track my food. And I like the end of day summary. But there are a lot of annoying ads pop ups and requests to review. That being said here is my positive review despite that. Also I love the food library and the rating system amount information collected on each food.

title: Great App
body: I am a former weight watchers participant and I used WW e-tools. This app is similar but gets into greater detail regarding food choices. It will give the food a grade and also offers healthier alternatives. Although it seems costly for an app - it's the same as a one month subscription to WW. Easy to use and it syncs with other health apps.

title: Rasheed93
body: I just downloaded this and I am very pleased with all the information I can get on products and their alternatives. It is an excellent app if you want to know what certain ingredients are and I like the rating system it uses,  it's very helpful and I would definitely recommend this app to a friend or anyone who cares about what they eat.

title: Amazing way to be mindful
body: This is so user friendly and makes it so much easier to be mindful about what I eat and make better choices. I have struggled with my weight my whole life and this app makes it so I am not hungry because I know what to eat and what has lower calories so I can eat more!

title: Love this app!
body: highly recommend this app our 12 year old uses it to scan products both at home and at the market and he is having fun learning about food and making better choices.  great for kids and adults who want to learn more about what foods they eat.

title: Wonderful!
body: This app is so helpful to anyone who cares about what they are consuming. I watch what I eat but a lot of "healthy" products marketed have added and sometimes harmful ingredients. This barcode scanner does more than tell you what the product is--it tells you what's in it and if it's healthy!

title: Great for healthy living
body: Fooducate is perfect because it has an option for calculating caloric & dietary needs for women who are breast feeding, vegans, vegetarians, and other special considerations. It also will issue reminders without being obnoxious. I also like the articles posted on the home page.

title: Seriously a must-have app!!
body: This has made such a huge difference in the things I buy and eat. I realise now just how many unhealthy things masquerading as "good-for-you" foods I've been buying and consuming for a long time. Now I'm better educated lol seriously, I encourage everyone to get this app!!

title: No information
body: Ive bought this app over a year ago & theres not much bad to say. Considering a year+ I just recently had issues with the health tracker not even showing up & same for contact/support. So, all dietary points & values I manually did, which defeats the point of the app. Hopefully, they'll fix the 'bug' and I can continue loving Fooducate app.

title: Could use more utilities for exercise but otherwise great
body: It's a great app and provides many options for food and exercise. It's simple and easy to use even if you're often busy. I just wish that it had the same summaries for workout amount/quality per day as it does for calorie amount and quality.

title: Life SAVER
body: This app helps me stay on track by giving me alternatives and tips. Something I didn't have on other apps I was using. When I had a craving for something I knew wasn't good for me i would just eat it anyway because I didn't know anything else to eat. But the alternatives help so much. I love it.

title: Gives a break down of more than just calories and points
body: The barcode tool makes it easy to track your intake by nutrients. Warning, it can be shocking to learn what your actually eating.

title: Love it but....
body: I got this after using Fitbit's food tracking. I wanting to eat better and track macro numbers. I love that this grades the food, explains the grade, and gives you better alternatives. I wish it tracked carbs in the free version. You have to pay to count carbs. The food database is great. Seems to recognize some aldi brands which is mostly where I shop. Just wish the free version had more options.

title: I really love this app!
body: I like the way this app is set up. I've been only tracking my calories for 2 days but this app is very informative and helpful on the calories you need per day to loose "x amount" of weight by such and such date. It's a pretty good app. I can't weight to lose weight on this app.

title: Definetely informative
body: I enjoy this app, it really opens my eyes to some things that I thought were ok snacks for my kids, also like to scan those foods that I am proud of to eat and see that "A".  My son loves to use this app when I get home from the grocery store to scan everything I bought!

title: Really useful
body: I tend to expect too much from apps, but this one is just great. It doesn't always have data on obscure products, but that is to be expected. This app does what it says and does it well. It would be hard to think of ways to improve this app.

title: Good to use
body: I am a health nut, so I like to know what's in the food I buy. This gives me a pretty good read on what's in my food - both what I want in it and what I don't want in it. The recommendations could use some work though, as some of what's recommended can be higher in added sugar or some other ingredient you don't want. Overall though a really good product.

title: Great App
body: This is just what I needed something to help me make good decisions at the grocery store, Inform me about what I'm eating,  And guide me to a healthier lifestyle. Use it as a supplement to your current weight loss program; Or like me use it in loo of other paid programs. Free and easy to use. Definitely worth downloading and giving it a try. üëçüëç

title: Great App!
body: I love this app because it is so easy to use and read. A lot of similar apps give the same nutritional breakdown, but this ones rates your food between A and D so it is much easier to read. It also tells you what the red flags of your meal are so you know what to look out for later. This is a great app!

title: Love ‚ù§
body: Great app! Tells me everything about the food from fat, carbs, protein, and vitamins, to facts about sodium, cholesterol, processed foods etc. so much info and helps me keep track during the day. It would be nice if at the end of the day it would give you a total of fats, proteins, etc. it does for carbs and cals but not anything else üòî

title: Wow!
body: This app is great! It's helped me realize some of things I was picking at the store were not the best choices and I can easily find a better product to choose in no time by using the scanner!   Definitely one of the most used apps on my phone! Couldn't go without it now! Thanks Fooducate :)

title: Saving Lives.
body: With the thousands of choices that we have at the grocery store, a lot have potential hazards to our families health. Thank you for helping me decipher through the misleading labels and advertisements. Easy to use and understand which ingredients or

title: Love this app!
body: Great app for making you aware of what goes in your mouth and its impact on your health. Trying to monitor my fat and cholesterol intake and I haven't been able to locate this option ... Thus 4 instead of 5 stars. Thanks Fooducate! 2 weeks later i am managing my health like never before . Thrilled with this app!

title: Me
body: What a great app. It answers my questions about products & gives so much guidance about food. Amazingly, most of the name brands & a lot of the lesser brands are there in their listings. I  really appreciate the help with what I eat. It makes food shopping so much easier with the scan feature.

title: Next Update
body: This app is amazing! But, I think that when you do a comparison, you should be able to click that item and find the nearest store that sells that item. You could also add comparison prices. Please add more products because going through our pantry, you had at least 10 items that you didn't recognize. Other than that, this application is helpful! I give this app 3.5 stars

title: 1st impression
body: As a new user I find it useful for items already in the data base. Consistency between labels on the product vs those in data base are acceptable.  Response to items not already in the data base is too slow.  Alternatives are generally difficult to find in same location.  Would like to see pricing added to this app.

title: Best food app out there!
body: I am impressed with the quality, accuracy, and overall look of this app. It has an easy-to-navigate format with very useful info. Love having WeightWatcher points available for most foods and the alternative feature is great. Powerful app you will use often!

title: Amazing!
body: I have been overweight for some time. I joined Weight Watchers and the pounds started falling off. With this application I am able to keep a more accurate track of food items. I didn't believe it when I saw this app in action. I recommend it to anybody staying in shape or on a wright loss program.

title: Love this app
body: This app is so helpful in how I go about choosing what packaged foods I buy. If something gets a C or lower it doesn't go in my basket. I've gotten funny looks  when I scan my food and the ding happens. It does give me an opportunity to tell people about the app though. Thank you iTunes for having this great app

title: Great way to pay better attention to what you eat!
body: I love this app because when I use it, I think about what I eat a lot more than I would on a normal day. It's also interesting to know how many calories you are actually taking in with out any hard work.

title: Great App!
body: This is a truly great weight loss and nutrition app! Better than any other I have tried, it is very thorough and provides a great breakdown of the foods you eat as well as making you aware of good calories and bad. The only reason I gave it 4 instead of 5 stars is because it is a little more difficult to navigate than other apps

title: Great App +A
body: This is my second year using this app. I started using it because I was having a problem controlling my blood sugar. I was able right away to get it under control and keep it that way. It has also helped me keep my wait stable. My doctor was very pleased.

title: Love the Info but the app needs an upgrade
body: I do love all of the great info and the rating system. The reason for my low star rating is the lack of a search feature. The browse option is not cutting it. And I'm not in store shopping while using the app, I'm trying to plan my list ahead of time so scanning isn't an option. The only way I can search is through google which will take me back to the app. Why not add this as a feature?

title: So far it's great!
body: I had this years ago and didn't really use it too much, although it did change the way I think about "healthy food".

title: Must have!
body: Wonderful app but I will warn you, you can get addicted to scanning everything! :)

title: Informative
body: This app has been extremely helpful in showing me healthier alternatives to what's in my pantry. I've scanned dozens of items and only one wasn't in the registry, so it definitely has a large inventory of products. I would highly recommend this app to anyone seeking a healthier lifestyle.

title: Best Nutrition Info App Available
body: Absolutely fantastic app. Could be called Nutrition for Dummies. It's amazing what foods so many people think are "healthy" alternatives to other foods. There is so much more to our food to consider than calories and fat. This app give you the hard truth (which is, 75% of what we eat is garbage!)

title: EXCELLENT APP
body: This app has helped me make much better/healthier food decisions while grocery shopping. I love the alternative options key, when you know what you want but just don't know which "brand" or ingredients are better in the actual item...the best app. Wish they offered one for dining out too.

title: Addicting app!
body: Really dig this app - I've only been using it for an hour and I'm already reconsidering several of my food choices! Very good / helpful info about food ingredients.

title: Love this app!
body: I use it all of the time while shopping to help me choose better options of products I want to buy!  I'm often amazed by how some "healthy" products aren't really that healthy for you.  This app has helped me and my family make better food choices!

title: Love this app!
body: Fooducate is the greatest app ever! It has helped me so much with my clean eating journey! I like the simplicity of scanning in my foods instead of having to log them in manually. Also, this app has taught me so much about foods I thought were ok. Thanks Fooducate! I am going to recommend this to all my friends!

title: Love it!
body: I love the scan function, especially the feature that offers alternatives to the item that you scan. I also like that you can send in pictures of items that aren't currently in their database so that they can be added.

title: Better but still needs work
body: Great and really quick but same product has different revues even though they have the same ingredients ex look up skippy natural creamy. Also takes forever to upload new products. Overall very good app sometimes shuts down but very well designed and organized

title: Wonderful Eye Opener!!
body: I just installed this app. This is going to be useful to me when I go grocery shopping. I scanned a few items I thought were  healthy that I had at home and was surprised how unhealthy they were.  With this app, I'm glad I can finally make some real healthy choices.

title: One of my favorite apps
body: For someone like me in the healthcare field this app is great!  My wife and i use it all the time and i told my friends and patients about this app. The only issue i have is that many of our food products we use at home are not in the database yet.  I give it two ÓÄé

title: Changes your outlook on the food you eat.
body: Love this app!  It gives you so much insight to the food you are eating.  I love that it grades your food and offers alternatives.  I scan food I would be purchasing at the grocery store and then end up buying a healthier alternative thanks to this app!

title: Great weight management app!
body: Since I started using Fooducate I've adopted much healthier eating habits and I've never felt so good about my body! The food database is incredibly simple to navigate and makes it easy to stay accountable for what I'm eating throughout the day. 5/5, would definitely recommend!

title: Love it!
body: This app is neat, keeps you up to date and informed . The only thing I would change would be when you type in what you already scanned or recorded, it would scroll up on "recent" tab rather then finding it all over again. Love it and helps me stay on track . Lost 10lbs so far by using it daily.

title: Loving it
body: This app is great for becoming more aware of the foods that you are eating (and how much of them). The design is intuitive and simple yet informative. I also appreciate that you can select breastfeeding since this changes caloric intake (although you have to have an upgrade).

title: Love
body: I just happened to hear about this app on a tv show that was playing in another room & decided to look it up. It's great! I had been using a different site for a long time but gained back all my bad habits. I enjoy the rating system & the pie chart of processed food consumption.

title: The Best
body: Learning to eat better is what's most important for me ,I do not go on diets anymore,a better way of eating is best and learning about what you eat.

title: Simplistic but very intuitive.
body: I love this app already. It has a simple interface but it's packed useful information regarding what to eat and what not. I have a high cholesterol and using this app has helped me lower it to a good level by using the food scanner to check the nutrition and its grade.

title: Love this app
body: I found this app on accident but I'm really glad I did. I have been using fitness pal and I thought it was the best till I found this one. The community here is great lots of support and ppl to help motivate you to keep going. Fitness pal doesn't have that. I will definitely keep using this app ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

title: Not as good as others
body: Used a few apps like this.  Compared to others the database of foods and products was lacking.  Tried nationally recognized products, regional products and local products. Poor job in all three categories.  While doing a search for a particularly large regional grocery store for their Italian bread I received every conceivable item that was Italian in any store even though I chose Publix Italian Bread so I would limit the number of hits.  Deleted app.

title: Love it!!
body: Easy to use and navigate! I've shared it w many friends and people have asked me in the aisles what I am using when they see us scanning our options! I live handing it to my 13 yr old and telling her she can pick any snack that is a B and up!! She is not thrilled but it's a great tool to help make people aware of what is in their foods and to make better choices.

title: Excellent guide for choosing healthy food!
body: Very educational and informative. I love how it points out when a product has preservatives or less nutritious ingredients. I also love the suggestions and even recipes it gives as alternatives! This is a must have when changing your diet for the better/best.

title: Awesome program
body: The database for this program is chock-full of timely and very useful information. it is one of the most useful if not the best program on the iPad. I highly suggest this program to anyone who's interested in information and data about food. Get it today

title: Love this
body: Very informative! In 5 minutes using the app, I was learned that the substitute sweetener I was using wasn't really a better choice for my diabetic husband; learned of The Dirty Dozen- the 12 fruits and vegetables to buy organic as they are heavily sprayed with insecticides; The Clean 15- fruits and veggies that are not sprayed much or do not hold onto the insecticides so organic for these, eh. VERY happy with this app.

title: Will change the way people eat!
body: Perfect for this generation! I can't believe how many unnecessary things I DID NOT buy because of how unhealthy they were. This app is like carrying a nutritionist with you during groceries. You will become a lot more self conscious about brands and the types of foods you buy.

title: Awesome!
body: This app is great. I wouldn't use it for tracking food, there are other apps that are better. Maybe if it divided meals into breakfast, lunch, dinner and snacks. But when I'm grocery shopping I use it all the time. Also, I've been trying to clean up my diet, so I only eat foods that are rate higher than a B-

title: Great app!
body: I use this constantly. They are great about letting you add products to their db that they don't have on file and they update as soon as they can. Love this incredibly useful app. The only "downside" is realizing how awful most packaged foods are, but who doesn't need to purge their pantry once in a while?  ;)

title: Keeper!
body: Great app for on the go education. I like that you can customize it for your personal health goals. For instance heart, vegan, vegetarian, or processed foods just to name a few. You can get a quick food grade, or read more if you have the time. It would be even better if  I could record my weight in tenths.

title: Superb!
body: I use this in the grocery store and I am a frequent Whole Foods shopper ( hey, you can never be too smart about food options). I send in photos and info to help update their info. I love the blog and everything about this make this a MUST have app. Thank you for your hard work and dedication fooducate.

title: Problems...
body: I love this app so much!!! The only few problems are its very difficult to record homemade things, which is a very big part of my diet. Also, when I try to add my own food item and I tap the calorie section and try to type, the entire app freezes! This happens all the time!!!!! Please tidy this app up. I'd be more than grateful! :))

title: No I'm Not Crazy
body: Ok, so I am going through Costco and the grocery store scanning all sorts of products! What are people thinking!?! Who knows? But I am having a great time and learning interesting nutrition facts about the foods on the shelves. This app is useful, interesting, educating and FUN! Go ahead, give it a try! I would/will give it a five star when they build up their product base more. <3

title: Actually very good!
body: I normally don't take the time to write reviews but this APP is truly very useful for anyone wanting to clean the garbage out of their diet.  As long as they keep expanding their library of items the APP can scan...this is well worth the download and I wouldn't mind paying for a tool like this.  Very good job.

title: So great!
body: This is a wonderful app. It gives you useful info in a simple and easy to understand format. It also gives you access to more in depth info. I love the compare and find better alternatives options as well. I'd gladly pay for this app so I'm thrilled that it's free!! Thank you for this app devs! It's awesome!

title: Appropriately named app!
body: Even if you already read labels this app is helpful...and fun! I was surprised to find it had many store brand (Giant) items too.  I've scanned at least 3 or 4 dozen items with no problems.  It is also a great way to involve children and help them make healthier choices-they love it!

title: Quick and easy shopping assistant
body: Love the easy access convenient scanner that quickly let's you know the ins and outs of the products I buy. Amazing to see how many "natural, green, healthy, humane" products that have bad preservatives. It makes label reading a quick snapshot away!

title: Addicted to this App!
body: I use this ALL the time and have been alarmed at what I didn't know I didn't know. This has made it so much easier to shop and I love the alternative options not only for finding healthier choices, but also for finding cost savings for similar rated products.

title: Life-changing!
body: This is one of, if not the best, app I've ever used! So informative, well-designed, user-friendly, and convenient! Only I wish it could save products without adding it to the grocery list .. They should also add more products! And add more alternatives to junk food items.

title: Very Helpful App
body: I discovered this app by reading the Daily Herald. It provides very helpful information about different foods, and it raises my awareness of what I am actually putting into my body. The food database is large, but many of the store brands I consume are missing. Additionally, my experience of this app would be improved if Fooducate could interact with Fitbit and MyFitnessPal apps.

title: Fantastic
body: Great app with wonderful interface. Love the ranking system given to each item. Would like more transparency on items sent to be uploaded. All that was received back was and email stating usage is greater than normal and added item will take a while.

title: Great app for tracking your food and getting educated!
body: Enjoying this app, upgrades are a bit expensive but so far I've found them worthwhile. This app is helping me find the best food options and tracking calories and weight loss goal progression. Also helps with gluten free diet. Love it!

title: GREAT APP! LOVE IT!!!!!
body: I LOVE  this app. It is easy to use. I am often surprised at foods I thought were really healthy, and are not. Really good information so I can make better choices. Love the part where there are optional food if what I'm looking for doesn't have a good score. I share Fooducate with other people often. LOVE IT!!!

title: Looks nice..before you download it..
body: This app looks awesome in the App Store, but once you download it, you are hounded to constantly pay for features that are commonly free in other apps!  Okay, say that you don't need all of the features that Fooducate has to offer.  Since you're still not paying for their apps subscription, you get to enjoy an advertisement banner at the bottom of your app.  Unless you're willing to pay a few bucks a month for this app, don't waste your time in he first place.

title: Only good tracker app that counts added sugar
body: I love this app for the added sugar tracking & pie charts showing % of protein, fats, carbs each day and for the supportive Twitter-like community. On the other hand, their list of foods to track is extremely small compared to any other tracker & the exercise calorie count does not factor your personal info so it way overestimates calorie burn.

title: Real food is essential!
body: This app has been an incredible eye-opener for me in my goal to eat clean. Calorie count doesn't cut it anymore, it's calorie quality and WHAT I am actually eating. So helpful in my journey to move toward cutting out processed food and GMO. I use it every day to track everything I put I my body!

title: Looooove
body: I've had this app for so long but I haven't used it in months that I didn't realize I had the old version. I updated and it looks SO much better and has a lot more information on the foods I scan. It's very dependable when I'm not sure if I'm eating right.

title: Room for improvements
body: I have used two similar weight loss apps (Livestrong and MyFitnessPal) and I have to say that I love this one for the "rating" system on food health and processing along with its very fun visuals. If I could make a suggestion, however, it would be to allow for a higher variation of portion sizes (i.e. 1/8, 3/8, 5/8; 1/3, 2/3; 3/4) and better integration of these sizes at higher values (e.g. 2 1/4).

title: Just what the Dr. ordered.
body: Find out about the app because in my visit to my nutritionist this is what she use. Love it! My shopping guess is a thing of the past. Can have all the info about nutrition in my hands. Convenient, practical, useful and a great tool to help you achieve your goals.

title: Great source of info
body: Practical way to improve a little each day. Great features. Very useful information. Rating system is easy to understand. I've lost 15 lbs. so far just because it helps me pay attention and make better choices.

title: Just what the cardiologist ordered
body: My Emory cardiologist and hospital instructed me to keep track of liquid intake, sodium and general nutrition daily. this app not only provides an easy manner to do that; AND scan barcodes for complete data on food items.

title: Love it already
body: I just downloaded this app but I can definitely see why so many people use it as a weight loss tool. I love that it not only examines calories but the ratings for each food items and explanations really help learn what your eating and how to better your health!

title: Great app!
body: This app really helps you stay informed about what's healthy or not. Great for any one trying to stay fit or just looking to keep healthy!

title: Love it
body: Fooducate is awesome if you a weight watchers member no more typing in things to the points calculator just scan the product and the points are right there on the screen along with comparison choices. Only thing is sometimes new products aren't available you you have the option to add them and help our foodicate.

title: Amazing!
body: This app is great because it scans quickly and gives you a letter grade for the product as well as highlight the good and the bad ingredients with a summary of what they mean. It also gives you a list of healthier alternatives in the same product category. Thank you Fooducate for this very helpful app!!!!

title: I love this app
body: This is a great app. I find myself scanning things before I buy them. The only issue I've had is when I've scanned a lot of items the "scanner" is unable to focus on the next item. It fixes it self when I restart the app other than that I love it. Truly an eye opener :)

title: Educational tool
body: I show students in my high school health class how to use this app. Every drink or food item that is brought into my classroom is "'fooducated' and becomes a teachable moment. My new rule: students can only eat real food in my classroom with a rating of an A or B. Foods have become an academic topic thanks to the Fooducate app.

title: Great app
body: I totally love this app. So helpful when trying to find out the nutritional value of an item..love how you can scan an item that is not listed and in a short time the working team will gather all the info and submit all the nutritional value of the item you scanned.

title: The best health food app available
body: The best, most resourceful health food app ever! I've tried them all and I use this one everyday. If you are concerned about GMOs, not getting enough of your daily vitamins and minerals, trying to shed a few pounds or just trying to eat a bit healthier then this is A MUST HAVE for everyone.

title: Great, but could be better
body: I love this app. It usually has everything I eat in its system. However I would like it to be able to calculate homemade meals better and also show me some sort of history of my previous meals. Like 7/10 days I met my calorie goal, or on what day I did best with my food points. But overall very helpful.

title: Outstanding
body: Excellent app for anyone interested in a healthy lifestyle. Beginners and advanced health enthusiast alike will be completely satisfied with this elite health app. Learn the facts about your food choices, track and record your calories, exercises, and goals while being informed of your decisions and other options. OUTSTANDING!!!!!!!!!!!

title: Wow!
body: This is one of the coolest apps I have ever seen. It's easy to use anywhere and there is nothing that it doesn't track. It not only tracks calories, but the actual food intake, gives food alternatives. Also tracks weight, water intake and exercise! Definitely download this. It's worth it!

title: Very Useful
body: This is a great app. It is practical and useful. Use it to help determine better, healthy lifestyle food choices. Even if you think you know what you are picking to eat is a good choice, you will be surprised by what this app reveals. Love the ease of use of the scan function; quick and accurate.

title: Good but could b better
body: This app is very convenient and provides a lot of information for packaged foods.

title: Awesome!! Thank you for a great app!!
body: It's like your personal shopper and personal trainer all in one!! It has helped me to eat much healthier!! Provides the reason why a certain item is or is not healthy, Takes your personal goals into consideration with every product, And is a breeze to use!! üí™üí™üí™üí™üí™

title: Wonderful
body: I really love this app. I thought I was shopping smart and healthy for my kids before but had quiet a rude awakening. I wish I could set it to weed out foods with specific thing I don't want but maybe you can do that on the paid version but I still love this thing nonetheless.

title: Thanks!
body: I begin with the only negative in this app and that is you cannot edit/ erase food list.  There are no complaints with anything else. Excellent teamwork - have learned great deal regarding nutrition - awareness of dangers in food - awareness of value in food - in other words I love this app & heartily thank everyone involved! Great work!

title: All-in-one!
body: Great app! Provides guidelines for weight loss AND nutrition. You can track by calories and food points, which is great if you're coming off of WW. Please make this app universal (and enable iCloud sync) and provide a Notification Center widget...then it's definitely worth five stars and the best in its category!

title: Retired restaurant mgr
body: I have leaned A lot since I've been using the dictate it tells you the nutritions it tells you the protein it tells you what good it tells you it's bad you can scan items at the grocery store to tell you what kind of a grade it will get a A- BCD etc. is been very helpful for me

title: Pretty good food tracker
body: I really only got this app to track my food in terms of fat and sugar, not just calories, which it does really well. Good range of products to pick from, but I'm surprised at some that aren't already on there. I like you can save meals you make, bc I basically eat the same things every week. All around good app.

title: Changed my eating habits
body: Just got this app and it has already made me really look at what I'm putting in my body. I love that it gives you food alternatives and grades the food you eat. This is an awesome app and I highly recommend it to anyone trying to watch what their eating!!

title: Great app, needs bug fixes
body: I love the layout and form of the app. It's very useful and easy to figure out. The only problem is the fact that it keeps crashing. Every time I open it I have about 1 minute and it automatically goes black a shuts down. Should definitely get an update to fix that but.

title: Fooducate
body: Amazing! This product is easy to use, loads the product quickly, and displays all the information I need as well as expands details with links to learn more. It also provides 'alternatives' to help make better choices. It is everything I want!

title: Most important app in the world!
body: I wish iPhones were not so expensive because every human needs to start eating better. This app makes it clear and simple which products are healthier than another. It's a shame this app needs to be invented but I am grateful that it is. Great app!

title: Must share
body: I use this app all the time while shopping. It is easy to use and has helped me make better food decisions for my family. I have even had a few other savvy shoppers ask me what I was doing and I was happy to share with them this app and it's uses.

title: Great app! Easy to Use!
body: This app is great! Easy to use, highly informative and addicting. Once you start scanning you can't stop. It gives alternatives to help you make healthier choices as well as educates you about Ingredients (artificial flavorings, sweeteners, fats and  preservatives) they should have this is schools to teach kids!

title: Amazing
body: This app is incredible. It makes shopping and dieting so much easier. The food tips are awesome also!!!!! Keep up the good work. I'd like to see an upgrade that allows you to set a workout schedule with reminders for 7 days, and keep track of sets/reps and calculates progress, etc.

title: Love!
body: I absolutely love this app! It's great and really gives you great info not found on the nutrition label of so many foods. The only thing is that you can search meals that aren't packaged or sold in a supermarket and don't have a barcode. For example tuna roll with brown rice or tuna tacos.. But other than that it really is a great app!

title: Useful
body: I like this. It really breaks down the ingredients so you know exactly what you are eating. It had an extensive database, and they are good about adding things they don't have, if you submit a request.  Be warned, though - this will tell you that pretty much anything in a package isn't good for you (duh!).

title: Great App
body: I love this app!! It is easy to use, motivating and really helps to make some better food choices!! Recommending alternative food choices for things that don't rate well has lead me to some really great products that I formerly did not know about. I highly recommend!!!

title: Great but...
body: I think this app has a great concept however, the food I scan sometimes is not completely updated. For instance I scanned a bag of popcorn at Whole Foods, it had the GMO project verified stamp on the bag and Fooducate let me know that it has a High Probability of GMO.. Not true.. So whoever is in charge of food updating may need to be replaced lol.. Or you could contact and pay me to update it! Haha! Otherwise this app has a ton of potential!!!

title: Wonderful
body: I love this app!  It looks at more than calories which I love.  I would rate it a five if you were able to save frequent meals and they had generic foods to look up such as a hamburger or grilled chicken so if you ate at a local restaurant that wasn't listed you could still track what you ate even if you don't know the brand of the food.

title: Best Food App in the market
body: It's great to use at any time. I use it every time I go grocery shopping and even go through my kitchen and pantry at home scanning stuff I already have just to find out if there's anything better/healthier/new that I haven't discovered yet. A must have for any foodie! Download ASAP!!!

title: Love it
body: Love this app, I use it to track what I eat. Total calories, makes it easier to stay in a calorie range.  I really like the macronutrient ratio chart helps me stay in the correct ratios, I highly recommend this app if your looking into what you eat, how much you eat,  or your tracking cholesterol or high blood pressure this app can help if you work it.

title: Great App for keeping track and much more
body: Love that this not only keeps track of everything, but it also gives suggestions and provides relevant articles on nutritional information and issues.

title: Really helpful app
body: I really find this app to help me with what I eat during the day and keep me on track with getting to a healthy weight, the only thing is that I'm not too sure on how to submit products for them to check up on other than that, it's completely fine and extremely helpful.

title: Well done!
body: This app is very informative and well done. I could find most of the food products I buy through the scanner. That makes it so easy to know what you are actually eating. I feel I am much more in control of my food intake now.

title: Helping me lose weight little by little.
body: This app is amazing. I recommend it for anybody who is busy and can't workout like they want to. It sets your caloric intake for you and using the scanner it's easy to track your food. Absolutely worth the click!

title: Love this app!
body: I use this app anytime I make a trip to the grocery store! It definitely helps me make more informed decisions! A lot of things that I thought were healthy had a lot of no so obvious unhealthy factors. With this app, I can easily scan an item and make a better choice!

title: Really Great...except...
body: This is a wonderful resource for keep regular tabs on your health. I just wish it was a little easier to enter homemade dishes. It takes quite a while to try to get it logged accurately. The resources in this app are really wonderful as a whole - even when compared to all the competition out there now.

title: Love this app!
body: I feel like you can't trust a lot of food brands and labels these days and this app provides the truthful facts about the good and bad we're putting into our bodies. This app is helping me make better, healthier food and drink decisions to help me stay in shape and feel better throughout the day:)

title: Can't choose a different email client
body: With iOS 10, you can delete the default mail app and use a different client. I use Microsoft Outlook as my email client and no longer use the default mail client. When I try to contact customer support through the app or I want to add a new product to the database, I get an error saying I need to install the default email client. Please add the ability to choose your email client in the app settings. I know this is possible since I see other apps doing it.

title: Good guide
body: This app is great, very resourceful in the market. I live how we can help by submitting pictures of items not currently rated. I would like to be able to type in a product type and see a list of the healthiest products. Such as juice boxes an it bring up the healthiest kind of juice box.

title: Using with iPod 4
body: Pretty good program but scanning with iPod camera is hit or miss. It also seems to crash when trying to input the barcode manually. I'm hoping that's addressed in later updates.

title: Super useful and easy too!
body: Began using it today and I have been running around my house simply scanning things! I've been checking more than eating, ha! Super easy interface with awesome barcode scanner. Very easy to add info about products it does not currently have. 5 stars!

title: Great app
body: One of the best features is the scanning. Super quick and always works. Very helpful when in the story shopping for food. Also love that the app provides alternatives to what I scan that is healthier. Been recommending to everyone I know that cares about what they put into their bodies.

title: Great education, poor diet tracker.
body: It's really cool how you can scan bar codes to learn about your food and add it to your diet tracker!! I love all the info they have about foods. However, the actual diet tracking feature is awful! Can't control portion sizes well at all. Also it doesn't tell you how many of your calories came from protein, carbs, fat, etc. I prefer myfitnesspal. I wish the two could combine!!

title: Best food tracking app
body: Highly satisfied and love this interface + free scanner + tracking! Way better than Daily Burn which charges you $10/mo to use their scanner, ugh. I also love how every food has a grade and highlights relevant health info like GMO and how processed it is. This app is a gem. Thanks so much Fooducate!

title: I love it
body: I never go to the grocery store without using fooducate. Many of the items that are advertised as healthy, are really not. Fooducate breaks every food item down and informs you why it is not good for you. I also like that the app gives you healthy alternatives.

title: Awesome app
body: My aunt told me abt this app and I love it..I brought some veggie patties that I thought was vegan, when I scanned the patties the app let me know it was not vegan..even though it was in the same place as the vegan products..I was so happy that I had this app to scan the product..thanks a lot..will refer this to more people..

title: Excellent App---where to buy feature?!
body: Love the app, I have learned so much more about healthy choices and it's always with me. Would love to see, however, a built-in "where to buy" feature. Constantly searching the web isn't always practical!

title: Very Helpful
body: All I can give is my personal experience. And one thing about this app that is really good is that it has you list everything you ate and drank each day. And it's one thing to know you ate a lot, but another to eat a lot AND THEN have to report it all. (Added motivator)

title: Grades are misleading
body: This app is a great idea, BUT the grades are inaccurate or at least misleading. I scanned dozens of things in my kitchen. Some of the products' grades made sense (e.g., potato chips got a C-). But others were downright nonsensical (e.g., plain old fashioned oatmeal only got a B+ and OJ got a C+... I'm sorry, but WHAT?!?!). I consider myself to be a rather informed individual when it comes to healthy eating, and this app's grading scheme made no sense about 1/3 of the time. You're better off learning how to read and understand labels yourself.

title: Offers useful insights and alternatives
body: As another reviewer put it, if you just curious about what you eat, but are not going to make changes to how you eat with the useful information provided by the app then the app is not worth it. If otherwise, then download now.

title: Fun, useful guide
body: I'm having so much fun using this app! My husband and I had a heated debate about the quality of our preferred English muffins. Mine, at b+ was the winner while my husband's got b-. I have scanned pretty much everything in my fridge and pantry and it's reassuring to know we're generally eating As and Bs. Except for my beloved cheeto puffs, they are a D :(

title: Learning how to use this app
body: Just started using this, so far I like it. I'm trying to figure out how to tell it about calories I've burned.

title: Great app with a great Watch extension.
body: I really like this app for tracking calories. I can now use the watch to enter calories from a meal I just ate witch is nice. I also like how I can see what I have eaten and how much I have left. The app has also helped me pick out better foods at the store.

title: Great app to track food intake
body: It is great and there are additional pay option for more in depth features. But the free portion is great and is simple to use and keep track of daily in take. Library of items you can track is fast and vast. I'm liking it so far.

title: Not too shabby.
body: The fact that this app gives you a grade on how healthy your food, I love. It helps me to be more aware and make better choices. I do wish tho that they would provide more personalization without having to paying for premium, but of course I'm also just cheap so it depends on the person.

title: Easy to use, simple
body: Love this app. Easy to use and log in food, water, and exercise. You can save meals that you eat often. I enjoy the articles and love reading about all the weird ingredients in food. All the foods are rated, too. I don't care for all the comments people write, just not my thing, so I just don't read those.

title: Fantastic
body: I really like this because they don't just throw out a grade they also tell you why. Informed people make better choices. Doesn't mean I won't eat something with a C grade but at least I know where I stand and maybe make a better choice elsewhere

title: Pretty good
body: Seems like the points system is close to weight watchers but a little under. I also wish the food came with descriptions and options to add or omit certain items to get an accurate count of calories. Annnnd if there was a feature that said you have xx amount of calories left, you can eat these options for dinner.. would be super helpful.

title: Good for grocery store purchases
body: Easy to use, scanning is fast, extensive database, very very helpful to have products graded A-F and explanation of why, and helpful to know a product is one of the top rated in its category. Would be even better if it included restaurant food, but still a 5-star app.

title: Better than Weight Watchers!
body: Love this app! I am a lifetime WW member and got bored and tired of entering points every day. I also got tired of eating the same foods but didn't know what else  to try.

title: FAVORITE APP
body: This app has everything every good diet app has and more. You can learn more about what you eat so you can make healthier decisions and you can log food, exercise, and more! I recommend this app to all my friends and I use it AT LEAST three times a day minimum! No complaints whatsoever!!!

title: Fooducate
body: Wonderful app! Accurate, reliable, easy to use. The only thing I would change is that they seem a bit slow with adding new food to their catalog. But they do make progress with it. Customer support is great, over all it gets 5 stars.

title: Love it!
body: I've always maintained a healthy lifestyle, and have lived by the motto: everything in moderation. I still live by that motto, but now I can do an even better job of gauging my moderation. I love this app, and I especially like the feature that allows me to send an unknown product to fooducate to add to the database.

title: Great product would love more
body: I havent tried the track diet part since im using the myfitnesspal app. However the food ratings part is amazingly easy to use and has immediate access to information thats otherwise hard to find. I would like ratings for more products though, hence the 4 stars

title: Unimpressed! Will no longer recommend!
body: This "improvement" took out all the GMO info, vegetarian info etc. and made them subscriptions.

title: Awesome App!
body: With all the food allergies I have this app is awesome at helping me navigate through the grocery stores. I scan an item and the app lets me know if any of my allergies are in the item. Love love love this app!  Also love the tips and info sent out everyday.  Thanks for the hard work placed in this app!

title: Liked it before but now you have to pay so much
body: I bought this app originally for $5.99 I think it was. Loved it then. One of the best things about it and why I chose this app was because of the GMO checking. Well, I had a hiatus with a samsung phone, came back to iOS and now you have to pay through the nose for every little thing! Disappointed.  I think I'll just go back to MyFitnessPal it's basically the same thing.

title: This app is a wake up call
body: Amazing app that is helping me so much. I have tried a bunch of stuff to lose weight. They worked but this one is so much easier to use and I love the alternative options it gives you. I 100% recommend it!

title: Great program for eating better
body: My wife & I have recently started wanting to eat better, and Fooducate has been a huge help in letting us know what's healthy and what's not. It's amazing how things that we thought would be healthy actually aren't.  So glad we found this app.

title: Awesomeness!!!!
body: As a busy mom who makes food for a living, I am always trying to find something to help me save time and stay healthy. this app is AMAZING!!!! The food grade that each item receives was a true eye opener for some things! Great job!!!!! Keep up the good work. I am encouraging all of my chefs peers to use the same app.

title: Love!
body: I love this app! It is my absolute favorite, I use it all the time! There are a few items I've scanned that are not in the system, however I submit the 3 required pictures they need to add the item in the collection. So please do the same so we can all help this application grow! I would recommend it to anyone. It's a must have!

title: Very helpfully when trying to choose!
body: This app is so helpful when you're not quite sure if something is really healthy or when you're stuck between products. Labels can be deceiving, and this food app lays out the good and bad about products.

title: Must have this when grocery shopping!!!
body: Awesome app!  Helps you to make better food choices and know more about what you're eating. Not only gives food a grade but also explains why it got the grade it did.  I highly recommend this app.

title: Great app, but it keeps crashing
body: I got this app a while ago, but now when I'm using it most, its harder to use. Sadly, I can't go much further than scanning and alternatives without it crashing when I want to see the product details. Also, what happened to the "compare" option? That was so helpful. If these problems were fixed it would be a fantastic app.

title: Answer to my prayers
body: I am morbidly obese and want to lose weight.  Unfortunately, all the doctors do is send me to Bariatric Surgery. I would really like to do the weight lost the old-fashioned way-with diet and exercise. However, I didn't know what was wrong with my diet and this app told me what I need to know.

title: Love it! User friendly!
body: Assuming the science behind the app is accurate, I love this app! The barcode scanner is a game changer. I have used it so many times at the grocery store to help stir me in the right direction so I 1) limit the unhealthy things I buy 2) look for alternatives the app recommends. Very helpful!

title: Needs to Integrate With other Apps
body: I just downloaded this app and was considering switching from my fitness pal, but upon discovering it doesn't even import steps from Apple health or Runkeeper - I'm over it before I even had a chance to get started. It appears as though it should be pulling the steps/workouts in, but it's not. It's a shame because I was really excited about the food grades, but I don't have time to do multiple inputs.

title: I've had more fun
body: With this app! I literally wandered around my grocery store comparing things I eat. Next thing I knew it was 2-1/2 hours later. No kidding. I learn a lot every time I use this. I took a hiatus, came back and enjoyed it even more. I highly recommend for nerds and thinkers!

title: Pretty useful
body: Great app. It's helping a lot on my weight loss journey, but some of the foods I eat (which are pretty basic/common) aren't found in their list of options. So I have to go through a little bit more to add my own food and find out all the nutritional info.

title: Eye opener
body: I love this application. It has been an eye opener to go grocery shopping and comparing products to make a decision. I am trying to eat a clean diet and this had been amazing! It has it's limitation that I hope gets fixed, but there is nothing like this out there and regardless, it's amazing!

title: Excellent!!
body: This is my favorite app to date. It gives me accurate and reliable information to help me make better food choices. I find it to be very informative and up to date. A must have app for those serious about eating better.

title: Very nice app!
body: I really like this app. Very comprehensive list of items on the market. This is great for weight loss or maintenance. Only downfall is that it is difficult if you make your own meals. You can put it in the system but I have no idea how many calories are in what I made, not the fat or carb percentages. Still love the app and use it all the time!

title: Love this app!!!
body: I was trying to lose weight with Weight Watchers on my own, but was lying to myself about portion control. With the UPC scanner and database of food items, I can accurately track what I am actually eating or drinking. Thank you for all your hard work to create this app!

title: Fantastic App!
body: This app is wonderful if you want to track what you eat in a day! I had no problem learning it and I am amazed at its features. I highly recommend it if you are trying to lose weight or just trying to eat healthier!

title: Useful
body: Wonderful app, does a great job of explaining which foods are processed and why. Also love the recommendation/ alternatives the app provides. Can be a little too harsh on some foods. Wish it could provide feedback on supplements. Overall, a great app to help choose which foods to buy and why. Fast and easy to use. Definitely Worth downloading.

title: Love the app
body: I love the app. As a nursing mom I was put on a dairy restriction for my child. This app has saved me so much time and worry about whether I am eating things that could adversely affect my newborn. This is the second child I've had a dietary restriction and chose to use the this app through. Love it.

title: Very helpful and informative app
body: I've tried other apps like my fitness pal and I find fooducate tons more useful. From the first day tracking my meals and ex resize I was completely wowed. It helps to have an app like this especially for someone who has struggled with weight all of their life. It makes it easier to chose the foods you need.

title: Balance
body: This is exactly what I need to track and balance my macro nutrients.   After one week, I am better at eating the right balance of carbs/protein/fat.  The food grades are good guideposts, and I find them motivational.   Eating healthy isn't easy, however this app makes it easier.

title: Love this app
body: While not everything is on here it's nice to know there is an app that works like thus I've been trying to lose weight and I love getting to know what is healthy and why!!! This app not only tells you what is healthy but also educates you!!! Nice app I would have paid for it!

title: My most used app
body: Very handy to have in the grocery store. Helps with WW points info. I point it at everything because even if you know An item is good the app has extra info and alternatives if you just want to try something different.

title: Impressive...
body: Most impressive :)

title: Easy to make informed eating choices!
body: What a handy app. I like to make healthy food choices but sometimes the time it takes to thoroughly read labels and ingredients lists' makes eating healthy a daunting task. With Fooducate I can now can make my food choices at lightning fast speed! Thank you!

title: When you don't believe the hype, come here for the real story
body: I have found this helpful to eliminate and make better choices.  The only thing that would make this better is to ad prices next to items so you can balance health and wealth.

title: Insanely helpful.
body: I have recently become more aware about what I should and shouldn't be eating to maintain a healthy lifestyle. The trouble for health newcomers like me, however, is learning how to decipher nutrition labels. This app makes it super simple to learn more about a food item before it goes into your cart.

title: Ssgglg
body: I have looked at different sites to find out with medications I take If I can eat grapefruit. This site will give you the answer.

title: This app will make you smarter
body: This app will make you smarter about your food choices. You will at least have a better idea about how to get better food in your body. The explanations are clear and I really like the option to see alternatives.

title: Love this app!!
body: Much better than WW! If you scan something and they don't have it - they add it for you and it goes into their database for everyone to use.  They keep adding features - I highly recommend this app !  I've list over 22 lbs (lowest I've been in 9 years)

title: Great Tool
body: This app is very useful in helping you make smarter food choices. Food choices that I thought were healthy, weren't! It makes me think twice about some of my eating choices because I can see those decisions right on my phone. I haven't used it in the grocery store yet, but am looking forward to it.

title: Amazing, but could use an improvement
body: I think this is a great app! It shows very basically if it's the best option. But I do think it should include the nutritional facts overview.
