And as far as the apple comment, the apples have a barcode on the price sticker next to the pile of produce; or you can look up the particular type of apple online.

title: Pro version is worth it
body: Got the 12 month subscription and there are soooo many more features that are all genuinely useful. You can tailor food grading to your specific needs, like if you want to go vegan or are trying to watch carb intake, etc.

title: Addicted to this app!
body: I used to use another calorie counting app. But I have completely ditched it now to be fooducated! I probably look like a crazy person walking around scanning everything at the grocery store, but I never wanna make an unfooducated decision again!

title: Easy and convenient
body: My have used several of these types of programs.  It is not the best for reporting, but it is extremely quick and easy to get data inputed into the program. Recommend it highly.

title: The best shopping assistant
body: I used the app the other day at the groceries store, and it was much easier than go trough the Nutrition facts or ingredients. Also by using the scanner you see the true "healthy facts" of what you are buying. A must have for every organic and healthy freak like me!

title: Grades Food!
body: So not just counting calories or fat, carbs, but grades each good item- and not by FDA standards which are subpar! Graded by true actual food vs nonfood stuff, GMO, artificial crud, preservatives, and so forth. What a surprise for a few things I thought were healthy! Great app! My only downside is it is not as smooth as some others I've used. Well worth the upgrade though.

title: Good tool for losing weight
body: I have been using this app for a few weeks because I need to track carbs and lose weight.  I have lost 4lbs so far.  It is easy to use - most foods I eat are already entered by other users.  I recommend it.

title: Great App to Watch What You Eat!!!
body: This app is awesome!!! While grocery shopping you can just scan your products and figure out how good/bad they are for you. It hasn't been glitchy and seems to have almost every product I scan!!! Love this app!!!

title: Know what you are eating!
body: Best app out there.  If you care what you're eating or are looking for a healthy alternative this is the app for you.  Track you food?  Easy!  Track your exercise? Easy?  Track you're weight loss? Easy?  I've tried them all.

title: Awful
body: This app used to be great but now it's really bad (were they bought by someone else?). Much slower than it was. Several foods and especially supplements were removed. Even when you input your own stuff it is very limited as to what you can add, just the basics. Used to have more options for adding additional vitamins etc. Too bad, the rating system is about the only thing useful in this anymore. And I'm not sure that alone is enough to continue to use.

title: Love the health tracker
body: I love that a health tracker was added in the recent update, I'd like to see this expanded to show more then just calorie and carb intake.  I would find it more beneficial to be able to keep track of the nutrients I'm taking in, and would like to have an app that shows a breakdown of the different vitamins and nutrients that have been consumed.

title: Easy to use and informative
body: I like that you can submit foods for their data bank. I've mostly noticed that it's store brand foods they don't have, or maybe it's just the stores in my area but I can usually find something comparable for now.

title: Opinion and criticism
body: It's a very fun and interactive app to use when you want to monitor your food. It's very simple and easy to use for all ages! The only criticism I have is they should allow people over the age of 15 because many teens struggle with loosing weight and this I believe would be a good app for those who want to loose weight.

title: Great resource!!
body: There are a lot of new organic products that do not compute. But if we keep sending them in they will get around to getting them on!! They have done a great job and its getting better. I rely on Fooducate more and more.. I'm surprised I have not been thrown out of the market..

title: This is a Helpful App
body: I'm really enjoying this app.  It's hard trying to keep track of what you eat on a daily basis, but this app makes it "fun" to keep track of what you eat.  It really helps to keep you motivated to begin to eat healthier and get out and exercise more.

title: Great reminder
body: This app is a great way to find not only the best foods to eat, but the healthiest brands of each particular food. I like that it puts an emphasis on real and whole foods. This app isn't perfect, but it's a wonderful tool to have and will certainly help you plan a more successful shopping trip.

title: MUST HAVE app for Weight Watchers!
body: Food shopping is easier now! Instead of pulling out my calculator each time and punching in everything, I just scan the barcode. Much faster! Plus, there's all kinds of other health info you get besides points. Love this app!

title: Excellent for keeping track of food intake!
body: It scans almost every product and is really helpful for seeing how many calories you're consuming daily. I just wish it kept a count on protein! Other than that I am thoroughly impressed.

title: Use this one all the time.
body: I find myself making better choices with this app and surprised that items I thought were good picks might have better alternatives.   It has a wide range too and I use the food tracker to help with my intake as well.

title: Needs lots of work
body: Good n bad

title: Wow!
body: I am blown away by how awesome this app is. Visually pleasing and extraordinarily useful. And free!! As someone else mentioned I can't stop scanning things in my house and I've already learned so much. Great concept, great execution. Beautiful. All apps should work this well, look so nice and provide this much information. Bravo!

title: Good features
body: I love this product. I use it almost everyday because it makes shopping easier. Since I got the app, I have been scanning items in my food storage. This app works wonders!!!

title: Just about the best app ever!
body: This app is amazing for what it does. The only thing that would be better would be if they merged the Fooducate and LoseIt apps together and you could scan in foods to a weight-loss log. But they would have to use the Fooducate database because the LoseIt database is worse.

title: MUST HAVE app for Weight Watchers!
body: Food shopping is easier now! Instead of pulling out my calculator each time and punching in everything, I just scan the barcode. Much faster! Plus, there's all kinds of other health info you get besides points. Love this app!

title: LOVE this app!
body: After I scanned a couple of items in my pantry and found put how unhealthy they were, several people on my family immediately downloaded this app! Indispensable tool for grocery shopping and provides great nutritional "food for thought". LOVE this app!

title: Grocery Shopping Secret Weapon
body: This is by far the best app I have ever used for grocery shopping. You would be surprised how many food products pass themselves as healthy eating. Great for finding those little known healthier alternatives to foods you already love. An extremely beneficial tool for dieting.

title: Dieters dream!
body: For a busy family on the go, this has been a huge time saver for shopping and making better food choices.  Love the color coded food "grades", makes it a no-brainier explaining to my kids why we choose one product over another!

title: Perfect!!
body: I am currently studying to become a registered dietitian and like to think I know a lot about what's in a lot of food items. This app provides information about each food item that I never knew and I love it!! I love learning through this app!

title: Nice app for watching your food intake
body: This app has helped me focus on what I'm putting in my body. Great list of foods, though more focused on prepackaged food.

title: Best health app out there. . . .
body: I used the free version for I few weeks and it was amazing.  I didn't really think it could get much better, but the paid version actually is better. Definitely would recommend this app.

title: Eye opener!
body: This app REALLY made me think about the things im putting into me and my boyfriends bodies! (I do all the cooking) i love how informative the app is and how it really breaks the ingredients down even to how they are made! I was so interested that this has been the ONLY app i have ever paid for EVER I cant wait to see how this changes my eating habits for the better. :)

title: Must have app
body: I cannot eat food without having this app. It scans almost every food item with a barcode and tells you if it's healthy or not. Great for people who not only diet but want to know exactly all the chemicals in your food

title: Awesome app!!!!
body: I like the app. I found that I didn't use it as much as I thought I would. Logging in everything was kind of a pain. But if your glued to your phone already then there should be no problem.  I'm still looking for the A list foods. What I thought was healthy like raisins were given a C. All in all it's a great app.

title: I'm sold!
body: I was a hard sell when first looking at this app as I have used WW in the past and wasn't sure if anything out there was any better... But I'm sold! This is a great app full of solid information. If you use this consistently you will drop the pounds!

title: Kickstart eating better
body: A friend referred this app to me and I love it! It's a great way to begin seeing processed food and real food differently. I'm changing what I buy in the grocery store based on discovering that some of the food I thought was "healthy" isn't all it's claims are cracked up to being. It's a good start to a reality check before diving deeper into nutrition.

title: It's pretty good.
body: I am paying the monthly premium because I want to see the perks. The GMO information is nice and it's great to see a break down of my meals and what I should be targeting for in terms of iron and calcium etc.

title: Super easy to use!
body: Great app, already has helped me in making better food choices. Found it easier to use than other apps and I really like that it shows you what percentage of your diet is processed foods or added sugars, etc.

title: Really helps and is addictive üòä
body: I really like this app. We are trying to eat more healthy and my kids and I have been having fun scanning food to see its grade. My husband has been skeptical about it but now he looks for the grades that I write on the food :)

title: Great App!
body: I have used this app for about a year now and really like it. I wish under Restaurants we could just type in the name and it would bring up a menu we could click on. Other then that I recommend it.

title: Love it
body: I would give this app 10 stars if I could. It makes keeping up with calories easy. It also, if you are honest with yourself, makes you aware of how many calories you are ACTUALLY consuming versus how many you THINK you are eating.

title: Only one problem with the app....
body: My whole family loves this app! The only problem is when you have a product that does not get picked up from the scan the app makes you do extra work like, taking a pic of the product and nutritional label, to get nutritional information, but they never once ever told me the results of the products I scanned.

title: Perfect for the health conscious shopper!
body: I love this app! Once I downloaded it I was scanning everything in sight to see how the foods I usually buy rate. I was very surprised on some and have now taken steps to buy and prepare better food choices for my family. Thank you for such an ingenious app!

title: Great in theory
body: I used to really like this app; after not using it for a couple of months and an apparent upgrade, it remains frozen on the loading screen. I have turned off my phone, exited out of the app multiple times, and patiently waited, to no avail.

title: Love it!
body: I found myself scanning everything in my kitchen and I've told all of my friends. This is an app that you really need to have. It is so helpful in making better & healthier food choices. Depending on our choices, food can cure us or kill us!

title: Perfect
body: Quick and easy to use at home or in a store. Shortens time reading confusing labels and lays all out all information you could possibly want to know about the product, even warns you when a product may be made with GMO's.

title: Good, but would like to see more facts
body: When using the health tracker, at the end of the day it would be nice if it had a list of all the nutrient percentages so you can know how much or how little you consumed. Right now it just has your bare minimum of carbs, fat, calories, and protein. I would like to see more details, such as calcium, iron, fiber, and so on.

title: Multiple ratings for same product
body: I was looking up the rating for Krave Chocolate cereal and was pleasantly surprised at the B- rating. I proceeded to read the review on it and was confused to see a screenshot showing a lower rating. So I conducted a second search and noticed 5 different reviews of the same product with 3 different ratings ranging from B- to C-. Makes you question the reliability of the ratings.

title: The most effective fitness app.
body: To make changes in your fitness level you really have to know what you're eating. This app takes a lot of guesswork out of your questionable food items and is hard proof for people who try to live in denial.

title: Amazing
body: I use this app daily! I scan everything now. It's definitely helped me to rethink what I'm eating and drinking and has helped me to discover new foods and brands of food.  Love that you can submit new finds and they will add what you send in to their database. The scan contests are fun too.

title: For Beginner and Seasoned Food Trackers
body: This app is great! Fairly easy to learn and start using quickly. I do get a bit aggravated when I can't find a specific food or my foods won't scan. Hopefully, the ones I've sent in for Fooducate to enter into the system will be in there soon. I do believe it's worth the money, though.

title: Fantastic Application
body: This is a wonderful and informative app.  I downloaded it last night and have already told three people about it. I agree that the scanning is addictive, but it's worth it in that you may be surprised as to what you find.  Great work on this app!!!

title: Excellent resource
body: This has really helped me make better choices, before I buy. I love the alternatives tab, the warnings, and the fact that the database has almost everything I've scanned. It is also very easy to submit new products.

title: Fudulove it!
body: Use it all the time while shopping. Very handy app.. You don't have to spend so much time studying the labels just scan the product and if you don't like what you're scanning look at the alternatives the app is recommending instead. Great feature!

title: Fantastic app
body: This is exactly what apps are made for! Organized, useful information that is easy to access and helpful to the goal of eating right. My only qualm is that products with artificial sweetners receive high health grades, and I find that questionable. But I know the research there is inconclusive, so one can't complain too much. Thank you for a great app!

title: I LOVE IT.
body: It's definitely my FAVORITE app! It's such a fantasic idea and it really helps you eat healthier. You think certain products are healthy because they are  advertised to seem like it, but once you use Fooducate you realize it's not so the app gives you healthier alternatives. I'm so suprised this app is FREE!

title: Wow!
body: Well, I have only had this app for five minutes and have scanned my whole kitchen!!  So easy, so cool and so informative. This is going to be my go-to when making food decisions in the store. (I already have made a few changes to my shopping list)

title: Necessary App
body: If you are serious about what you put into your mouth, then get this app and scan everything in your pantry. It gives you info, research to back that info up, an alternatives available. If you want to be healthy, download this.

title: So helpful!
body: I try to feed my family the healthiest options and this app helps SO MUCH! I love being able to look up an item and see what's in it or the next best choice. I've already made several changes to our weekly grocery trips!

title: Good for the whole fam!
body: I love it ! The one thing I wish it has was were you could find the possible better choices.  (what stores might carry them)

title: Very informative
body: I don't know where they get their information or how accurate it really is, but the app gives tons of interesting info that cannot be found on labels. I watch what my family eats and stay quite informed, but this app has taught me a lot!

title: Amazing and High impact
body: Fantastic app that provides plain English nutrition information and even provides suggestions for healthy alternatives within the same product category. This app has the capacity to improve public health and nutrition and is fun and very easy to use.

title: Recent updates lowered quality
body: I have the iPhone 6 plus, and recent Fooducate updates resulted in a super tiny font making the app difficult to see. I emailed them directly about this nearly two months ago and was reassured they are working in it. Database is still lacking. I'm a premium member and don't feel like it is worth paying for.

title: Love it!!
body: While this app doesn't have every food item known to man it does have a lot! My boyfriend and I just scanned every item in our house anything that was rated below a B was tossed. This app not only rates the items but explains how it was rated. Very helpful learning tool!

title: Life Changing
body: This app has helped me overcome so many bad habits, negative thoughts, and terrible choices. I now know how to eat healthy-eat the food my body deserves, and I've become so committed to this new healthy life of mine. Fooducate gave me such a great foundation and knowledge about how to perpetuate all of this! best app ever invented

title: Fun and easy to use
body: I enjoy using this so I can challenging myself to eat better. The scanner part is very  helpful and makes things super easy. I also like that it does the calories consumed vs calories expended and puts it in an easy to understand summary.

title: Great app
body: Great app. Really like the Food grades and points, as well as the detailed info and the substitutes.

title: The Greatest Out There
body: I've used just about every free health&fitness app on the market and this one tops the rest. Its helping me track what's beyond my calorie intake by giving me an EXTENSIVE evaluation on the foods I eat and what's in it. The features are easy to use and enjoyable and the community is supportive ^_^

title: Helpful and good experience
body: Tried another app before with nice results however this one seems to be one of top ones around. It needs little improvement to the meal/food search and addition to meals. Also it would be great to be able to list foods that scored most for carbs, fat and protein. Very good app indeed.

title: Keeps crashing
body: The app looks great, and I really want to use it, but it won't even open. It keeps crashing. Quite upsetting, I'm hoping this can be fixed so I can use the app

title: Best app to eat healthy
body: This app is great for checking if food is healthy or not. It shows you the the things that aren't required to be listed but are very harmful for you. Best way to compare food to see what's healthier. Also has good tips and alternatives for eating healthy.

title: Best App Ever!!
body: I use this app daily! This app changed my  life. I now see what really is in the things I/we eat. I changed my habits and made new ones. I tell everyone I know to download. They are shocked when they scan their supposedly "healthy" things they like.

title: Fooducate Rocks!!!
body: This is a great app to help you make healthy food choices. An app that breaks down the nutritional facts and gives you a heads up on unknown or very highly processed ingredients used in foods. The grading chart is easy to read and use as well, especially with the foods that are advertised the

title: "Log my meals"?!
body: I haven't upgraded from the Fooducate app/name because I don't care about losing weight - I care about a quick way to compare options at the grocery store. Yet I still get a notification to "Please log your meals. Even a few is fine." ...EVEN A FEW IS FINE?! Uninstall. You've got to be kidding me. A meal logger is a great option for those doing so to lose weight (or track food's effect on a health problem), but that notification out of the blue is just encouraging disordered eating. F you.

Not to crazy about this app. Seems that everything that I eat is not available. I like that you can send the app the nutrition info but, it take a long time for them to put the information in. I would like to see the app updated with the ability to put in our on nutrition information for it to be more convenient.

title: Love it
body: Still learning the ropes. But so far so good. Learned a lot in one day about the foods I've been eating. I wish I could list the ingredients to my own recipes and then have it do the calories and grading for me but that's ok, it's giving me a chance to brush up on my math skills.

title: Helping me with willpower
body: I've only been utilizing this for 2 1/2 days so far. However, I've not been extremely successful, but this is showing me how to improve each day. I suggest you try it at least, then decide for yourself.

title: Cool app!
body: I really enjoy using this app. It's about time we have something that gives us some decent info about the food we eat. I like the way it gives us alternatives to the products we buy.

title: Great for learning about nutrition.
body: I have used the scanner to compare and make better, well-informed choices about which foods are more nutritious. I read all the daily tips and am becoming much more educated about food and nutrition related issues.

title: A must-have...
body: A user-friendly way to quickly identify healthier foods, and to easily track food intake as well as overall body health - this is definitely one of my most functional, and certainly most used, apps. Indispensable.

title: Terrific information in this app
body: Fooducate is great app to help me choose what better foods to buy.

title: Very Informative!!!
body: I really enjoyed this app, and it's completely free!!!! It gives you a different viewpoint on the foods that you eat. I was surprised about some of the reviews (Oreos were given a C, which is high I'm my opinion), but it's still really cool how they break down why they think a food I healthy or not. Overall, Great app for extra nutritional help!

title: Very useful app
body: I use it often when I have to pick a product and I have some doubts about it's healthiness, and in most cases I put it back on the shelf. It is also a way to build healthy eating habits if you are ready to give up some 'good' (in taste only) food.

title: Excellent!
body: This app is awesome! I've even wrote them an email and the responded and updated with my suggestion. Love apps that get updated and developers that listen! This app is a very handy tool to bring shopping or to check food you already have in your home. Super cool!! Works great!!

title: Loving this app!
body: I just downloaded yesterday and haven't even been to the grocery store. I'm just enjoying checking out the food I have at home. I've already made one change for the next time I buy food. I love the "alternative" feature. Great app!

title: Fabulous!
body: This app has been super helpful to get a better idea of what I am consuming and the explanations are relatable and meaningful.  My only recommendation would be to add a feature to track daily food intake, like the map my run app has.  It would be helpful to have all of that information in the same place.

title: Great free app
body: This is a great app to allow you to take a closer look at your food choices and then make better choices if you need to. Only had a few items I scanned that weren't in their database but overall really easy and useful.

title: Love this app
body: It is my "go to" for quick checks on food products. I appreciate the information, education and the fact that it is always accurate for plus points in the weight watchers program.

title: Great idea/format
body: Very useful, it definitely gets you excited to research and eat better right away. I've adjusted what I shop for and consume now. The format and information are perfect. I have my friends and family hooked to this now too!

title: 1st app to meet all my needs!
body: Thanks you. You have created a well executed program that is functional and has everything I need.

title: Mom
body: I love that this app gives me alternative choices. I can make small changes and be healthier. I had no idea some of the things I was eating were full of sugar and/or GMO's. The cottage cheese I was eating was one of the worst in its category. I switched brands and I actually like the taste better! Love this app!

title: Versatility abounds
body: Wow, I have been looking for this type of information for a long time! I am still getting used to it, but I appreciate how comprehensive the information is!

title: Amazing
body: I use this app daily! I scan everything now. It's definitely helped me to rethink what I'm eating and drinking and has helped me to discover new foods and brands of food.  Love that you can submit new finds and they will add what you send in to their database. The scan contests are fun too.

title: Informative
body: This app is a great choice for people who want to make smart choices about the food they buy but don't have time to waste reading ingredient lists. I love it, it has shaved time off of my shopping trips that I can use to do other things.....like review apps!

title: Fabulous and Easy
body: I love the scanner and the grading system.  It makes healthy food choices easy.  It is also a great value for being able to make it so personalized.  I am recommending it to everyone I know and they are switching apps.

title: Awesome info and articles
body: Articles are fun to read as they have a lot of personality in them. By that I mean the writers use funny and strong and sometimes exaggerated words to describe everything but in a good way that makes you want to keep reading

title: Fooducate
body: Great app!  I use it to track my food. I've lost 25 lbs with no exercise. Had foot surgery and haven't been able to bear weight on it for 21/2 months therefore unable to exercise. I also love the daily tips and articles. Have learned so much!!  5 stars from me!

title: Nothing like it!
body: I can't tell you how many food items I was about to put in the cart when I remembered to swipe the barcode and put it right back on the shelf. I love the way it explains the letter grade. Fooducate makes it so much easier to eat healthier. Love it!

title: I LOVE this app!
body: This app really makes life easier when it comes to comparing healthy foods, really looking at what's in their ingredients, and this app even gives you alternatives to foods/brands that have subpar ratings. I highly recommend. I use it every day now!

title: Fantastic app!!
body: It's hard to know which products are actually good for you when you're flooded with so many options at the grocery store.  This app simplifies that confusion so I could make better, more healthy decisions.  Must have!!!!

title: AMAZING
body: Best thing I've ever done! Yiu just scan the barcode of the product and boom it gives you the rating (a-f) and based on your gender, height, weight, and age it gives you an accurate amount of calories, sugars, etc. you should be intaking! This tracks exercise too!!

title: Tell me the truth, I can handle it!
body: Excellent App. Simple to use. Very educational. Gives me the real data, that helps me buy the good and healthy food. It goes beyond the lable scanning. Feels like you have your personal advised with you all the time.

title: An App that I can't do without!
body: I initially downloaded this app to confirm that I've been eating healthy. I was surprised to find how many preservatives (artificial) were in the food I was feeding my family!

title: Trifecta!
body: I use this app in tandem with LoseIt and iMuscle for losing wait and getting fit. What I love about this app is that it gives me an idea of what exactly is going into my body. The healthier alternatives that appear in the same category of what I scan is probably my favorite feature.

title: Registration shows Tracking
body: What is with these programs saying Apple changed their policy so now you have to register with your email, etc.!  So they quietly tracked us before Apple respected "some" of our privacy, and now apps can't freely track like they did in the past?!  Their paid version has not updated to the registration version YET.  Perhaps this company wants to see how offended users of this program are before requiring it in the Plus version.  Let them know!!!

title: Love but weird people on comments
body: Love this app! Has so many foods on list. The points match up to weight watchers, at least from what I have used.

title: Fooducate
body: I like how this app grades each item, but a little more info on why it received the grade would be nice. My favorite thing about the app is the alternative suggestions! You can easily spend an hour in a store scanning everything...addicting!

title: Helpful app
body: A quick and easy way to learn more about what you're eating.  it gives you the rationale of why foods earn any given rating and it also offers helpful alternatives.  It also lets you know if something is vegetarian or vegan.

title: Great app to help with food choice
body: Perfect for anyone who's trying to take their health and food choice more seriously. Lets you know why a product is healthy or unhealthy and gives great alternatives. Not too wordy with the explanations, so there's no chance I feeling overwhelmed with scientific vocab

title: Some changes would help
body: This App is helping me to stay on track.  Very helpful tips.  I would like to see you add a recipe calculator.  I would also like to be able to delete things from my food list because scrolling through everything is time consuming.

title: Easy
body: This is a great app that is very easy to use and navigate. The scanning feature makes it so easy to input the food you eat and if it's not on file the auto update email feature makes it easy to add new items.

title: Love love love this app
body: Very useful in being able to scan products and then get back info about it and if product isn't as healthy as u thought it gives you other suggestions for healthier foods and snacks.  Live it. It's a must have!!!!

title: Good app, approaching greatness
body: The app works great. The only thing holding it back is the speed at which new products are added. They are quick, but due to regional products you may have to give them a hand and photograph some products for them.

title: Nutritionist at my fingertips!!
body: Love this app!! It helps me to make better food choices and informs me of the nutritional facts of my grocery store purchases. If I run across several healthy products and want to pick the most nutritional, this app does just that!! Highly recommend!!

title: Perfect!
body: It's better than I thought it would be. It changed my mom from buying an expensive cereal, thinking its healthy, and I showed her this app and she switched to a healthier cereal that was also cheap. She's so happy saving so much money every other week.

title: Love it!
body: This is a great app!  It helps me see how some "healthy" choices aren't really that healthy. My grocery trips take longer because I want scan everything. Actually, I've started buying food without labels more often now!

title: I Love this App !!
body: I have struggled with my weight all of my life. I found this App yesterday while searching the App Store. I got so Excited !! It interacts with my Health App on my iPhone 6 and it holds me accountable. I needed that !! I love the daily tips, restaurant guide...etc. This App is a "Necessary" aid in my weight loss journey !!

title: Supportive
body: Some people say this app is for 18 years and older but I say it's for 9+! It's an awesome app with a supportive community but some people are too up tight! They say oh no your tooooo young. Well we're not for your info! And if you stick to eating healthy this app can really help you!

title: Love this so far!
body: Really like this app so far! I always thought I are relatively healthy--not the case. I recently ha a baby and wanted to get some baby weight off. I started using this app in conjunction with a running app for exercise. Working well so far!! I'll keep with it!

title: Great way to steer your eating on the right track
body: Fooducate is unique to all the other dieting/food tracking apps I've used. It grades each item of food you enter, gives an explanation for why that grade, and offers better alternatives.

title: Weight loss tool
body: It's not the prettiest one but it has a lot of features I didn't know I wanted. Entries are easy to edit when put in incorrectly. It is nice to see pictures of the food that I have entered. When I emailed them for support, they responded quickly. Its nice that one can subscribe  monthly, annually or buy it for $75.

title: Love this app!
body: It is very informative. I am learning a lot about foods, some things are not that pretty. You really are educated about the food you eat and it is also a calorie diary and weight loss helper. Love it. I use it daily and I'm eating healthier. What more can one ask for!

title: I love it!
body: I would give it the full five stars, except that it is only usable when you have Internet connection. I also have a problem with glitches. But it's an extremely useful tool that focuses not only on weight loss, but the quality and details of your foods and brands.

title: Food knowledge = better choices.
body: I like the fact that a lot of the food items are graded A to E...healthy to not healthy.  It is the aspect that makes fooducate stand out from other apps.  You have the ability to look for healthier choices...see how your food divides out into carbohydrates fats and proteins...great app

title: Best All Around Food App Yet!!!
body: FINALLY!!! Finally someone got it right. ONE place to track your overall food consumption, from Nutritional Values to GMOs. This tool is now an integral part of my healthy lifestyle. For a Vegetarian who charts everything they eat, this app just simplified my life. Well done.

title: Works great!!
body: I haven't  encountered any glitches so far, and everything I've scanned the barcode on works!!

title: Thank you
body: I only started to log as my food diary but found out I was eating over 2000 calories. I logged my food with an end goal to loose 15 lbs. Watching what I eat with the app and running I've met my goal!!! I'm now eating at 1400 calories a day and I'm not starving :)

title: A must have
body: If you are very conscious about the things you eat, you have to get this app. I use it at the grocery store before I buy things that I'm not sure of. I have had to change things that I buy on many occasions. A great app thanks Fooducate!!

title: Resourceful!!!!!!
body: This is the best app!  I use it every day.   I track with it and I look up everything I eat!!  I always look forward to the daily tips, too!  I have recommended this app to all of my friends. It is truly worth paying for!

title: Highly Recommended....
body: To anyone that cares about what you and your family eats. I recommend this app to all my friends and even strangers I meet along the way. Keep up the great work on making this the most useful app I have.

title: VERY educational, MyFitnessPal still a better tracker
body: MFP has a larger food DB & quicker data entry, so I'll stick with it primarily. When I have an extra moment, I re-scan my food with this app for excellent education, advice. If you use both, make sure to DISABLE Apple Health connectivity from Fooducate so you don't get duplicate data

title: Great app for the food conscious person
body: I really enjoy this app as it helps me choose a more healthy alternative option. If there is any downside, it doesn't work well with some bulk items found at Costco. Normal grocery stores have been great.

title: Outstanding!!!!!!!!!!
body: Fooducate is an excellent tool for a healthy lifestyle. It helps me to make healthier choices when shopping for my  family. I wish this app. was around years ago. Keep up the GREAT work Foodicate. You are on the right track with helping America stay healthy.

title: One of the most useful apps!!!
body: I really like how it tells you about all the hidden ingredients and what they do and why they put them into the product.

title: Great! Very Useful.
body: It is great when technology truly helps us make positive health choices simple and time efficient. What this program does would take me hours to accomplish manually. Great for all you Weight Watchers out there, this gives Points Plus numbers.

title: Great idea, few products
body: Maybe it's because I don't live in a major city, but I found that only about one-in-ten products were actually in the database. Of those, the alternatives suggested were never products available in my state, let alone my town. Basically, if you have a Trader Joe's or a Whole Foods in your area, you might find this app useful. If you shop seemingly anywhere else, it's a waste of time.

title: Mind blowing information
body: I've been treading the clean eating waters and this app has really been eye opening as far as the nutrition of some of my favorite "diet" snack foods. Since downloading this app I've started to eat more whole fruits and veggies and stopped relying on prepackaged convenience food.

title: Great app
body: For the most part I love this app. It has helped me make some better choices in the grocery store which not only help my health but also saves me money in that I don't buy a lot of the overprocessed and overpriced items which I used to buy.

title: I'd pay for this app!!
body: Getting healthy made easier with FOODUCATE!! So easy to use, great knowledge base on TONS of different food. It has definitely encouraged me to put poorly rated items BACK on the shelf! Been recommending to all of my friends and coworkers. Thank you so much for this amazing app! :-)

title: My go to App
body: I highly recommend this app. Perfect to see what is actually good/ bad for you to eat. You'll be surprised at how items that you think are healthy are not good. Love how the app gives you suggested alternatives that are better choices.

title: Great app!
body: I love this app! It is so eye opening to see how unhealthy some foods i was eating are. Fooducate has definitely changed the way I eat. It is also very motivating to see how many calories I have left for the day, it's like a game to try to stay within my personalized limits.

title: Amazing
body: I cannot stress how useful this app is for anyone who reads food labels. Wonderfully intuitive and beautiful user interface. I really like that you can what you might normally purchase and the app will give suggestions for related but healthier options. And it's free! Wow!

title: Everyone should have this app!
body: I have always been a consummate label reader, but this app teaches me something new every time I use it. For example, WHY a particular ingredient is not good, or HOW items are manufactured.

title: Great App!
body: This is a quick app which provides wonderful information on the food you are considering along with healthy alternatives. I use it every time I shop. It really makes you think about your choices!

title: Easy and Fun!
body: What a fun app!  Very easy to use and oh so helpful. I recommend it to all who care about learning more about what you are putting into your body. Really makes you think differently about how easy it is for manufactures to mislead you with product labeling.

title: Fooducate
body: Love this app had weight watchers but like this one better they do the research for you. You log in what you eat and they grade it also giving you the alternative of what is better than the choice you made

title: Food shaming/scare tactics overdrive
body: I think it can be a great tool for people with a nutrition background. Should be avoided for people in recovery from eating disorders.  Large amounts of misinformation without solid scientific backing.  I feel it does a great deal of food shaming. Not the most user friendly either. Difficult to track in a hurry.  I love the idea but I feel it's going to far in the wrong direction to be a realistically useful tool for the general population.

title: I'm really enjoying the Fooducate app
body: This is very easy to use and I'm learning new things even the first day. I would like to be able to see the food points as I'm progressing thru the day as opposed to only at night when I finish.

title: A+ App!!
body: I have been very pleased on the ease & use of this app. It has been so easy to incorporate this app while grocery shopping and my daughter has become more interested in what foods we eat. Thank you for such an incredible experience. üëç

title: Don't go to grocery store without the app...
body: I find it very helpful to go shopping. There have been quite a few surprises, items that I bought were decent, turned out a D, but also the other way.

title: Meh
body: It seems like a good idea. I don't think it's a good idea to put allergies in the Pro version though. I have browsed through a few times and started getting together ingredients for a recipe only to realize it has something I'm allergic to in it. So, I have to put everything back up and search again. Probably going to just stick with MyFitnessPal. üòï

title: Love it!
body: Using Fooducate every day! Helps me to make better informed food choices. I've already lost 6 pounds in three weeks and improved my health with healthier food. I'm actually eating more than I did before and losing weight! It's so easy to use. Thx!

title: Love this app! So useful
body: When I started using this app I realized how poorly we choose the foods we eat. But with this I am aware of the pros and cons of everything I eat, and look for smarter choices with the "alternatives button". I use it allll the time literally, not exagerating!

title: Easy & Useful
body: This is the best food tracking app I've tried. Love that you can find out why an item received the rating it did. Thanks to this app I won't be feeding breakfast sausage to my family anymore. They alerted me to a dangerous additive that I never knew about.

title: Informative
body: I really like using this app at the grocery store. It's especially helpful when trying to decide between different varieties of the same product. I would highly recommend it.

title: Great easy to use App!
body: Easy to use app. Keeps track of calories and food. Scan works good and has most of the foods I eat in the system already. Just wish I could put a picture in for my own food though. Thanks!

title: One of the best apps on my phone!
body: If you really want to get serious about what you are putting into your body, then this is the app for you! I can easily see what foods are truly healthy, and which food labels are hiding unhealthy ingredients. A must-have app!

title: Awesome way to keep track of eating
body: Healthy or not this app will tell you! I love how it offers healthier alternatives to foods that aren't so good for you! Way better than MyFitnessPal or whatever that app is everyone is always raving about... Seriously this is better.

title: This app rocks
body: My only complaint is that it's hard to figure out the calorie content of home cooked foods, but for packaged store-bought goods and many simple grocery items, this app offers a comprehensive and helpful evaluation of the calorie content and healthfulness as well as great alternatives and a great community of food reviewers. A+

title: Love it!!
body: I use this app to track my food everyday. It works great. I love that you can scan the barcode on certain items, making logging them much easier! I also love the food rating system. Thanks!!!

title: Best Calorie Counting App
body: The best app I have found. It rates your food choices and offers better options if you need other suggestions. Easy to use. And interacting with others on line is helpful. Lots of useful information.

title: Really good for those that are obsessive about what they put in their body!
body: This is one of the best free apps. Great for shopping trips at Costco before you buy that huge tub of party mix that gets a 'D' rating. when you see how awful some items are, it will spoil your appetite.

title: Very handy app
body: Wow!!  I'm amazed at all the info this app gives you. I'm surprised some of the foods I've been eating are so unhealthy. I've tried making better choices and this app will help you do that. Great to use right in the grocery store because it scans barcodes.

title: Addicting
body: Slowly but surely switching my teenagers over to the Real Food plan with me. The app helps me explain why I won't buy certain food-like substances for them. I told them I'd buy anything B or better. I won't take a C from you in school and I won't take a C home to eat ;)

title: Wonderful!
body: Went to the grocery store with my eight year old and used this app to educate her about some of her favorite snacks. Love the "alternative" choices option..helps our whole family eat better! Thank you!!!

title: Best App for Health Nuts
body: I love this app! When I first started eating healthy I had a hard time choosing foods because I didn't know what they contained and wether the ingredients were bad or not. Now with Fooducate I am able to choose products that are good for me and are made of the best quality.

title: Great App
body: Though they don't have absolutely everything on here, they have A TON. What they don't have, you have the option to scan the nutritional info on an it and they will evaluate it. Definitely great to use while grocery shopping.

title: Gray App
body: Incredibly useful in regard to eating healthy.  This app cuts through the claims or inferences of foods that companies promote as healthy and are actually not.  The app also provides healthy alternatives to specific items that may not be healthy or conducive to weight loss.  Easy and fun to use.

title: Love this app!
body: This is great for helping you to eat right and help you make better decisions about the food you eat!ni have shared this with everyone I can!  I didn't think it could get any better but it did! With th tracker on her of what you eat, it's even more AWESOME!

title: Changed my life
body: You will never look at store bought food the same way again. A very powerful app both in scope and comprehension. If you're serious about changing the way you eat buy this app.

title: Best Weight loss App Ever!
body: This app is easy & fun to use.  It allows you to set your weight goal, then it calculates your daily calories needed to achieve that goal.  All you have to do is log in what you've eaten for the day, the exercise you've completed, and voila--the app subtracts calories expended!  Love, love, love it!

title: What you don't know about ingredients
body: A lot of food packages are touting health, but an analysis of ingredients says otherwise. I have been reading ingredient labels for years and really understand only a few. Fooducate covers the rest and will really open your eyes to what your mouth is eating.

title: Good idea, mediocre execution
body: I love the idea, and this is not bad for most people. App is very easy to use and attractive. But I'm already somewhat educated about nutrition and reading labels. I find the results repetitive, the background info not very thorough and the assessment  sometimes not accurate (i.e. hydrogenated oil was indicated as a reason for a poor grade but no such oil was in the product). Could do more with this app.

title: Awesome and educational
body: I love this app!! Only thing I wish they'd add would be a button where you can say "I ate this today" and it would keep a log for you.  I know there are other apps for that but it would be nice to have that and fooducate all in the same app. A+!

title: My doctor recommended the app to help me lose weight.
body: I am daily exploring all of it's features, and am finding it an easy to navigate. I like the way it gives you a reality check on the foods you are eating. I needed this app.

title: Love!
body: I love how convenient and fun using this app is. Not only have I gone through and scanned just about everything in the house, but I have also been entering in the food that I eat to make sure I am eating the right amount of food.

title: Great app for those with food intolerances
body: This app lets you scan barcodes or search the food and then tells you the ingredients which helps a lot since I have a few food intolerances. Amazing app that saves a lot of time!

title: Great food app
body: Very helpful app when you're concerned with nutrition.  Helps you pick more nutritious foods as well as track the calories you consume & burn.  Been using for a couple of years and it has only improved over time.

title: Best Frozen Fish Stick
body: I love fish sticks and I love quick! These fish sticks live up to their name. I took off one star for a bit too much bread ing, but they also seem to have much more fish than most. The fish is tasty and moist if not over-cooked. I use my convection setting (400) on the toaster oven and they come out perfect in 15 minutes right out of the freezer

title: Love it! With one Caveat
body: I love everything about all inclusive food lifestyle app. The only thing that is keeping it @ 4 stars is their turn around time on user submitted  food label reports (for missing items). It's so long that I may suspect that they have, in fact, simply stopped adding in user submitted items.

title: This app is all that!!
body: Thank you for creating! I've been using this app for about 5 days and I'm already down 5 pounds with using this app to keep up with calories I intake, eating clean, and educating myself on what I'm putting in my body. FYI mostly eating paleo. This app rocks!!

title: Everyone needs this app.
body: This app tells a lot of shocking information and great information about foods and drinks we are eating everyday.  Everyone knows whats in items are putting in our bodies. This will help everybody to start eating right.

title: Shady Upgrade!
body: At first I loved this app! It helped me set a goal, monitor my calories and carbs, and worked really well with my diet/fitness program. I got halfway to my goal and suddenly I have to pay 4.99 for an 'upgrade' so it will continue to track my carbs. Feeling a little hoodwinked. Think I'm going to check out some of the other apps my doctor recommended.

title: Lookin' good...
body: This looks like one I will buy once they have the food bank updated!  (And out of 70 apps I have only purchased one!). It is so easy to keep track of what I am eating and what calorie count to go each day!  I am handicapped and cannot always cognitate üòÆüòÉ..I was mischievously surprised when it automatically adjusted down my daily allowance due to weight loss!

title: Love this app!
body: Found this app in a mag. While look through it. I was curious so I download it. I love it. It's great. It has almost ever food on it and if not u can add it. I fill myself on it a lot looking forward to the day results. Very easy to use. Love the little tips too!

title: So I loved this until
body: Things got different. I don't know what happened but not my health tracker when adding food only shows carb intake on the top and when I go to look at my health tracker it won't load. I'm so annoyed because I really loved this app but now since I can't see my day I will use something different. All I want is a simple log, if I could fix it to where I had my calories on the top like before and able to see my log I'll use it again

title: Love it!
body: I love this app because it tells you what is in your food and what your actually eating! I also love how it scans your food instantly and that its really easy to use! I also enjoy that it tracks your progress! Totally worth getting!

title: Healthy App
body: Great app for eating better. It's actually kind of fun to bum around the store and scan different items to see their health grade. Includes great nutritional info. Easy to scan the items you eat to track your daily nutritional intake.

title: More than helpful!!!!
body: This app is a lot of help to compare different foods/snacks to see which are healthier. It gives descriptions, nutrition facts, as well as healthy alternatives to most foods. I recommend getting this app, especially if you're a nutrition freak like me ;)

title: Great app for tracking
body: I really think this app is awesome it's great if you want to keep track of you food and exercise! It also gives a grade on the food you eat so you can even start to pick better options. It also counts calories what more can you ask for

title: Best free "food tracking" app I have found
body: I've downloaded tons of Apps looking for one just to track my food and activity intake for free. Not trying to diet, just look at what I'm eating to help make better decisions! East to use. I like the activity tracker as well.

title: A great guide
body: I would give this 5 stars but sometimes the criteria for rating is hard to derive. For example, Trader Joe's turkey jerky gets a C+ but all that seems to be at issue is the "all natural" label. And that isn't even listed as a negative: it's marked merely as "information." A clearer explanation for what attributes contribute to a rating and how they are weighted would be helpful.

title: Great app to teach kids to eat right.
body: I love this app, what a smart idea. My kids are grown but if I had this when they were young I would hand them my phone in the store and tell them they couldn't buy any thing that wasn't a "B" or better.

title: Oreos
body: I deleted this app after seeing that Oreos had a grade of B. Several Fooducate members posted their excitement that Oreos "were good for you." This doesn't seem like reliable information. I was sad to see how many people said Oreos are a great healthy snack for their children. Feed your kids the occasional cookie, but don't walk around thinking that they are nutritious. In this case, Fooducate is perpetuating the idea that you can eat crap and be healthy. Fruits and vegetables are good snacks for kids, not cookies. Good luck everyone.

title: Great App!!!
body: You won't regret it! It is a really great App.!!! I have my shopping list in it. I can browse foods and see how healthy it is. It gives lots of good information on all kinds of food. It does a whole lot more...I haven't used it to it's full potential.

title: Love!!
body: This app is so helpful! It is so hard to grocery shop when everything claims to be a healthy choice now days. This app will tell the truth about items, and if it isn't the best choice, they offer healthier alternatives! I'm so glad I found this!!

title: Obsessed
body: I am so excited to have found this app - it is so much more than I expected , have found very few items not in the database and am learning so much about what I have been doing wrong and what I can do right..

title: Love it
body: The app does a great job helping me feed the best possible foods for my family.  As a budding vegan, my options become fewer and fewer.  This app helps me right in the grocery store and many times gave me good feedback on what I thought was healthy.  I've scanned my pantry! So much fun!

title: Exactly what I'm looking for in food app
body: Not only do I want to watch calorie intake, I also want to eat good quality food and this app helps me do this. I especially like the "vegetarian" option - I haven't found that in other food apps. Thank you fooducate!

title: Fantastic!
body: I would highly recommend this app to anybody. It allows you to be aware of so many variables in your diet from GMO foods to helping you lower your blood pressure. This is the best app of this kind I have ever used. To the developers: thank you and keep up the great work!

title: Great app!
body: This app has been awesome! The scanner has been awesome for helping to make healthier choices while grocery shopping and it also makes it super easy to keep track of your calories and points to help with weight management. Love it!

title: Great for me, but needs updated research on fats to be useful
body: I am a research nurse, so I am aware of updated studies on fat/health/nutrition, however most people do not have the time (nor energy because they are following outdated "low-fat" advice) to find out the best and most fervently researched studies which have come to light in the past 1 to 5 years.

title: Weight watchers rejoice!!!
body: An amazing app...one that is truly helpful and relevant throughout my day. A HUGE timesaver and resource for folks on the WW points plus program. Just scan...no calculator needed for many, many items! Don't even think twice... Just download it right now :-)

title: Scanning madness!!
body: Love the app!! Sometimes the alternatives are not that much better! Also, maybe stores which carry brands I'm not familiar with would help? Sure makes you think twice when you scan and see what you're eating!! Yikes!

title: Loveeeeeee ittttt
body: Every thing I need this along with my fitness pal helped me lose all the weight I wanted in a month 40lb by eating 1200 cal a day and every thing doesn't matter oh and drinking green tea normal store bot kind 5x a day but stop after u lose weight green tea is ancient remedy for everything

title: Best App!
body: This is such an amazing app! I recommend it to all of my friends! Takes all of the guess work out of deciphering nutrition facts! Makes grocery shopping a breeze when trying to choose the more healthy option on the shelf!

title: Informational
body: Gives a lot of information. Interpret the information on your own as you deem relevant. It has a lot of popular food items. But if something is missing, you can just take 3 photos of it and they will add it to the database.  Great for a free app.

title: Mucho Bueno!!
body: This App not only gives you insight by breaking down the processed food we may enjoy and gives alternatives . It also helps you keep you in check by allowing you to keep track of your daily caloric intake . So cool !

title: Life changer
body: I just started using this app, but for the week I've had it, it's opened my eyes to the amount of food I was eating. I'm sure with this and a little exercise I'm going to lose the weight in trying to lose. Great app

title: Hard to Please
body: This is by far the best nutrition app I have ever downloaded. Not only does it allow me track what I am eating, my exercise and Weightloss, it tells me what exactly is in my food (GMOs, additives and controversial ingredients).

title: Great app, interface could be a bit more polished
body: Love the app, much of the functionality that I'd want is there.  The interface feels just a bit clunky, however.  Still, it works better than similar apps with a better interface, so I'll take it.

title: Super usefull and user friendly
body: It's missing some products, so that is why I gave it four stars instead  of five, but otherwise it does exactly what it's supposed to  in a convenient and useful manner, I'm very happy with it and use it all the time to make better sections about what I eat:) try it!!

title: Absolutely a go-to
body: This a wonderful app to use at the grocery store. So many products are marketed for the health conscious but really are no better than their counter parts. It's nice to really get accurate and key facts to help my family develop and maintain healthier eating habits.

title: Pretty good, will be better as database grows...
body: Really easy to use convenient app.  Big drawback is no alcohol nutritional.  Also would be useful if you could create a list of regular foods and be able to select from that each day and week what you eat.  Fast food from the chains would also be useful.  Overall best food / health monitoring app I've seen.

title: Great app!
body: I find this application very helpful in understanding what's in what I am eating. It's helping me to make better choices, take better care of myself, to live longer for myself and family. I like the fact I can simply scan the barcode to get the quick nutrition facts on it. Thanks.

title: Sweetness!
body: This is a wonderful app!  It helps me keep track of my daily intake of calories and exercise!  I can customize it to fit my needs and it even reminds me very few hours to plug in what I have eaten!  I highly recommend this program!

title: Loveeee this app!
body: This app is great. The scanner I use daily when food shopping and I love the health tracker. Being a vegan I can track my proteins along with fiber and carbs. It's easy to use. The emails and updates on brands recipes and articles about products is also great

title: Exceeds expectations!
body: I downloaded another app but this app is much more powerful. I'm still learning the features. Like the grading system . Found out how much junk is in our cupboards. My wife will be using this for shopping.

title: Fun!
body: Scanning food items makes this app fun! I like how foods get letter grades because it makes it easy to chose healthier items. You can add your own food items that aren't already programmed in there, but a lot of goods are! Definitely a great app.

title: One of my most used apps!
body: Fooducate shows me how to choose better food. I must have upgraded at least 50 products since I started using this app last year. Went up from a C- average to a B+.

title: LOVE the simplified home screen
body: I love the new simplified home screen, the previous version was too much and deterred me from using the app for what I love most; scanning and browsing food to see its rating. Happy with the new change. Thank you Fooducate!

title: Pretty Good - Needs a Couple Things
body: Needs to have serving size info...maybe toggle to that when you click on Calories.  This can be highly misleading on many packages.  We both started Weight Watchers recently. FoodPoints seems to be very similar to WW's PointsPlus. Maybe Fooducate can convince WW to embed their tool in WW's eTools. Otherwise a very useful and helpful app.

title: Wonderful resource
body: Learning about your food products has never been easier then this! With a wide array of items, expanding constantly, this easy to use app helps you get a handle on the food you eat every day!

title: Great app!
body: My only complaint is how much longer my shopping trips are because I want to scan EVERYTHING! :) I love the amount of input we have and I appreciate all of the little details about what makes an item healthy or not-so.

title: Old guy
body: I am trying to loose weight. I thought I knew which are good foods and which are poor choices. This app really helps in making good choices . Not only in caloric intake but salt and " strange ingredients" too.

title: One of the most practical apps!
body: App works well and the scanner is excellent.  I find some of the food conclusions I do not agree with especially when ingredients are not considered on their own merit.  Overall a great guide when shopping that everyone who desires to eat healthier should use.  Highly recommended.

title: Great ap for all
body: This is a great ap for all users and very useful to know about what your eating. Dont get frustrated about them not having certain products they will add them, there are too many to put on over night! Be patient its great.

title: Very useful
body: Alerts me to hidden stuff like bpa and other tricky substances hiding in foods I previously thought were safe. Quick way to discover things like refined grains masquerading as whole grains and trans fats that go unnoticed due to the labeling loopholes. And it's free. Everyone needs to get this essential app.

title: Wonderful tool at the grocery store
body: I love this app, I use it at the store and won't buy anything less than a B for my 10 month old. Gives me the confidence I need to know I making the right decisions in selecting food for my baby.

title: Scanner doesn't work
body: Never scans on my iPod with camera. Almost always returns 'not found' error when barcode is entered manually.

title: Changed what I buy at the store
body: This is an awesome app! As soon as I downloaded it, I went into my fridge, started scanning, checked the healthier alternatives, created a healthy shopping list, BAM! Simple as that. Being healthy starts with the food you buy.

title: Impressive
body: So far, so good. I've only used it for a few days. But so far I'm thrilled. The only challenge I see for its long term success is the discipline necessary to build and maintain the habit of use. But if you do your part, the app will do its part.

title: Completely Disgusted ‚ùóÔ∏è
body: I paid for the pro version of the Fooducate app thinking it would be useful and factual information.  I was clearly mistaken!  They have no problem with listing items as non GMO even though they contain GMO's.  What is worse is that even after they have been informed and supplied the information from the companies they still just leave it incorrectly documented.  This is not an app to trust when it comes to you and your families health!  Beware!

title: Holds you accountable
body: I love the app because it makes you write down everything you eat in a day. It's easy to use do there isn't excuse.  I only need to loose 5 pounds but those are the hardest.  This apps keeps me accountable to what I put in my mouth.

title: Love this app
body: I love fooducate! It's seriously AMAZING! I haven't used it in years but just got it again and it is fabulously upgraded! It rates foods to let you know how good or bad they are, gives you healthier alternative suggestions for foods you like, has a recipe section, and MORE! So great!!!

title: Good App!
body: I bought the pro for a year. This unlocked amazing benefits. I love that each item I record gets the rating. Then each meal is graded like stop light. I can compare my choices by item or meal. I also love the attachment to my health app. Bravo! If you want that extra kick to improve your eating habits, this is the app!!!!!!üëçüèª

title: Ive found it
body: I've found the app that is finally going to help me reach my goal of losing weight. With tracking my food, my calories, and my activities I no longer have to download 2-5 apps, I only have to download 1üòä

title: Blind & like app
body: I am blind and I really like this app most all of the buttons are labeled so it's easy to use

title: Great app!!!
body: Fabulous app!! Very well designed and easy to interact with. Posting and using recipes is nice and easy, as is tracking your calories and exercise habits. However, the app would be better if I were able to input my diet while offline. Otherwise, no complaints!!!

title: Great so far!
body: This is my second day using it. I'm learning a lot. I love the fact that it can scan your food and give it a grade. It's awesome! It also notifies you about ingredients, if you indicate that you only want to eat certain things.

title: Very expensive. And not worth it.
body: So if you don't like this app they are not able to reimburse you. And when you select the in app purchase they charge for a full year, not month by month. So I just paid 24$ for an app that I am deleting because it's too confusing and too difficult to use. And the recipes are just full of fattening gross food. What kind of food educating are you doing with recipes chalk full of butter and cheese ... soooo disappointed.

title: Nice but needs improvements
body: A nice app with one reservation.  Scanner (iPod touch w/cam) is slow and unreliable compared, e.g., to RedLaser.  Needs some improvements.

title: This app is amazing!
body: I never knew just how good (or bad) my favorite foods were until I started using this app.  Now, my family makes wiser and healthier decisions at the grocery store.  This app keeps us from putting "junk" in the grocery cart.

title: Love this app.
body: Having the reminder really keeps me honest. I do wish it had restaurant foods included (I switch to Eat This,Not That) and I get stumped if my hubby cooks and I don't know the brands he used in a recipe. I am finding that I'm actually eating fewer calories than I need to, which may be why I've been tired.

title: Eye opening
body: I like this app.  I had trouble with the scan function at first but am getting the hang of it.  Some stuff I scanned were not in system which was frustrating.  It really shows how processed most if our foods are--even the "healthy" and "light" ones.  Very useful app.

title: Better than average, but far from intuitive
body: I appreciate Fooducate listing "A" list items.  Is does an excellent job of providing education of more nutritional items to consider.  I would like to think that the items I scan are forwarded to be included into their food directory.

title: This has it all!
body: After using a number of programs similar to this - including SparkPeople - nothing comes close to Fooducate in terms of convenience, functionality and ease of use.  Incredible app at any price.  Best of all, it's free and the ads are unobtrusive.

title: Excellent app
body: I love this app; it's a great help; my only complaint/suggestion is that I don't think it makes sense to give a food an A or B if its GMO probability is high. So I pay less attention to the "grade" given and more attention to the other info provided, which I think is fantastic!!! Thank you for creating this app.

title: Love It but...
body: I love this app. I use it with my iPad mini. My children love it, especially when they are out with friends looking for a snack to buy (they use it home and then recall what they learned).  We are making better food choices.

title: ‚ù§Ô∏èüçâüçåüççüçêüçÖ
body: I love this app and use it multiple times a day. It's always good to be aware of what you are really consuming. I also love the alternatives feature for when you are considering eating something that gets a low grade. üòä

title: Products
body: Was really impressed that after I sent them a picture and nutrition facts of a product that wasn't listed, they e-mailed me only days later letting me know that it had been added!

title: Very Useful...
body: This App really helps on the go. However, I have found a few mistakes here and there, and if I had any complaint, it is that I am not sure whether the grading system is based on the health value of the product or the diet value. Nevertheless though, I am very appreciative of this handy app!

title: Awesome App!
body: 5-star app for me!  Just recently learned about this and it has become my go-to app while I am shopping & trying to make healthier choices.  Very informative and is on my home page. Database is very extensive, and it is free as well - thanks to the developer!

title: Cool and useful
body: This is a great app.  Easy to use and it gives useful information about ingredients, serving size and better products to look for.  I really like that you can submit pictures for products not in their database.  I'm amazed that it is free.

title: Awesome app!
body: Just had this app about 5 minutes and I am already throwing out some of my food in my office!! I will no longer eat some candy I have bc I found out there is powered bugs in the red food dye!! And this is a well known brand!

title: Amazing!!
body: This app is awesome!  It really opens my eyes to a lot of the preservatives and such that are put into foods that one would normally consider healthy!  And I love the "foodpoints"!  It makes grocery shopping much easier when I don't have to figure it out myself.

title: Everyone needs this app!
body: I knew I wasn't always eating the healthiest foods, but fooducate really put into perspective just how unhealthy some of my choices were.  I'll never buy anything again without a fooducate barcode scan!

title: Enlightenment is bliss!
body: All I can say is that going grocery shopping with this app in tow takes marketing to a whole new level!  You feel as though you were an ignoramus before...great app if you really want to know what you're eating.

title: Really helpful
body: I love the info about the products. It's great that you can find alternatives, and the app tells you what if anything is wrong with the food. Not sure if the points are the same as Weight Watchers, but it is still helpful.

title: Great App
body: Really helps to make smarter choices when grocery shopping and deciding between products. Demystifies the nutritional info for you and gives fact on things you might not take into consideration normally.

title: The Perfect Assistant
body: I love this application. It's informative and helpful in finding new brands if products and helping us determine the difference between existing ones. Making more informed decisions about our food and beverages is very important, and Fooducate is the perfect assistant to do that!

title: Great
body: It is a great app to find better for you food.  Its not perfect, but it might stop you from buying product A, and think about a healthier B.  Couple this app with the lose it app, and you have a good amount of control over what you are eating.

title: New Grocery Store Buddy!
body: Super easy & the perfect app for daily grocery store goers like myself. Now I don't have to waste precious time comparing labels aisle after aisle. And if there's not a product page for an item take 3 pics from your phone & send them in. It's genius!

title: Comparing
body: I bought an iPhone 4 yesterday and have downloaded many apps. This is the most addictive one so far. I love the compare tab; it recommends eating "this" instead of "that". Plus, it has the information I am looking for.

title: Nice little app
body: I don't use this in the grocery store. I usually just compare the labels on boxes of similar items. But I love the share feature and also the little contests. I also love sending in info to update the app for other users.

title: Love this app!
body: This app has become my favorite! I like how it has a photo of the product, and very detailed explanations of why the product got the rating! Definitely going to tell my friends about it.

title: Awesome and Helpful
body: If you are trying to keep track of what you are eating and make healthier choices, this is your app! Really keeps you on track and the new improvements help you follow a diet plan! Definitely download

title: Love
body: Quick way to get nutritional info on products we are eating at home and love that it gives you an alternative or better option with every food selection.

title: Very informative
body: One of the best apps I have!! I use it at home and in stores all the time when looking for a healthier choice. They also respond back quickly with items that are not in their base. Great job!

title: Excellent App
body: This app enabled me to lose over 25lbs a year ago. I kept it off. It really kept me focused and on track. My recommendation for anyone who wants to lose weight is to have measuring cups, measuring spoons and a food scale to make the process easier. üëç

title: Love it but Needs bug fix
body: My only problem is that I have to clear all my other apps before I open this or it will crash. However This app is really helpful, it has so many ways to customize it just for you! It even gives you grades on the food you eat and tells you what's really in it.

title: The future of grocery shopping!
body: This is an enormous step forward for the NON GMO movement! It's user friendly format is amazing for those moments when you grab something off the shelf that you aren't sure if it is verified NON-GMO (genetically modified organisms). It's amazing. So happy that this exists.

title: Awesome
body: This is an amazing app. I have not only started making better choices on what I buy, I am realizing that just about all the things I thought were healthy were not, and this app gives me alternatives that are healthier. Love it

title: Great app!
body: I love this app! It helps big time making quick decisions at the grocery store! I dont have to spend more time comparing ingredient and deciphering which product is healthier and better for the family!! Try it out!

title: Easy to use!!
body: I love this app. This helps me keep track of what I'm eating. Fairly easy to add new items if it's not listed. I have suggested this app to 2 other people. Hope this helps but when I make my own meals I add the ingredients one by one.

title: Very expensive!
body: I don't need to lose weight, I don't need to control my cholesterol, and overall I'm in excellent health. I just want to know better than product labels what's in my food and the harmful effects. I uninstalled this app as soon as I found out what a money generator it is for the developers. You could spend up to $175 a year (more if you subscribe monthly) if you wanted to take advantage of every module. I'll do my research on the web thank you very much!

title: Favorite awesome app
body: Love this app and it is part of my daily routine! Reviewed before as great but you went over the top! Loving the new features by popping up and reviewing things I'm not checking such as cookies peanut butter etc keeps me informed as well!!!! Keep up the good work!

title: Best apps out there.
body: I love this app. It helps provide guidance & knowledge to make healthier choices when it comes to food, snacks & why the ingredients in certain foods aren't the best for us. Thanks so much fooducate for all that u do to help make this app soo user friendly & helpful.

title: All in one handy app!
body: Not only can you scan foods in market, the immense library of choices make tracking my food easy. I love the exercise tracking device too!  It's easy to use and a great health support!

title: Useful tool
body: Shows important qualities of food. Has a narrow view of what people need to eat at times. Tired of my high fiber foods being downgraded for one percent over Someone else's ideals.  Most of all the paragraphs on details of food's ingredients are repetitive, and says nothing about the food you are looking up. Reminds me of old horoscopes in the news paper.

title: Good app
body: This App works as described. There are still quite a few foods that need to be captured on the Apps list, but between scanning the barcodes and the ability to enter your own food nutritional facts, the app works well. I purchased a lifetime support, but I'm not sure that that is necessary for most people.

title: Fantastic Application
body: Both my daughter and I love this app. It has really changed our food selections. We thought we were healthy eaters and learned that small changes in our selections made a huge difference in our health.

title: Fooducate & American Grown
body: This is the app that a family member that is trying to eat healther recommended to me. I know food but I have learned a lot from this app.

title: Awesome!
