body: I love the Fooducate app. It helped me to realize how badly I was eating.... especially when I thought I was eating pretty well. I definitely use this app. more often than not because of its ease of use.  I love that it gives me great tid bits of information. Very helpful!

title: Great tool!
body: So helpful in making healthier choices for me and my family. I especially love the healthier options button to show you better choices than the product you originally chose.

title: Great app!
body: This app has become really useful for me, although I sometimes don't always agree with the ratings. It is helpful to know which foods are the best and why they are when compared to other products.

title: Life Changing
body: I'm am one to train dirty and eat clean! This app definitely gives you the advantage to control and know what your eating when you can't always buy fresh or organically or are on the go! It has become my new obsession!

title: Wonderful app!! Amazing!
body: I use this every day and its so helpful to find foods that are actually clean and green! And I try to help any way I can with the picture feature.

title: Super useful
body: Really uncovers bad foods that I am eating and I love the new food and weight tracking features. They have an amazing list of scanned products which really makes food tracking quick and easy

title: Fabulous!
body: This app is fantastic! It gives great information about foods and has helped me to stay on track with my weight loss. It has also helped me to make more nutritious food choices for my kids.

title: Great App
body: I really like this app and love the fact that it has the barcode scanner. Only problem is I can't get the function for creating a custom food to work. The app gives clear instructions on how to do this but it just doesn't work for me. Other than that its great!

title: Sp. Ed. Teacher
body: Love this app! Especially love the fact they have at least 5 other suggestions of a better product if the one you are researching comes up short on the grading scale. I have told many people about this great app and they love it too!

title: Great app
body: Downloaded the app this morning with no problems and used it this afternoon. Very helpful, fast and intuitive. If a product is not in their database the app asks if you would take several pics and send them in.

title: Awesome!!!
body: This app has saved me so many calories. It has also changed my mind on some things that I thought were good, and come to find out they weren't !! I love using this and being able to choose foods with confidence.

title: Awesome!
body: This app is great! My kids have really enjoyed looking through our pantry and fridge to investigate our food. They also love to use it in the grocery store. Of course I love it, but the biggest perk for me is how it's helped my kids open their eyes to what they are eating.

title: Excellent app!
body: Easy to use & I like that it will give healthier alternatives to what you have scanned. I also like that if a product isn't in the database then take a picture of it & they will email once that product is entered.

title: GreatGreatGreat!!!!
body: Without a doubt the best app EVER for dieters!!! I am on weight watchers and it even gives u the points values, plus if you are shopping it will give u better suggestions to buy for dieting. Absolutely the best and FREE. If u are dieting, or just trying to eat healthy do yourself a favor and dl this app!

title: Stop guessing and start eating
body: One of the best apps you can have. It's fast and you really learn a lot about what you are eating. I was blown away at some of the stuff I thought was healthy and found out I was completely wrong.

title: Fun app
body: Very easy to use and also helps you shop better for more healthy choices of the food you buy .when using this app you may find some things abt certain foods that will surprise you .üç¥

title: Concerned American
body: I like this app for the most part.  I don't agree that foods with aspartame, food coloring, or high fructose corn syrup, should be given anything higher than a D or F rating.  It is proven fact that these things are very bad for you.  I would appreciate it if you would tell us if something is made with GMO (genetic modified organisms), for this has also been proven to be VERY bad for us.

title: It helps if you stick to it
body: Like with many things, if you stick to it and continue to use the apps many benefits, it can help you toward your goal. I love the recipe feed, diet tidbits as well as how user-friendly this app is!

title: Wonderful tool!
body: Love this app...fairly easy to use.   Attribute the use of it to my success--if u eat even one bite, commit to adding to your tracker...if toy are anything like me, it's easier to skip that bite than add to the tracker..lol!  Wish I could save meals and add the whole meal or recipe to the tracker.

title: Like this app!!
body: I downloaded this app and the weight watchers one. This one is remarkably better. There are a lot of items that are recognized by just scanning, making it convenient and easy to use.

title: Fun for my whole family!!!!
body: I love this app!!!! My sister told me about it and I have loaded on my phone and my kids iPods as well! They love going to the grocery store and making sure they get all A's & B's on their "food report card"!!! Thanks fooducate!!!!

title: Love!
body: I love the scanning feature! I use this app at least 3 times a day. It's helped me keep up my new healthy lifestyle and I'm already seeing incredible results. Super helpful for grocery shopping. Recommend for everyone!

title: Great app
body: I use it mainly to compare products when shopping. Even when certain info isn't available they have been pretty consistent with getting the info to you.

title: We have a winner
body: Very informative, useful app! Gives you critical information on the items you consume daily. I've recommended this app to many friends & family members trying to live a more healthy & sustainable life style.

title: Helpful app
body: Has lots of good information about many foods. When I came across one that wasn't in the system, it was easy to get it added. I especially like the user comments section.

title: I love this app!!!
body: I have tried so many random crash diets and even weight watchers to help loose weight. This is really the only thing that has worked for me! I feel so much better and have lost weight!

title: Works for weight loss üëç... If determined
body: The healthier you eat, the easier it is to use this app. I mean it's difficult to calculate exact calories of a fried meal that you prepare yourself, whereas a sandwich or a salad that you can add as a single serving then save it as a meal later on. Love this app!

title: Awesome & Informative
body: I love that the app not only "grades" what you're putting in your mouth but also tells you why the food gets that grade and alternatives to the food! Truly an awesome app if you're trying to change your eating habits!!

title: Love it.
body: I absolutely love this application and would give it 5 stars, but I've noticed that a lot of the food I buy has either limited information and therefore no grade, or is not found in their database at all. But other than that, it's pretty amazing! Plus it's free, so why not get it and eat healthier?

title: I use it all the time!
body: Fooducate will probably end up saving my life. I use it everywhere. Literally, I will stand in a store aisle scanning everything until I find a healthy alternative. For example, did you know that reduced fat peanut butter is a C+ while regular is a B?

title: Great , easy app!
body: I wouldn't call myself a health fanatic but I like to eat healthy. This app allows you to scan almost everything you buy, gives it grade and then gives you healthier alternatives. It makes you realize what you put into your body. Some foods may surprise you!

title: Making better choices!
body: Love the app as it helps me make better choices as to brands. I don't like the network issues I experience every time I'm in the store, and very often the items are not yet in the database, but when they are it's extremely helpful!

Alternatives could be better. Also some barcodes don't give you the exact product and ingredients don't always match. Also they don't tell you how the score is decided. For example for me, sugar is something I'm more conscious about but calories isn't. But over all pretty good!

title: Great app
body: Helps you make healthier eating choices. Extremely helpful since most product labels in stores are misleading and allow you to think the product is healthy when it's really not.

title: Love it! But..
body: I absolutley love this app. It's a great tool to use when wanting to eat healthy! The only problem is that whenever i click on an item's "more info" section, like where it lists the pros and cons, the app closes on me and i cant open up that section. Other than that it's very good.

title: Learning so much
body: Excellent app!  Makes learning about the food around you fun & interesting...but it is dad to see how unprotected we are, how much we allow food producers to do to the food we eat!  Hope to see better regs in the future.

title: Love
body: I've been using the app for 4 days and I am so amazed how encouraged I feel. It is so easy to use and  understand... I just feel great! Totally recomend it for people that, like me, dont know where to start. It will automtically guide you to your goals. 5 stars for me.

title: Helped me get fit
body: Great app, helped me track my calories & get in great shape. Surprised me when foods that looked "healthy" weren't so great after all. Only problem is that it can't track most fast food items or general home-cooked foods. This would be a great addition. Otherwise, it's a very useful tool.

title: Very useful app!
body: This app is great for learning about what is actually in your food. It goes in depth on all the scientific terms that no one really knows what they are. Makes you think twice about all the food you thought was good for you!

title: The app you have to have
body: If you care about your health this is the app for you. fooducate rates the food that you eat. If an item that u scanned has a low rating it gives you alternatives to better and healthier choices.

title: Awesome!!
body: This app is so amazing, and has really opened our family's eyes on what we are eating. My son who is 6 does not want to eat anything under an "-A" which is almost impossible, but I love how he is understanding the importance of living a healthy life. Thank you!!!

title: Love it!
body: This is the best App!  I continuously check my food only to find what I thought to be "good for you" really isn't as great as you thought. Use it always. Have sent the link to my friends!  Highly recommend it:)

title: Awesome! Has much for improvement.
body: This app is great!! I recommend it to everybody! I just wish when u scanned ur food it would automatic save the item so you keep track of all foods u eat that day. Like a diet analysis. It should keep count on vitamins, cal,carbs,protein etc.

title: Excellent app Dietitian Recommended
body: This app is very helpful for people who are often confused about what foods are healthy. Cereals are some of the most confusing, and Fooducate's App helps. Dietitian approved to help clients eat healthier. We always looks for tools to help our clients with the the foods in packages.

title: Great app, but needs to synch with Fitbit
body: I love this app!  One of the better to keep track of calories.  I also love the scanner to catch foods that may not be in there system.  Only downside right now, I wish they sync he'd with the Fitbit.  I want to upgrade to the surge but won't until they can synch.

title: Very happy camper
body: I absolutely adore this so far. So easy to use and it's helped me so much on eating better. I don't think I'll get the pro version though, since I can just get most of that info for free on the internet.

title: Great great app
body: I thought I'm buying healthy food and pretty educated in what products are good for you

title: So great
body: I love the feature of being able to post recipes; and then if you make a recipe that's been posted in the forum, all you have to do is hit the "+". I also like the fact that it won't dip below 1300 cals in a day üòä

title: One of the better food apps
body: An easy way to track food intake especially since i do not need to lose weight. Unfortunately, all the apps I have tried focus on more weight-loss  than on health. Would be a 5 star if I understood food points better.

title: Quick research
body: This is a well thought out app.  Colorful, fun, useful.  I deleted livestrong since I got this.  The scanner is very useful and when it's not yet in the data base, you get to send the info and they quickly add it.  Excellent!

title: Really like it
body: I use it all the time. I don't like the limited products, but it is new. It does have a large amount if products. Not sure if "probable high GMO" is a fail safe for companies that aren't organic, or if its bc the company is known to use GMO. Need a better definition I think. Otherwise it's awesome!!

title: Great app
body: Great app no problems with it. Helps you see what you are putting into your body so you can control or modify it. Also reminds you to put in your information so you can stay on track.

title: Keeps you in the know
body: Good to have this around while grocery shopping. It's informed me of several things that I had no clue I had been obliviously consuming. Everybody needs this to make better, health-conscious picks

title: Very good to keep track for your health
body: As most folks know, eating well and exercising well is good for you! This app is easy to use and I can't think of any way to improve it. Well I suppose if it also tracked blood sugars it would rule!

title: Overall good.
body: It needs little improvements in the app, such as more products being rated and more information on each product. But overall this is a great app! It really helps me understand more of what is going into my body!

title: Great helper in the store!
body: Like the fact it gives a rating to almost everything I buy, helping me make better choices.  Including exercise daily helps with the calorie tracking! Great app!

title: I Love It!!!!!
body: I use the app when I go grocery shopping, intead of looking at the long list of ingredients on a package I just use the app & it has a useful A thru F system weather or not a product is good or not. Also press the tab alternatives & it gives you a list of better products.

title: Good but crashes
body: This app is awesome and is something everyone should use. The only problem is it locks up my phone every time I do something. I can scan about two to three thing then it locks up my phone. I am running a 4 do maybe that's why but still annoying. Awesome app though otherwise.

title: Favorite nutrition/shopping app by far
body: Very easy to use, expansive database, and so far I haven't come across any nutrition information that seems misinformed. I love having this at the grocery store to reduce the guess work and help me make the best choices.

title: Addicted!
body: Oh my gosh, I can't go to the grocery store anymore without looking at this app! Every time I cook I'm always typing in my ingredients to this app just out of curiosity. I have stomach problems and this app absolutley helps me buy the right foods.(: get it, get it, GET IT!(:(:

title: Useful and practical
body: I didn't realize how much I would use this app until I downloaded it. I currently scan everything and use the grocery list function constantly. Love it!

title: Love it!
body: Love, love, love this app!  Makes watching what you eat so easy.  Only problem has been that after using it for a week it deleted all my info for some reason and I had to start over again.

title: Amazing
body: I have been a dietitian for 15 years and this is the most user friendly and comprehensive program I have seen. The grades help guide your selections and making grocery lists has never been easier.

title: Loving it:) amazing technology & info!
body: This app has been awesome from fantastic information on grading food to helping reach my weight loss goals while learning the healthier options:) hands down best... Have already referred multiple friends...

title: Has changed the way I eat
body: I check all my food with this ap. shows there ARE excellent alternatives to anything. Most are better for you and you won't miss out on a thing!

title: Useful information
body: You can't change what you don't know.  Keeping track of what I eat, my exercise routine, brings me greater knowledge in regards to what I'm eating and possible alternatives for healthier eating happens.  Thank you.  Please make it easier to make corrections to entries and duplicate items.

title: My Favorite App!
body: This app is amazing! I use it daily. Helps me make the healthy choice and avoid the deceit from so many companies false claims (ex: Special K- SO BAD FOR YOU! Who knew?) also you can track your daily intake and exercise, so helpful. My favorite app on my phone!!

title: Food education
body: I absolutely love this app!!!

title: Easy to use - takes the mental math out of shopping
body: What a great tool. I try to make healthy choices for my family - now it's even easier! Plus my kids can easily see why I won't make certain purchases.

title: Awesome app!!
body: Love this!  Great tool for the supermarket and for everyone trying to maintain a healthy lifestyle!  I love that you can take pictures of anything not in the database and submit it for evaluation. I don't ever submit reviews but this is too impressive to pass up.  Superb job!!!

title: So fun and educational!
body: In a sea of thousands of nutritional labels, it's nice to have an app that can make things easier to understand!!  Compares a variety of products and brands so any trip to the market less stressful.  So much fun to use! I highly recommend it!

title: Quick Tips
body: This app is great for those of us that read labels in the store before buying any new foods. It gives you a quick analysis of what the label says. I love the quick list of pros and cons. Really makes shopping easier.

title: Helpful
body: There is a feature that shows you how healthy you are compared to others which makes it sort of competitive. It also helps you want to eat healthy :)

title: Great app
body: Very informative and helpful, saves times in store, rather than comparing every brand you can check it quickly on the app and get a review, and/or other brands that may be better or perhaps less money.

title: Great app!
body: This app is awesome! So easy to use and gives a lot of great information. Plus, on the off chance the food isn't in the database, it guides you through the process to take pictures of the revelant info needed and send to fooducate to add. Really cool!

title: Awesome app...
body: I like this app! But how do you get it to scan the barcode on iPod touch? Mine won't do anything. I can see it through the camera but it doesn't scan or anything, I have to manually type in the barcode.

title: Very useful app
body: I use this app when I'm grocery shopping all the time. It helps me make good choices when selecting food. I like that it gives the weight watchers points plus values and shares insightful information about ingredients.

title: Great resource, but...
body: This app offers really great features for tracking weight loss and creating a diet plan, but I can't get past the fact that it crashes only after a few minutes.

title: Comparing
body: I bought an iPhone 4 yesterday and have downloaded many apps. This is the most addictive one so far. I love the compare tab; it recommends eating "this" instead of "that". Plus, it has the information I am looking for.

title: This app really is great!
body: Such an easy to use app, love the ability to scan and add to health tracker. Creators did a great job! I'm thinking about updating too, I'd love to track my protein and fiber intake. If you guys added some more vitamins to the tracker that would be awesome!

title: Thank You
body: This app was with me through a wonderful journey. Helped me lose 90 lbs!!! Couldn't be happier with this app. Of course, it's not perfect; but it's what you make of it!!! And it's always working on making improvements!!

title: One of my favorite apps, used regularly
body: This is a must have app. It has changed my eating habits. Allows you to test a food before buying. The letter scoring system is great!  I love this app. Great for determining what you are eating.  Leads to eating much healthier.

title: I love the app, you will to
body: I love this app I think anyone who is watching what their eating or staying staying away from process food this is the app for you !! I love scanning to in stores!! This is better than w.w. Tools it's Good for counting calories to.

title: Just Started
body: I just started Wednesday. So far I like this app.  It's user friendly and it a good measuring stick to help educate yourself to make better choices both at home and where I really need it, fast food restaurants.

title: Super!!
body: Best way to lose weight is to pay attention. To what you eat. Fooducate helps you do that without much fuss, and it has lots of helps that make it easy to use. It's a great program for healthy eating or weight watching.

title: Very helpful app!
body: I use this app quite a bit. It is very helpful because he gets all the nutritional information about the product. I specially like the healthier alternatives it provides to a unhealthy product.

title: Terrific
body: Or use this application when I worked at the grocery store to educate customers and myself. I am now using the calorie and exercise feature to help me lose weight and make wise decisions.

title: Best app ever
body: The kids love using it.  I love using it.  I've made my friends get it.  Take the mystery out of grocery shopping for healthy choices.  This app is excellent for those who want to make eating healthy a priority.  It's not perfect, nothing is.

title: Educational and practical
body: I have only been using this app for a couple of days and I'm learning so much from it! It has helped me stay focused and aware of what I'm putting into my body and choosing better alternatives!

title: In to Healthy Eating- This is a Must Have App!
body: I love this app! If you are into eating healthy and want to make sure that what you think is good for you really is......this is the app for you! I use this all the time but specially when I shop for healthy meals and snacks.

title: It's a good idea, but...
body: When you log in your food choices, it doesn't offer some homemade food choices. If I make an 6 oz rib eye steak there's no way to log that in and get my protein/calorie intake.

title: This is the greatest app I have ever seen!
body: I've been so impressed with Fooducate from the start, but since their update I've just been blow away with all they have to offer. Truly amazing how much I can learn from this app.

title: Flaws
body: Great concept with the app and has multiple functions but has several flaws. If you're going by points it's a little harder to find the point breakdown for each food. Major flaw for me is the lack of fresh produce in the database compared to the plethora of trader joe branded food. For example, it has no nutritional data for a fresh nectarine but has plenty of processed juices to chose from.

title: Useful
body: The app really makes you aware of what you eat during the day. I have cut back on snacking and it has made a difference. I also enjoy scanning products at the store. I have my friend hooked on it now!

title: Excellent food app!
body: The best thing about this app is then ability to scan bar codes and get instant info on most foods. If the food is not in the database you have the option to submit the food to their database.

title: Real eye opener!
body: It's great to have the honest facts, to know whats really going into your body.  Advertising, stores, and packaging can be so misleading, so many things I thought were healthy are not.  Thanks to this app I can eat better and feel great!

title: Fooducate
body: Used to love it and considered purchasing, but I haven't been able to log on my phone for about three weeks.  Contacted support last week and still haven't heard back from anyone.  If that's the customer support they offer, I think I'll pass :-(

title: Still the champ, better than ever!
body: Other apps come and go, but Fooducate has delivered years of value for my family and I. Honest, accurate info that will help you make life changing choices!

title: AWESOME APP!
body: Informative and easy to use with a huge database.

title: Very useful app!
body: If you're trying to watch what you eat and want to be sure that what you're buying is the best thing for you, then this is the app for you! Easy to use and full of good nutritional information.

title: Amazing
body: This is hands down THE BEST app I have. I literally use it everyday especially when I go food shopping. It has completely changed the way I eat and the products I buy. It truly makes eating healthier so easy!

title: Handy info in the palm of your hand
body: Good information to keep on hand when you are trying to eat smart! It's nice to be able to get a quick glance at what I am putting into my body just by scanning the package .

title: Excellent
body: Love to be able to scan foods quickly and determine which products are better. Trying to reduce and eliminate artificial colors and weird preservatives from our diets, and this has been an excellent tool.

title: Great app
body: Very useful, love the feedback mechanism for unknown products that allows a photo to be submitted.

title: so annoying!
body: Just downloaded this today and at first it worked great and I loved it! Then every 15 seconds it starts giving me a message saying that my cellular data network is having an error. I am able to do anything involving Internet except this app. I want to delete it but am waiting for an update that will fix this! Won't let me scan products either due to this issue! Fix it and I will give five stars!!

title: LOVE THIS APP!!
body: Won't go grocery shopping Unless my phone is fully charged so I can scan every product

title: Meh
body: It's okay, but it is annoying that you cannot easily edit foods and exercises in the health tracker.  For instance, if I eat an orange in the morning and then have another in the evening then I have to add it again rather than edit my first entry to 2.  In addition, the proportion options are limited to 15 minute increments on exercise and .5 increments on food.  Very limiting, especially if you eat a lot of fresh foods and cook at home.

title: Great app
body: I love the app and use it in conjunction with Myfitnesspal app. The one thing I wish I could do is type in an area I need more of like- "protein" or "iron" and get good food options that are high in that area. after using the app I got my mom to download it too and now we have been eating a lot healthier.

title: Great app!!
body: I love this app. I learned a lot about many products that I regularly use. I like that it offers better choices for the products. It looks really easy to recommend new products, too.

title: Excellent!
body: I was grumbling to myself food shopping last weekend about how hard it was to compare things.  This is so easy to use and has fully solved my problem.  Thank you for creating this!

title: The best and fun
body: I have used this app for a month now has help me lose more weight and has open my eyes on the items that I thought were healthy and told me the real facts about what's really inside the product.

title: Best app in the app store!!
body: This app is amazing and the developers are just as great. The only bad thing about this app is finding out all that "healthy" food you consume isn't healthy at all. Great interface, easy to use, and highly addictive. THANK YOU!!!

title: This is Big
body: Completely changed what I buy. Also made me a hit with friends and colleagues. I appreciate the quick product feedback while in the store and love grabbing the healthier recommendation down the store isle.

title: I love it!
body: I love to be able to compare the different brands and find the healthiest choice. I pretty much scanned everything in my house and figured out which things to quit buying and bought the healthier alternatives. A must have App!

title: Making better choices easier
body: Scans and finds most products, offering nutritional information and WW points values. Shares nutritional information and offers better options. Not affiliated with WW, but it beats the pants off of scan calc!!! Great app!!!!

title: Love it!
body: I really love this app for both me and my daughter! It's very helpful to instantly find out how good/bad the  food you're thinking about buying or going to eat really is and find an alternative product! I use this app often.

title: Great app!
body: Really easy and quick to use with good information. Helps me make better food choices and gives detailed explanations of each food grade. Also, it's really fun to play around with.

title: Healthy Lifestyle
body: I am one of those people who must track my food intake if I gave any chance at losing weight/maintaining a healthy balance. This app makes it easy to do! Also, love that we can share healthy recipes.

title: Great app!
body: I must say this is genius! I only use it to scan the food that i shop for and see the ratings def going to keep using... Saw a few bugs on the app would be great if those get fixed :) thank you!

title: Love this app!!!
body: The scanning feature is awesome and tracking daily is simple! If a product is not in their database, it is so easy to send them the information to get it added! If you keep a food diary, this app is a MUST HAVE!

title: Superbly informative
body: I usually don't care about what it how much I eat, but after I found this app, I started being more alert, of course with the help and prevention of the options available.

title: Incredibly useful
body: This is by far the best food scanner and knowledge base app I have found yet!  Excellent database of foods and greatly appreciate being able to provide info on a product not currently in the database.  Well done!

title: Excellent and realistic!
body: This app is my favorite. It provides a summary of everything you need to pay attention to. Also, this is the only health app I've found that allows a HEALTHY amount of calories per day.

title: Well worth using
body: I find it easy to use and has a large database of foods. By counting calories taken in and burned off, I have been able to reach my goals. I highly recommend it.

title: Gotten a lot better
body: This app has really become a great part of my health maintenance program.  Could have a little more demos to fully understand all functionality but over all great app.

title: The Best Nutrition App
body: Knowing the correct way to get your nutrition is difficult due to companies that advertise their food to "look" healthy. This app will help you identify and understand which foods ARE healthy and which ones are not!

title: Love this app
body: The only thing I can complain about is that to get all the features I would have to pay monthly or a large one time price. Otherwise I love everything about it!!

title: Awesome
body: Been using this for 7.5 weeks- lost 25lbs! Great app.

title: Great!
body: Comes in handy at the grocery store and seems very fair. Doesn't appear to be promoting any certain company or type of food. I loved seeing how more expensive food can be more unhealthy than less expensive, generic brands.

title: Great app!!!
body: Love that I can scan items & also suggests healthier choices.  I just wish I could type my items as well it still love the convenience of it even without the typing option!!! :)

title: Easy
body: I love this app for all the reasons others have said, but, in addition, it has taught my kids of all ages how to evaluate their food choices and that thrills me. Not that they always demonstrate self control,  but I'm certain they are informed.

title: True Food Education
body: This app will help you to take charge of what you are putting in your body.  What you don't know you'll discover by a simply scan of the barcode.  Invest in yourself by investing in this app.

title: Very useful
body: Although most of the database is made up of foods you can scan, it still has a ton of foods. It allows you to count calories based on serving size and portions. I love it for my food categorizing/calories needs.
Great app, scans nicely, explains clearly, offers better food options, easy to add add'l products... "Make-Your-Own" recipes are nice... Has helped me make better food choices... Thank You!

title: Fooducated!!
body: I really enjoy this app even though it still seems to be missing quite a few foods. My only other complaint is that you need to know a proper serving and that information is not always available or known by the consumer.

title: Love This Freaking App!
body: Get it use it and you won't be disappointed. Just got back from Trader Joe's and was scanning everything. The people that work were so impressed they were going out and downloading it.

title: Love it!
body: Makes it easy to track your daily food choices and count calories.  If your choice is not very healthy, it gives you several alternatives that are better.

title: Excellent app!
body: Excellent app I do not count calories but I love I scan and the alternatives it provides. I also like the ratings as I learned a few foods I eat and thought was healthy were not! Grrr !

title: A wonderful app to download
body: This is a great app! It always has some interesting facts about each food I buy and lists some good potential concerns for some foods that really aid in the users ability to make healthy choices!

title: Very educational tool
body: This is a great app!  This app helped me pick out the healthiest foods available in all categories. I also like how you can type in a specific brand for what you are looking for and it will give healthier alternatives.

title: Awesome app
body: I love this app for so may reasons but mostly because it allows me to make small changes to be healthier without changing the way my family eats. It is helping me to make wiser choices for my whole family!

title: Super app!
body: I really like this app and use it frequently.  Also, my daughter is interested in it too which is helping me to teach her about wise food choices.  I do look forward to an updated product list.  Great App!

title: Fun & informative!
body: Not only can you see how the food that you purchase rates but you can also look at similar products to see which is the healthiest. Fooducate also describes what some food terms mean. That's helpful to me!

title: Good
body: It's nice to know if the "healthy" food you are eating is actually healthy or not. I wish they would tell you where you can buy the alternatives because sometimes I have no idea where to get them.

title: Update iOS 5.1
body: Ever since I updated my software to 5.1 this app doesn't work, it refuses to get passes the scanner without displaying the "check connections with cellular or wireless connections then try again or dismiss." it's irritating and trying to report the bug through support came up with a blank page.

title: Great for grocery shopping!
body: I've been using this app for a while and love it. Now that they finally order the searches by grades I had to give it a 5 star rating. It makes using the app so much easier!

title: Easy to use
body: Great app! It's easy and very informative. When they don't have info ready it allows you to take pics and automatically sends it in. Takes only 30 seconds

title: I deleted it due to new terms of service
body: Registration is now required. I didn't accept the absolutely outrageous terms of service so I don't know exactly what personal info was required.  I could not agree to give the seller all rights, title, and interest and waive any other remaining rights to my info. While I can understand the need for a  business to protect itself, this piece of software doesn't seem to warrant the extent that is demanded. Read it for yourself.

title: Awesome app! Just one additional request...
body: Love this app and all it does.  The only thing I wish could be added was the ability to search manually instead of always having to scan or enter a barcode. That would certainly merit five stars!

title: Fooducate is amazing!
body: Scanner works really really well... Fast. Comparisons and alternative choice tools in the app make it totally invaluable. I am also particularly impressed with how well they've implemented the process of contributing items that are not yet present in their db, very cool. Love it.

title: Great App
body: This is my favorite app! I am scanning everything in my pantry and the grocery store. I do pretty well buying the most healthy options, but I have had several eye-openers. I really like the 'alternative' tab and the 'compare' tab. Very helpful!

title: Great UI and super information!!
body: Love the look and feel of this app, and the info presented is way handy. While sometimes I'll still end up eating a poorly rated food, it's good to know I have some making up to do. Love this little buddy!!

title: ÓÄéÓÄéÓÄéÓÄéÓÄé
body: I love this app, tells me the best product to buy. Some products have misleading ads, by scanning the product it tells u the bad ingredients and also ratesbthe product. Since i have this app, i been choosing my food wisely.

title: Use it every time I shop!
body: I really benefit from this app! I have lost some weight because it has taught me how to eat healthier! There are a lot of diet foods out there that are not good for you, and this app has helped me eat more natural. I feel great!

title: Must have:)
body: Perfect for dieting, watching carbs!  The information on this app is so precise, if the average grade is low it gives you several alternatives to choose!  If u drink diet sodas your going to be shocked!  Well worth the price, the scanner is fun and the results are educational!

title: Amazing app
body: Great app, really simple way to check if a food is healthy or not. I don't use it to diet but instead to see what food is made of, if there's questionable ingredients, manufacturing process etc. This app is perfect for my needs.

title: Great help
body: I love this app! I use it while shopping. It helps me to decide which brand or type to buy. I'm becoming more and more aware about the ingredients I should avoid to help myself eat better food. Get it! Use it!

title: Great app...except for recipes
body: I love the app for scanning foods. However it's completely useless for recipes. You can't edit or delete a recipe once you've created it. You also can't change units when entering food into a recipe making me do odd conversions to enter ingredients.

title: Great!
body: This app is way better than myfitnesspal. But there could be more barcodes and foods put into the system so I don't have to create my own food everytime I scan something. I like that there are articles pertaining to fitness and everyday living.

title: I Shouldn't Have to Pay for Health
body: I really like this app and I turn to it whenever grocery shopping. However, I don't think it's fair to have to pay to find out if a product is GMO. It's counterproductive. If you preach that being healthy shouldn't cost much, then why do I need to subscribe to pro to make better choices?! Shouldn't I spend that money on healthy food instead?

title: Wonderful app!
body: I'm glad I found out about this app! I'm better able to keep up with what I eat & see how I can improve my diet!! I don't always have time to log all my meals but this app keeps me mindful of what I am eating

title: Great app!!
body: This app is informative, useful, fast, and efficient. My only critique is that more should be available without having to purchase an upgraded version. Other than that, though, it has helped me stay on my diet and encourages me to eat healthier 24/7.

title: Food app
body: Been using less than a week, but I can say I really am loving using it. Great way to understand what you are putting in your body.

title: Perfect App.
body: More information than you could ever wish for. Helping me to eat healthier to lose weight instead of turning to not eating at all. I'm proud of how I'm treating my body now, and fooducate has helped so much!

title: Great App
body: I own a Fitbit and the Fitbit app is great but I love this app it gives you a more detailed account of what you are putting into your body. It's quite fabulous and easy to you. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars was because the in app purchases are a bit pricey.

title: Absolutely delightful to use!
body: After recently being diagnosed celiac I've been struggling to figure out the best way to eat healthy. A friend told me about this app and pretty much changed my outlook on GF. It's absolutely a fantastic app and very encouraging. I'm so happy!

title: Great app
body: Love the app. Great for awareness of products. One thing i would love improved is the "alternatives" there are times that it gives alternatives that don't seem to relate, or maybe I'm reading it wrong... Other than that i love this app... Food smart!

title: Like the integration with my health apps & Apple Watch
body: I like this app but it needs to update its list of foods. I'll scan the barcode and the app won't recognize the food. I spend a lot of time putting in details about foods I like. Lose it! has a more extensive list of foods but does not integrate as well with my health apps & Apple Watch.

title: Great App!!  Very easy to use and helpful!
body: This is such a convenient way to count calories!  It also helps me to make better food choices by rating the items. Very helpful and easy to use!

title: Love it!
body: This app is very easy to use and motivating as far as making healthy food choices is concerned. I love having the ability to scan foods instead of manually entering in the food item.

title: Excellent
body: Great app with loads of info.  The database is always getting better because the users help gather, fantastic plan. We get chances at freebies too!  This is not even a game, yet the developers made it fun and informative. Highly recommended.

title: Love it!
body: So far I live everything about this app. I now scan everything before I buy it. I especially like that they provide better alternatives than what you may have chosen.

title: Very helpful thank you!
body: I had drifted ip the scales without really paying attention. All of a sudden I was 15 pounds heavier in only a matter if weeks. This app allowed me to focus and readjust with tracking along with good ratings to help me make smarter choices.

title: Good for GMO Advice
body: I love this application, particularly for looking to see if an item might have genetically modified food Ingredients in it. It is a rather simple application, for those that are used to reading labels. But I definitely use it at the grocery store while I am shopping to scan things.

title: Good app
body: Pretty easy way to track calories and helpful when shopping for healthy food.  Would love a "report" of some kind that actually provides recap of nutrients (and bad stuff) you eat.  Also, would be fantastic if there were a recipe input option (include all ingredients and then save the receipt to your favorites).

title: Worth the time and Effort
body: If you are serious about tracking meals or understanding make makes a particular food healthy or unhealthy, this is the app for you. I'm seriously considering upgrading to the fooducate Pro for 9.99 for the lifetime deal.

title: Love
body: Love this app.  Bought the pro version on my new phone. Was surprised by the health tracker and love it! One thing I wish was they had an option for nursing mothers in the health tracker. But other than that, I highly recommend.

title: Good App.
body: I don't like how you can't submit your own amount of water. I also think there should be more available pictures and info about more foods. But overall, awesome. Very useful and teaches you a lot about foods you probably never knew.

title: Pretty informative
body: Good way to get some quick facts about a product without  going through the hassle of sifting through link after link on the web.

title: Good stuff
body: I use this app everyday...it helps you be conscious of the food you're letting pass your lips and educate choice if you will;) also if you're on watcher watcher it tells you how many pts something is...one of my favorite apps!!!

title: Great, educational app!
body: Very engaging - I am a compulsive scanner now! They are still building their bank of food items and I have found a lot of products that aren't in yet , but this is an undeniably useful app for anyone looking to educate themselves and make better food choices.

title: Really cool
body: This app really impressed me. My daughter showed it to me. I didn't use it at first but then I was at the store with the wife and we were using it like crazy. Makes shopping fun and educated you at the same time.

title: Informative
body: This app turned out to be suprisingly fun. I cant help but scan everything i buy when at the grocery store. Allows me to do better choices and i like the list and history section! Fun fun fun

title: Informative

title: Great app
body: This app has really helped my parents be more conscious of what they eat. Now if I could just get the cost of nutritious food down to where they could afford to buy it over the unhealthier options.

title: Very useful app
body: I have frequently used this app to scan a product in order to obtain the points plus value. It has probably found the item 95% of the time.  I find scanning a barcode easier than computing the value. A very helpful app

title: Very useful app

title: Absolutely love the recent upgrade
body: This is the most used app on my phone! I love it! Informational, great usability, looks amazing too. Never glitches and the database is enormous. I also love that they respond very quickly to new food requests. The best!!!

title: Fun for kids - WW friendly
body: My kids love to find items in the store and scan for nutrition info or add to the database - which keeps me shopping and all of us happy. Also gives food point values for WW - which is a HUGE bonus!

title: Excellent
body: This app is excellent it tells you everything you need to know about everything. It is also fun to have a competition to see who can find the healthiest thing in your pantry

title: Great Idea
body: Great idea, can't wait to try it.  I think before I go to the grocery store I'll start scanning my "staples" and edit my list to cut down scanning time in the store.  This will give me practice and hopefully cut down on time scanning in the store.

title: Overall very good
body: Pros: tons of products; easy to add new ones; search by scanning barcode

title: Awesome

title: Great at what it's does!

title: Impossible to cancel

Now it's literally impossible to cancel the pro subscription. I have written to the support team with no response. So now I'm stuck paying $5/month till the end of time??? This is absolutely inexcusable if you ask me.

title: Best food app!

title: Can no longer use without signing up? Pass.
body: It was a good app that i would use on occasion. I just had an occasion..but was greeted with a sign up first screenü§î I closed the app and checked my screen to be sure I'd opened the right app..yep. Nope. Delete.

title: Fooducate
body: I've been using this app about a week now and I'am enjoying it. Lots of great info, recipes, news, motivational community, etc. Definitely a must if you are trying to improve your health!

title: Great food app
body: This app help you eat right and help you maintain your calorie intake. I love this app I've downloaded this app a week or so and I already lost 6lbs this app really tell you if your eat bad or to much which helps me a lot :)

title: Almost perfect food / healthy diet tool
body: Love using this in supermarket - and planning

title: Very Helpful!

title: Why an account is required before I can use the app?
body: This should not be a requirement. Many other successful companies, like Yelp, don't even need an account to use their app.  Give us that option! Name, email, password, etc.

title: Best app of its kind - visuals, info, positive msgs, customer support
body: I had Fooducate when I was just getting into the whole food tracking thing and loved it right away. So much so that every other one I tried fell short. And still does. Like any app, you have to log your food. But you can scan it, create recipes, and it‚Äôs there. It‚Äôs NOT a big deal. If you are invested enough in what goes into your body, this is part of it. I was fascinated by what I didn‚Äôt even realize ‚Äî especially how many carbs I was mindlessly getting. What I LOVE about this app is the easy graphics but also the unmatched scope of its info, and its whole attitude. Instead of feeling like I was depriving myself of something, it gave me GOALS. Getting enough protein has always been a struggle for me so this made it a goal. How close did I get to achieving that goal as the day went on? Well if I was only halfway there, I guess dinner had to be some salmon or chicken instead of corn flakes! EASY. It‚Äôs also one of the few apps that factors in things that are important - dietary plans chemicals and processed foods,gluten, vegetarian, allergies, etc. I know My Fitness Pal is getting a ton of play right now thanks to Under Armour‚Äôs financial backing but I‚Äôve used both and went running back to Fooducate.  I have been hassling their customer service for a week now because I had paid for an unlimited subscription that I thought I didn‚Äôt get back, but it was right there. I would like them to make the upgraded version a different logo so you could tell the difference. I find this to be the most user friendly, make you make good choices, not punish you when you don‚Äôt, adapt to your personal preferences, food tracker out there. It incorporates the exercise calories burned as reported by my fitness tracker too. FOR SURE GET FOODUCATE.

And yes ....it is true it takes a few weeks for them to get the products that you have requested but they are nice enough to send you an e-mail that states it is going to take time due to the number of request that they receive and you will be notified once they have your information for the product you have requested. üÜó.... It is not the end of the world. My suggestion is to eat something else until the information is sent to you. It is what I doüòâ.

Free calories, right? That was my thinking.

title: Yeah it‚Äôs great at first
body: But they are terrible at responding with suggestions or if you are bar code scanning your food in to be submitted. Also the app keeps glitching and logs you out daily . There has to be better apps out there

body: I live this app. I can make a healthy decision fast by just scanning the bar code of a food item. I do wish they had makeup/lotion  on here also

title: One on the BEST on the market
body: This food, nutrition, training app is one of the best on the market (iOS or Android). Please keep improvements on the horizon.

title: Subscription!  $30.00+ per year!!!!
body: I did not realize it would cost annually plus have in app purchases.   Never used it and had to pay an additional year because I didn‚Äôt cancel it.  Just make sure you know what you are purchasing.  I remember installing it but do not remember ever agreeing to pay over 30 bucks a year!

title: Great helpful and important diet tips
body: My username on this app is veggies17 in fact my whole family uses this app this is helpful especially if you are planning on eating healthier because of the diet tips you can make your own repices too this is too Freaking awesome üëè a round of apple get it hahahah

title: Just ok
body: I used to be able to migrate back to the home screen easier on Android. I also don‚Äôt like that I had to sign up with an email address.

title: Keeping track and staying fit!
body: I love this app. It‚Äôs easy to track your daily eating habits. It also gives you a rating scale on food that claims to be healthy. I love that I can check on food I buy from Trader Joe‚Äôs that‚Äôs not so healthy like it claims. The fact that you can scan the UPC code with your phone is great. I can add foods as well.

title: I want to upload new items but don‚Äôt use the mail app on iPhone
body: I like the app. I just want to upload more labels and barcodes to help the database. I don‚Äôt use the mail app apple provides because it‚Äôs clunky.

title: Is it really worth the cost ? NO
body: Personally the free version did enough I feel as though I wasted $89.00 on the paid version - sorry guys it‚Äôs a good app but not $89.00 worth of good  as it is not the complete app.

title: Unable to set up account
body: I tried to set up the account but it kept asking for a 5 digit zip code even though I added it several times. It would not complete the login.

title: Need to add more exercise or burn types
body: I love this app. It has helped me so far with being so much aware and cautious about what I eat.

title: Don‚Äôt waste your money
body: I spent $19.99 for the gluten free option and all it did was tag things that are gluten free! I already know what‚Äôs gluten free! For $20 I can get that info for free and many other apps- a waste of money for stuff my FitBit does already! And gives me WAY more info for free! And when I requested a refund the company said- sorry- not our problem! Not cool!

title: Daily User -LOVE this app
body: Update 20180423: still love this app. I find myself needing to get back to the straight and narrow and my go to is Fooducate. 5 stars all the way

title: I
body: I just installed this app no less than 10 minutes ago, and they asked me to rate it three times, so here you go.

title: Have only been using it for a few minutes, so kind of early to ask for my feedback
body: One problem with my first impression: the options for purchase of a premium feature, like gluten-free and allergies, is shown as $2.99 per month automatically renewing. But if you sign up for 12 months at a time, it states that it reduces your price to $1.43, non-automatically renewing for one year. When you choose this option, the screen shows a total of $19.99 for you to approve the purchase.  But when I did $1.43 times 12 months, the total comes out to only $17.76. Not a huge difference, but still, not a great first impression of transparency, since it‚Äôs a lot quicker to just purchase for $19.99 than to do the math and see that it‚Äôs not equal.

title: need more info on whole foods
body: new user, but not finding a lot of info on whole foods - foods without a bar code.

title: Very disappointing!!!
body: I started using this app but found it very confusing and not helpful. I added the gluten free option for $19.99, which in my opinion is crazy that you have to pay for it.  However when I figured out that it wasn‚Äôt helping me I asked for a refund, in which Apple wouldn‚Äôt grant. Very disappointing. Do not pay for the add one in the app.

title: Premium or Nada?
body: I am currently on Under Armor‚Äôs  My Fitness, getting 50% of the information from them for free. I can‚Äôt be roped into more fitness stuff that has to do with paying out 40 bucks a year. UA offers other premiums, as well as every other AP under, but at this rate I‚Äôll be spending $200 a year just find best hikes, caloric intake/BURN, vitamins and minerals shy of daily goals, bike trails, heart rates, farts/hour and everything else. But you Health applications that came with the phone monitors my movements, mindfulness and many other things, several free apps monitor other things and some even give ME $$$ for every step or exercise.

title: So far very nice
body: Have only used this for several days. Was also trying out MyNetDiary too but this one seemed more intuitive so going with it. Finds food quickly and the bar code scanner is pretty slick. If it helps me reach my goal then mission accomplished.

title: The is no ‚Äúfree‚Äù app here, just options to upgrade.
body: Downloaded this because from the description I couldn‚Äôt tell how much info was in the ‚Äòfree‚Äô version. The answer is pretty much nothing. The publisher should just go ahead and put the premium price on instead of wasting people‚Äôs time and pissing us off to be point we just delete the app in disgust. I don‚Äôt give publishers who do this crap a second chance.

title: Aeynub
body: Great!

title: This app is amazingly helpful!
body: Thank you for making such a helpful, free, beautifully designed app that literally has the ability to change people's lives.

title: Love it!
body: I had downloaded this app a while back and really liked it as it gives much info on ingredients and offers suggestions for healthier alternatives.  For some reason, the auto scan quit working with the last update, but all is well on my iPad again after this latest update. No need to enter bar codes, the scanner works perfectly.  Thank you developers for this very useful app.  I recently started paying attention to ingredients as I began the Cinch! Diet.  Love the diet and love the app.

title: Awesome app
body: Great app and works good. 19/20 of the foods I scan are in the database! That's really awesome. Please keep adding features and more to make this app even BETTER (if it's possible).

title: Outstanding
body: Found out about it from a friend and I cannot believe what manufacturers sneak into foods. This ap really tries to educate the consumer. The salt, sugars and preservatives are endangering our health in this country mainly because people are unaware of what is really in the food they are eating. I highly recommend this little sp to anyone even a tiny bit curious about what you eating

title: Love it!
body: This app is cool! My kids love to check their food ratings and have decided to eat healthier! Shows hidden things in food like colorings, chemicals and trans fat. Sone items I thought were good had hidden potential toxins being reviewed by FDA. Super easy to use too!!

title: Best App of 2011!!
body: Very informative with simple, easy to understand food facts. It's actually made shopping fun, it's like having a dietitian in your pocket! It helps you cut through the bs of advertising without having to read the whole label everytime. A vast database of foods and alternatives is impressive so far and scan results are compiled fast (depending on your connection).

title: Fantastic!
body: I love this app! It's the most useful in providing alternatives that are healthier which has always been my biggest problem when deciding what to eat. I can't say enough about how good this app is! It's also easy to generate a grocery list of the items I'll want to get by adding them as things I like.

title: Great help and quick educational guide
body: Love the bar code scanner!

title: Easy, quick. Love this app.
body: Extremely educational but not overwhelming. I get periodic information and like reading it. I did the Weight Watcher app and it was $$39.00 a month. I think this app was that amount and only a one time fee! I like this app a lot better. I am making progress too!

title: Price
body: When I ‚Äúokayed the purchase, it said $3.99/mo. I‚Äôm charged $39.99! Not okay!

title: Crashes
body: This app crashes consistently on my 3GS. Bummer. It was a cool app when it worked.

title: Good app, but needs overhaul
body: Same problem here. It worked once, very nice. Takes too long to initialize scanner. Crashes non-stop on my 3GS with IOS 4.2. will give it 5 when it works.

title: A Big Help
body: This is a great app.  I like that it tells you synonyms for additives that I didn't know -- for example, a type of cracker contains MSG but uses a different name.

title: Can't type in names
body: Why can't you type in names of products to search for? Scan bar code or shake for random? Random food item, really? Pointless implementation!

title: Needs better 3G support
body: The barcode scanner does not work on a 3G

title: Given a five for constantly looking to better service
body: I first downloaded this app to start picking my groceries in a more health-conscience manner.  I immediately started scanning everything in my fridge and cupboard.  This app has great potential and the fact that the users help updated it adds a sense that it's accurate and reliable.

title: Fantastic app!
body: I highly recommend this app. Already it has helped me eat better and I have also been surprised at some of the ratings of things I thought were healthy! title: Woke me up!
body: Great experience with this app so far. Unlike other diet/health apps, this one tells you the cold, hard truth about what you're consuming and how healthy your current diet really is. It does this through a color-coded grading scale of A to D. In addition, it has everything you would expect and more out of a diet app, including a barcode scanner, list of ingredients for every product, a daily calorie/food log, etc. It has a community forum where users can post and talk, it allows users to contribute by adding images to products that are missing them, and it suggests alternatives to all of those products. There is much incentive through this app for you to get off your lazy a** and fix your health.

title: Love the app, but..........
body: There are a lot of things to love about this app. The fact that one can scan the bar code and see the product information is a huge time saver. I also like the fact that foods are graded with alternatives given. However, some of the products are not available where I live (i.e. we are no where near a Trader Joe's). I am taking away two stars for the following reasons. First, if one misses adding a meal to the Health Tracker, the only way to do this is to move the arrow to yesterday and hope that the product you want is in the Recent, My Meals or a third tab. If not, you cannot go to My Lists since the Health Tracker will go back to Today. Major inconvenience if you forget a snack or a meal side dish. Second, the limit for serving sizes is three and only increments in .5 units. Would prefer additional flexibility like adding Weight to the Health Tracker or have the past date feature here. Third, if my wife makes bean soup with ham, finding the Nutrition information would be difficult. Making a sandwich with chicken, a little mayo and tomato on whole wheat bread requires four different product searches. Can a meal be created outside of the Health Tracker? I haven't seen it yet.

title: LOVING THIS APP AND NOW WITH THE NEW UPDATE SCANNING IS BETTER AND IPOD SUPPORTED!
body: Fooducate inspires ‚Äúwow that is cool‚Äù to me, scanning bar tags near instantly is pretty sweet, then pulling up a good amount of data on the product, even cooler. Eating well from pre-packaged food is a near impossibility anymore. Every single item in the store has a catch. Hidden sodium content, extra carbs, lack of protein, you name it. Fooducate helps with the decision whether to pick something up or put it down for good, an in-store, hand-held guilt trip. Point your iPhone or iPod with camera at a bar code and wait the 3 seconds for it to give you a grade on the healthiness of any product at your grocery store. It is super simple and quick as hell finding the info on your item. It includes a large amount of information on each product also, not just providing the grade, it tells you why it gives that grade, what the problem with the product is (30% of your daily salt in 1 serving, 1/2, of 1 can of Chef Boyardee Ravioli), alternative products to what you‚Äôve scanned that are better options,  and details about the red flags affecting the grade. It is pretty depressing to know your lunch is 60% of your entire daily allotment of salt, knowing you‚Äôre killing yourself with ravioli is pretty damned depressing.

title: So helpful!

title: Fooducate
body: Upon hearing that my boyfriend downloaded this app, I admit that I was skeptical. It's not hard to identify unhealthy foods; if it is packaged or wrapped it's cause for concern! I downloaded it today at the grocery store to find the safest butter and have used it at least 50 times so far. It is BRILLIANTLY informative as far as specific health concerns ranging from artificial colors to preservatives to sulfites to fiber content...easy to use, amazing app. If an item is not on their database, you can take a pic and send it to them, so they can add it. Well done!
